000002,000002:                                                                                          	# Copyright:    Public domain.
000003,000003:                                                                                          	# Filename:     MAIN.agc
000004,000004:                                                                                          	# Purpose:      Part of the source code for Aurora (revision 12),
000005,000005:                                                                                          	# Assembler:    yaYUL
000006,000006:                                                                                          	# Contact:      Ron Burkey <info@sandroid.org>.
000007,000007:                                                                                          	# Website:      https://www.ibiblio.org/apollo/index.html
000008,000008:                                                                                          	# Page scans:   https://archive.org/details/aurora00dapg
000009,000009:                                                                                          	# Mod history:  2016-09-20 JL   Created.
000010,000010:                                                                                          	#               
000011,000011:                                                                                          	# MAIN.agc is a little different from the other Aurora12 files  
000012,000012:                                                                                          	# provided, in that it doesn't represent anything that appears 
000013,000013:                                                                                          	# directly in the original source.  What we have done for 
000014,000014:                                                                                          	# organizational purposes is to split the huge monolithic source 
000015,000015:                                                                                          	# code into smaller, more manageable chunks--i.e., into individual
000016,000016:                                                                                          	# source files.  Those files are rejoined within this file as 
000017,000017:                                                                                          	# "includes".  It just makes it a little easier to work with.  The
000018,000018:                                                                                          	# code chunks correspond to natural divisions into sub-programs.  
000019,000019:                                                                                          	# The divisions are by the assembly listing itself.
000020,000020: 
000021,000021:                                                                                          	# Source file name                                Starting Page
000022,000022:                                                                                          	# ----------------                                -------------
000023,000023: 
000024,000024: $ASSEMBLY_AND_OPERATION_INFORMATION.agc		# 1
000026,000002:                                                                                          	# Copyright:    Public domain.

000046,000022:                                                                                          	#       date of the program revision or the assembly.]

000049,000025:                                                                                          	# reduction in image quality) are available online at 
000050,000026:                                                                                          	#       https://www.ibiblio.org/apollo.  
000051,000027:                                                                                          	# The original high-quality digital images are available at archive.org:

000055,000031:                                                                                          	# VERB INFORMATION.
000056,000032: 
000057,000033:                                                                                          	#  REGULAR VERBS
000058,000034:                                                                                          	# 01  DISPLAY OCTAL COMP 1 (R1)
000059,000035:                                                                                          	# 02  DISPLAY OCTAL COMP 2 (R1)
000060,000036:                                                                                          	# 03  DISPLAY OCTAL COMP 3 (R1)
000061,000037:                                                                                          	# 04  DISPLAY OCTAL COMP 1,2 (R1,R2)
000062,000038:                                                                                          	# 05  DISPLAY OCTAL COMP 1,2,3 (R1,R2,R3)
000063,000039:                                                                                          	# 06  DECIMAL DISPLAY
000064,000040:                                                                                          	# 07  DP DECIMAL DISPLAY (R1,R2)
000065,000041:                                                                                          	# 10  SPARE
000066,000042:                                                                                          	# 11  MONITOR OCT COMP 1 (R1)
000067,000043:                                                                                          	# 12  MONITOR OCT COMP 2 (R1)
000068,000044:                                                                                          	# 13  MONITOR OCT COMP 3 (R1)
000069,000045:                                                                                          	# 14  MONITOR OCT COMP 1,2 (R1)
000070,000046:                                                                                          	# 15  MONITOR OCT COMP 1,2,3 (R1,R2,R3)
000071,000047:                                                                                          	# 16  MONITOR DECIMAL
000072,000048:                                                                                          	# 17  MONITOR DP DECIMAL (R1,R2)
000073,000049:                                                                                          	# 20  SPARE
000074,000050:                                                                                          	# 21  LOAD COMP 1 (R1)
000075,000051:                                                                                          	# 22  LOAD COMP 2 (R2)
000076,000052:                                                                                          	# 23  LOAD COMP 3 (R3)
000077,000053:                                                                                          	# 24  LOAD COMP 1,2 (R1,R2)
000078,000054:                                                                                          	# 25  LOAD COMP 1,2,3 (R1,R2,R3)
000079,000055:                                                                                          	# 26  SPARE
000080,000056:                                                                                          	# 27  FIXED MEMORY DISPLAY 
000081,000057:                                                                                          	# 30  REQUEST EXECUTIVE
000082,000058:                                                                                          	# 31  REQUEST WAITLIST
000083,000059:                                                                                          	# 32  C(R2) INTO R3, C(R1) INTO R2
000084,000060:                                                                                          	# 33  PROCEED WITHOUT DATA
000085,000061:                                                                                          	# 34  TERMINATE CURRENT TEST OR LOAD REQUEST
000086,000062:                                                                                          	# 35  TEST LIGHTS
000087,000063:                                                                                          	# 36  FRESH START
000088,000064:                                                                                          	# 37  CHANGE MAJOR MODE
000089,000065:                                                                                          	# END OF REGULAR VERBS
000090,000066: 
000091,000067:                                                                                          	# EXTENDED VERBS
000092,000068:                                                                                          	# 40  ZERO (USED WITH NOUNS 20, 40, AND 70)
000093,000069:                                                                                          	# 41  COARSE ALIGN (USED WITH NOUNS 20, 40, AND 70)
000094,000070:                                                                                          	# 42  FINE ALIGN IMU
000095,000071:                                                                                          	# 43  LOAD IMU ATTITUDE ERROR METERS
000096,000072:                                                                                          	# 44  ILLEGAL VERB
000097,000073:                                                                                          	# 45  COMMAND LR TO POSITION 2
000098,000074:                                                                                          	# 46  SAMPLE RADAR DATA ONCE PER SECOND
000099,000075:                                                                                          	# 47  PERFORM LEM FCS TEST
000100,000076:                                                                                          	# 50  PLEASE PERFORM
000102,000078:                                                                                          	# 51  PLEASE MARK
000103,000079:                                                                                          	# 52  PLEASE MARK Y
000104,000080:                                                                                          	# 53  PLEASE MARK X OR Y
000105,000081:                                                                                          	# 54  PULSE TORQUE GYROS
000106,000082:                                                                                          	# 55  ALIGN TIME
000107,000083:                                                                                          	# 56  PERFORM BANKSUM
000108,000084:                                                                                          	# 57  PERFORM SYSTEM TEST
000109,000085:                                                                                          	# 60  ILLEGAL VERB
000110,000086:                                                                                          	# 61  ILLEGAL VERB
000111,000087:                                                                                          	# 62  SCAN LEM INBITS
000112,000088:                                                                                          	# 63  INITIALIZE AGS
000113,000089:                                                                                          	# 64  ILLEGAL VERB
000114,000090:                                                                                          	# 65  ILLEGAL VERB
000115,000091:                                                                                          	# 66  ILLEGAL VERB
000116,000092:                                                                                          	# 67  ILLEGAL VERB
000117,000093:                                                                                          	# 70  ILLEGAL VERB
000118,000094:                                                                                          	# 71  ILLEGAL VERB
000119,000095:                                                                                          	# 72  ILLEGAL VERB
000120,000096:                                                                                          	# 73       RHC USED FOR MINIMUM IMPULSE
000121,000097:                                                                                          	# 74       RHC USED FOR RATE COMMAND
000122,000098:                                                                                          	# 75       DIGITAL AUTOPILOT WIDE DEADBAND
000123,000099:                                                                                          	# 76       DIGITAL AUTOPILOT NARROW DEADBAND
000124,000100:                                                                                          	# 77  ILLEGAL VERB

000201,000177:                                                                                          	# OPTICS SUB-SYSTEM
000202,000178: 
000203,000179:                                                                                          	# 00105    MARK BUTTONS NOT AVAILABLE

000205,000181:                                                                                          	# 00112    MARK NOT BEING ACCEPTED
000206,000182:                                                                                          	# 00113    NO INBITS
000207,000183:                                                                                          	# 00114    MARK MADE BUT NOT DESIRED
000208,000184:                                                                                          	# 00115    X MARK NOT MADE

000215,000191:                                                                                          	# 00212    PIPA FAIL BUT PIPA IS NOT BEING USED
000216,000192:                                                                                          	# 00213    IMU NOT OPERATING WITH TURN-ON REQUEST
000217,000193:                                                                                          	# 00214    PROGRAM USING IMU WHEN TURNED OFF

000223,000199:                                                                                          	# 00403    STAR OUT OF FIELD OF VIEW

000285,000011: 
000286,000012:                                                                                          	# This source code has been transcribed or otherwise adapted from
000287,000013:                                                                                          	# digitized images of a hardcopy from the private collection of
000288,000014:                                                                                          	# Don Eyles.  The digitization was performed by archive.org.
000289,000015: 
000290,000016:                                                                                          	# Notations on the hardcopy document read, in part:
000291,000017: 
000292,000018:                                                                                          	#       473423A YUL SYSTEM FOR BLK2: REVISION 12 of PROGRAM AURORA BY DAP GROUP
000293,000019:                                                                                          	#       NOV 10, 1966
000294,000020: 
000295,000021:                                                                                          	#       [Note that this is the date the hardcopy was made, not the
000296,000022:                                                                                          	#       date of the program revision or the assembly.]
000297,000023: 
000298,000024:                                                                                          	# The scan images (with suitable reduction in storage size and consequent
000299,000025:                                                                                          	# reduction in image quality) are available online at

000303,000029: 
000305,000031: ???????                        A                  EQUALS   0                             	#
000306,000032: ???????                        L                  EQUALS   1                             	# L AND Q ARE BOTH CHANNELS AND REGISTERS.
000307,000033: ???????                        Q                  EQUALS   2                             	#
000308,000034: ???????                        EBANK              EQUALS   3                             	#
000309,000035: ???????                        FBANK              EQUALS   4                             	#
000310,000036: ???????                        Z                  EQUALS   5                             	# ADJACENT TO FBANK AND BBANK FOR DXCH Z
000311,000037: ???????                        BBANK              EQUALS   6                             	# (DTCB) AND DXCH FBANK (DTCF).
000312,000038:                                                                                          	# REGISTER 7 IS A ZERO-SOURCE, USED BY ZL.
000313,000039: 
000314,000040: ???????                        ARUPT              EQUALS   10                            	# INTERRUPT STORAGE.
000315,000041: ???????                        LRUPT              EQUALS   11                            	#
000316,000042: ???????                        QRUPT              EQUALS   12                            	#
000317,000043: ???????                        SAMPTIME           EQUALS   13                            	# SAMPLED TIME 1 & 2.
000318,000044: ???????                        ZRUPT              EQUALS   15                            	# (13 AND 14 ARE SPARES.)
000319,000045: ???????                        BANKRUPT           EQUALS   16                            	# USUALLY HOLDS FBANK OR BBANK.
000320,000046: ???????                        BRUPT              EQUALS   17                            	# RESUME ADDRESS AS WELL.
000321,000047: 
000322,000048: ???????                        CYR                EQUALS   20                            	#
000323,000049: ???????                        SR                 EQUALS   21                            	#
000324,000050: ???????                        CYL                EQUALS   22                            	#
000325,000051: ???????                        EDOP               EQUALS   23                            	# EDITS INTERPRETIVE OPERATION CODE PAIRS.
000326,000052: 
000327,000053: 
000328,000054: ???????                        TIME2              EQUALS   24                            	#
000329,000055: ???????                        TIME1              EQUALS   25                            	#

000399,000125: 
000400,000126:                                                                                          	#       THE FOLLOWING SET COMPRISES THE INTERRUPT TEMPORARY STORAGE POO
000401,000127: 
000402,000128:                                                                                          	#       ANY OF THESE MAY BE USED AS TEMPORARIES DURING INTERRUPT OR WITH INTERRUPT INHIBITED. THE ITEMP SERIES
000403,000129:                                                                                          	# IS USED DURING CALLS TO THE EXECUTIVE AND WAITLIST - THE RUPTREGS ARE NOT.
000404,000130: 
000405,000131:    0065                        ITEMP1             ERASE                                  	#
000406,000132:    0066     0065               WAITEXIT           EQUALS   ITEMP1                        	#
000407,000133:    0066     0065               EXECTEM1           EQUALS   ITEMP1                        	#
000408,000134:

000410,000136:    0067     0066               WAITBANK           EQUALS   ITEMP2                        	#
000411,000137:    0067     0066               EXECTEM2           EQUALS   ITEMP2                        	#
000412,000138: 
000413,000139:    0070                                           SETLOC   70                            	#
000414,000140: 
000415,000141:    0070                        ITEMP3             ERASE                                  	#
000416,000142:    0071     0070               RUPTSTOR           EQUALS   ITEMP3                        	#
000417,000143:    0071     0070               WAITADR            EQUALS   ITEMP3                        	#
000418,000144:    0071     0070               NEWPRIO            EQUALS   ITEMP3                        	#
000419,000145:

000422,000148:    0072     0071               WAITTEMP           EQUALS   ITEMP4                        	#
000423,000149:

000426,000152:    0073     0072               NEWLOC             EQUALS   ITEMP5                        	#
000427,000153:

000429,000155:    0074     0073               NEWLOC+1           EQUALS   ITEMP6                        	#

000431,000157:    0074                        RUPTREG1           ERASE                                  	#
000432,000158:    0075                        RUPTREG2           ERASE                                  	#
000433,000159:    0076                        RUPTREG3           ERASE                                  	#
000434,000160:    0077                        RUPTREG4           ERASE                                  	#
000435,000161:    0100     0077               KEYTEMP1           EQUALS   RUPTREG4                      	#

000437,000163: 
000438,000164:                                                                                          	#       THE FOLLOWING ARE EXECUTIVE TEMPORARIES WHICH MAY BE USED BETWEEN CCS NEWJOB INQUIRIES.
000439,000165:    0100                        INTB15+            ERASE                                  	# REFLECTS 15TH BIT OF INDEXABLE ADDRESSES
000440,000166:    0101     0100               DSEXIT             =        INTB15+                       	# RETURN FOR DSPIN
000441,000167:    0101     0100               EXITEM             =        INTB15+                       	# RETURN FOR SCALE FACTOR ROUTINE SELECT
000442,000168:    0101     0100               BLANKRET           =        INTB15+                       	# RETURN FOR 2BLANK
000443,000169: 
000444,000170:    0101                        INTBIT15           ERASE                                  	# SIMILAR TO ABOVE.
000445,000171:    0102     0101               WRDRET             =        INTBIT15                      	# RETURN FOR 5BLANK
000446,000172:    0102     0101               WDRET              =        INTBIT15                      	# RETURN FOR DSPWD
000447,000173:    0102     0101               DECRET             =        INTBIT15                      	# RETURN FOR PUTCOM(DEC LOAD)
000448,000174:    0102     0101               21/22REG           =        INTBIT15                      	# TEMP FOR CHARIN
000449,000175: 
000450,000176:                                                                                          	#       THE REGISTERS BETWEEN ADDRWD AND PRIORITY MUST STAY IN THE FOLLOWING ORDER FOR INTERPRETIVE TRACE.
000451,000177: 
000452,000178:    0102                        ADDRWD             ERASE                                  	# 12 BIT INTERPRETIVE OPERAND SUB-ADDRESS.
000453,000179:    0103                        POLISH             ERASE                                  	# HOLDS CADR MADE FROM POLISH ADDRESS.
000454,000180:    0104     0103               UPDATRET           =        POLISH                        	# RETURN FOR UPDATNN, UPDATVB
000455,000181:    0104     0103               CHAR               =        POLISH                        	# TEMP FOR CHARIN
000456,000182:    0104     0103               ERCNT              =        POLISH                        	# COUNTER FOR ERROR LIGHT RESET
000457,000183:    0104     0103               DECOUNT            =        POLISH                        	# COUNTER FOR SCALING AND DISPLAY (DEC)
000458,000184: 
000459,000185:    0104                        FIXLOC             ERASE                                  	# WORK AREA ADDRESS.
000460,000186: 
000461,000187:    0105                        OVFIND             ERASE                                  	# SET NON-ZERO ON OVERFLOW.
000462,000188: 
000463,000189:    0106                        VBUF               ERASE    +5                            	# TEMPORARY STORAGE USED FOR VECTORS.
000464,000190:    0114     0106               SGNON              =        VBUF                          	# TEMP FOR +,- ON
000465,000191:    0114     0106               NOUNTEM            =        VBUF                          	# COUNTER FOR MIXNOUN FETCH
000466,000192:    0114     0106               DISTEM             =        VBUF                          	# COUNTER FOR OCTAL DISPLAY VERBS
000467,000193:    0114     0106               DECTEM             =        VBUF                          	# COUNTER FOR FETCH (DEC DISPLAY VERBS)
000468,000194: 
000469,000195:    0114     0107               SGNOFF             =        VBUF       +1                 	# TEMP FOR +,- ON
000470,000196:    0114     0107               NVTEMP             =        VBUF       +1                 	# TEMP FOR NVSUB
000471,000197:    0114     0107               SFTEMP1            =        VBUF       +1                 	# STORAGE FOR SF CONST HI PART(=SFTEMP2-1)
000472,000198: 
000473,000199:    0114     0110               CODE               =        VBUF       +2                 	# FOR DSPIN
000474,000200:    0114     0110               SFTEMP2            =        VBUF       +2                 	# STORAGE FOR SF CONST LO PART(=SFTEMP1+1)
000476,000202:    0114     0111               MIXTEMP            =        VBUF       +3                 	# FOR MIXNOUN DATA
000477,000203:    0114     0111               SIGNRET            =        VBUF       +3                 	# RETURN FOR +,- ON
000478,000204: 
000479,000205:                                                                                          	# ALSO MIXTEMP+1 = VBUF+4, MIXTEMP+2 = VBUF+5.
000480,000206: 
000481,000207:    0114                        BUF                ERASE    +2                            	# TEMPORARY SCALAR STORAGE.
000482,000208:    0117                        BUF2               ERASE    +1                            	#
000483,000209:    0121     0114               INDEXLOC           EQUALS   BUF                           	# CONTAINS ADDRESS OF SPECIFIED INDEX.
000484,000210:    0121     0114               SWWORD             EQUALS   BUF                           	# ADDRESS OF SWITCH WORD.
000485,000211:    0121     0115               SWBIT              EQUALS   BUF        +1                 	# SWITCH BIT WITHIN SWITCH WORD
000486,000212:    0121                        MPTEMP             ERASE                                  	# TEMPORARY USED IN MULTIPLY AND SHIFT.
000487,000213:    0122                        DOTINC             ERASE                                  	# COMPONENT INCREMENT FOR DOT SUBROUTINE.
000488,000214:    0123     0122               DVSIGN             EQUALS   DOTINC                        	# DETERMINES SIGN OF DDV RESULT.
000489,000215:    0123     0122               ESCAPE             EQUALS   DOTINC                        	# USED IN ARCSIN/ARCCOS.
000490,000216:    0123     0122               ENTRET             =        DOTINC                        	# EXIT FROM ENTER
000491,000217: 
000492,000218:    0123                        DOTRET             ERASE                                  	# RETURN FROM DOT SUBROUTINE.
000493,000219:    0124     0123               DVNORMCT           EQUALS   DOTRET                        	# DIVIDEND NORMALIZATION COUNT IN DDV.
000494,000220:    0124     0123               ESCAPE2            EQUALS   DOTRET                        	# ALTERNATE ARCSIN/ARCCOS SWITCH.
000495,000221:    0124     0123               WDCNT              =        DOTRET                        	# CHAR COUNTER FOR DSPWD
000496,000222:    0124     0123               INREL              =        DOTRET                        	# INPUT BUFFER SELECTOR ( X,Y,Z, REG )
000497,000223: 
000498,000224:    0124                        MATINC             ERASE                                  	# VECTOR INCREMENT IN MXV AND VXM.
000499,000225:    0125     0124               MAXDVSW            EQUALS   MATINC                        	# +0 IF DP QUOTIENT IS NEAR ONE - ELSE -1.
000500,000226:    0125     0124               POLYCNT            EQUALS   MATINC                        	# POLYNOMIAL LOOP COUNTER
000501,000227:    0125     0124               DSPMMTEM           =        MATINC                        	# DSPCOUNT SAVE FOR DSPMM
000502,000228:    0125     0124               MIXBR              =        MATINC                        	# INDICATOR FOR MIXED OR NORMAL NOUN
000503,000229: 
000504,000230:    0125                        TEM1               ERASE                                  	# EXEC TEMP
000505,000231:    0126     0125               POLYRET            =        TEM1                          	#
000506,000232:    0126     0125               DSREL              =        TEM1                          	# REL ADDRESS FOR DSPIN
000507,000233:

000510,000236:    0127     0126               IDADDTEM           =        TEM2                          	# MIXNOUN INDIRECT ADDRESS STORAGE
000511,000237:

000536,000262:                                                                                          	#       STORAGE USED BY THE EXECUTIVE.
000537,000263: 
000538,000264:    0140                        MPAC               ERASE    +6                            	# MULTI-PURPOSE ACCUMULATOR.
000539,000265:    0147                        MODE               ERASE                                  	# +1 FOR TP, +0 FOR DP, OR -1 FOR VECTOR.
000540,000266:    0150                        LOC                ERASE                                  	# LOCATION ASSOCIATED WITH JOB.
000541,000267:    0151                        BANKSET            ERASE                                  	# USUALLY CONTAINS BBANK SETTING.
000542,000268:    0152                        PUSHLOC            ERASE                                  	# WORD OF PACKED INTERPRETIVE PARAMETERS.

000544,000270:

000546,000272: 
000548,000274:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING REGISTERS ARE RESERVED FOR PINBALL
000549,000275: 
000550,000276: 
000551,000277:                                                                                          	# RESERVED FOR PINBALL EXECUTIVE ACTION
000552,000278: 
000553,000279:    0264                        DSPCOUNT           ERASE                                  	# DISPLAY POSITION INDICATOR
000554,000280:    0265                        DECBRNCH           ERASE                                  	# +DEC, - DEC, OCT INDICATOR
000555,000281:    0266                        VERBREG            ERASE                                  	# VERB CODE
000556,000282:    0267                        NOUNREG            ERASE                                  	# NOUN CODE
000557,000283:    0270                        XREG               ERASE                                  	# R1 INPUT BUFFER
000558,000284:    0271                        YREG               ERASE                                  	# R2 INPUT BUFFER
000559,000285:    0272                        ZREG               ERASE                                  	# R3 INPUT BUFFER
000560,000286:    0273                        XREGLP             ERASE                                  	# LO PART OF XREG (FOR DEC CONV ONLY)
000561,000287:    0274                        YREGLP             ERASE                                  	# LO PART OF YREG (FOR DEC CONV ONLY)
000562,000288:    0275                        ZREGLP             ERASE                                  	# LO PART OF ZREG (FOR DEC CONV ONLY)
000563,000289:    0276                        MODREG             ERASE                                  	# MODE CODE
000564,000290:    0277                        DSPLOCK            ERASE                                  	# KEYBOARD/SUBROUTINE CALL INTERLOCK
000565,000291:    0300                        REQRET             ERASE                                  	# RETURN REGISTER FOR LOAD

000567,000293:    0302                        CLPASS             ERASE                                  	# PASS INDICATOR CLEAR

000569,000295:    0304                        NOUNCADR           ERASE                                  	# MACHINE CADR FOR NOUN
000570,000296:    0305                        MONSAVE            ERASE                                  	# N/V CODE FOR MONITOR. (= MONSAVE1-1)
000571,000297:    0306                        MONSAVE1           ERASE                                  	# NOUNCADR FOR MONITOR(MATBS) =MONSAVE+1

000573,000299:    0323                        CADRSTOR           ERASE                                  	# ENDIDLE STORAGE
000574,000300:    0324                        GRABLOCK           ERASE                                  	# INTERNAL INTERLOCK FOR DISPLAY SYSTEM 
000575,000301:    0325                        NVQTEM             ERASE                                  	# NVSUB STORAGE FOR CALLING ADDRESS
000576,000302:                                                                                          	# MUST = NVBNKTEM-1.

000578,000304:                                                                                          	# MUST = NVQTEM+1
000579,000305:    0327                        DSPLIST            ERASE    +2                            	# WAITING LIST FOR DSP SYST INTERNAL USE
000580,000306:    0332                        EXTVBACT           ERASE                                  	# EXTENDED VERB ACTIVITY INTERLOCK
000581,000307:    0333                        DSPTEM1            ERASE    +2                            	# BUFFER STORAGE AREA 1 (MOSTLY FOR TIME)

001099,000825: 
001100,000826: E7,1431                        RTSTDEX            ERASE                                  	#
001101,000827: E7,1432                        RTSTMAX            ERASE                                  	# 66 FOR HI SPEED, 6 FOR LOW SPEED RR,
001102,000828:                                                                                          	# AND 18 FOR LOW SPEED LR.
001103,000829: E7,1433                        RTSTBASE           ERASE                                  	# USED FOR CYCLIC SAMPLING.
001104,000830: E7,1434                        RTSTLOC            ERASE                                  	# GOES 0(6)RTSTMAX
001105,000831: E7,1435  E7,1434               RSTKLOC            EQUALS   RTSTLOC                       	#
001106,000832: E7,1435                        RSAMPDT            ERASE                                  	# PNZ FOR CYCLIC SAMPLING, -1 FOR HI SPEED
001107,000833:                                                                                          	# INSERT +0 HERE MANUALLY TO TERMINATE TST
001108,000834: E7,1436                        RFAILCNT           ERASE                                  	#
001109,000835: E7,1437                        RSTACK             ERASE    +71D                          	# BUFFERS FOR RADAR TESTING.
001110,000836: 
001111,000837:                                                                                          	# AGS INITIALIZATION
001112,000838: E7,1547                        AGSBUFF            ERASE    +27D                          	#
001113,000839:                                                                                          	#       STORAGE FOR INBIT SCANNER.
001114,000840: 
001115,000841: E7,1603                        LAST30             ERASE    +2                            	# LAST SAMPLED INBITS.
001116,000842: E7,1606                        MSGCNT             ERASE                                  	#

001282,000019:                                                                                          	#       NOV 10, 1966
001283,000020: 
001284,000021:                                                                                          	#       [Note that this is the date the hardcopy was made, not the
001285,000022:                                                                                          	#       date of the program revision or the assembly.]
001286,000023: 
001287,000024:                                                                                          	# The scan images (with suitable reduction in storage size and consequent 
001288,000025:                                                                                          	# reduction in image quality) are available online at 
001289,000026:                                                                                          	#       https://www.ibiblio.org/apollo.  
001290,000027:                                                                                          	# The original high-quality digital images are available at archive.org:
001291,000028:                                                                                          	#       https://archive.org/details/aurora00dapg
001292,000029: 
001294,000031:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING ROUTINE CAN BE USED TO CALL A SUBROUTINE IN ANOTHER BANK. IN THE BANKCALL VERSION, THE
001295,000032:                                                                                          	# CADR OF THE SUBROUTINE IMMEDIATELY FOLLOWS THE TC BANKCALL INSTRUCTION, WITH C(A) AND C(L) PRESERVED.
001296,000033: 
001297,000034:    4063                                           SETLOC   ENDINTFF                      	#
001298,000035:    4063           52120        BANKCALL           DXCH     BUF2                          	# SAVE INCOMING A,L.
001299,000036:    4064           50002                           INDEX    Q                             	# PICK UP CADR.
001300,000037:    4065           30000                           CA       0                             	#
001301,000038:    4066           24002                           INCR     Q                             	# SO WE RETURN TO THE LOC. AFTER THE CADR.
001302,000039: 
001303,000040:                                                                                          	# SWCALL IS IDENTICAL TO BANKCALL, EXCEPT THAT THE CADR ARRIVES IN A.
001304,000041: 
001305,000042:    4067           54001        SWCALL             TS       L                             	#
001306,000043:    4070           22004                           LXCH     FBANK                         	# SWITCH BANKS, SAVING RETURN.
001307,000044:    4071           76426                           MASK     LOW10                         	# GET SUB-ADDRESS OF CADR.
001308,000045:    4072           56002                           XCH      Q                             	# A,L NOW CONTAINS DP RETURN.
001309,000046:    4073           52120                           DXCH     BUF2                          	# RESTORING INPUTS IF THIS IS A BANKCALL.
001310,000047:    4074           50002                           INDEX    Q                             	#
001311,000048:    4075           02000                           TC       10000                         	# SETTING Q TO SWRETURN.
001312,000049: 
001313,000050:    4076           56120        SWRETURN           XCH      BUF2       +1                 	# COMES HERE TO RETURN TO CALLER. C(A,L)
001314,000051:    4077           56004                           XCH      FBANK                         	# ARE PRESERVED FOR RETURN.
001315,000052:    4100           56120                           XCH      BUF2       +1                 	#
001316,000053:    4101           00117                           TC       BUF2                          	#
001317,000054: 
001318,000055:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING ROUTINE CAN BE USED AS A UNILATERAL JUMP WITH C(A,L) PRESERVED AND THE CADR IMMEDIATELY
001319,000056:                                                                                          	# FOLLOWING THE TC POSTJUMP INSTRUCTION.
001320,000057: 
001321,000058:    4102           56002        POSTJUMP           XCH      Q                             	# SAVE INCOMING C(A).
001322,000059:    4103           50000                           INDEX    A                             	# GET CADR.
001323,000060:    4104           30000                           CA       0                             	#
001324,000061: 
001325,000062:                                                                                          	# BANKJUMP IS THE SAME AS POSTJUMP, EXCEPT THAT THE CADR ARRIVES IN A.
001326,000063: 
001327,000064:    4105           54004        BANKJUMP           TS       FBANK                         	#
001328,000065:    4106           76426                           MASK     LOW10                         	#
001329,000066:    4107           56002                           XCH      Q                             	# RESTORING INPUT C(A) IF THIS WAS A
001330,000067:    4110           50002                           INDEX    Q                             	# POSTJUMP.
001331,000068:    4111           12000                           TCF      10000                         	#
001332,000069: 
001334,000071:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING ROUTINE GETS THE RETURN CADR SAVED BY SWCALL OR BANKCALL AND LEAVES IT IN A.
001335,000072: 
001336,000073:    4112           36426        MAKECADR           CAF      LOW10                         	#
001337,000074:    4113           70117                           MASK     BUF2                          	#
001338,000075:    4114           60120                           AD       BUF2       +1                 	#
001339,000076:    4115           00002                           TC       Q                             	#
001340,000077: 
001341,000078:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING ROUTINE OBTAINS THE TWO WORDS BEGINNING AT THE ADDRESS ARRIVING IN A, AND LEAVES THEM IN
001342,000079:                                                                                          	# A,L.
001343,000080: 
001344,000081:    4116           54001        DATACALL           TS       L                             	#
001345,000082:    4117           22004                           LXCH     FBANK                         	#
001346,000083:    4120           22121                           LXCH     MPTEMP                        	# SAVE FORMER BANK.
001347,000084:    4121           76426                           MASK     LOW10                         	#
001348,000085:    4122           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
001349,000086:    4123           50000                           INDEX    A                             	#
001350,000087:    4124           32001                           DCA      10000                         	#
001351,000088: 
001352,000089:    4125           56121                           XCH      MPTEMP                        	#
001353,000090:    4126           54004                           TS       FBANK                         	# RESTORE FBANK.
001354,000091:    4127           30121                           CA       MPTEMP                        	#
001355,000092:    4130           00002                           TC       Q                             	#
001356,000093: 
001358,000095:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING SUBROUTINES PROVIDE TO THE BASIC PROGRAMMER ENTRY INTO AND RETURN FROM ANY INTERPRETIVE
001359,000096:                                                                                          	# CODING WHICH DOES NOT USE THE ENTERING CONTENTS OF Q AND WHICH RETURNS VIA DANZIG. C(A) AND C(L) ARE SAVED.
001360,000097: 
001361,000098:                                                                                          	# USER'S RESPONSIBILITY TO FILL IN ADVANCE THE APPROPRIATE OPERAND AND ADDRESS REGISTERS USED BY THE
001362,000099:                                                                                          	# INTERPRETIVE CODING SUCH AS MPAC, BUF, ADDRWD, ETC.; AND TO CONFIRM THAT THE INTERPRETIVE CODING MEETS THE
001363,000100:                                                                                          	# ABOVE RESTRICTIONS WITH RESPECT TO Q AND DANZIG.
001364,000101: 
001365,000102:                                                                                          	# USEPRET AND USPRCADR MUST NOT BE USED IN INTERRUPT.
001366,000103: 
001367,000104:                                                                                          	# 1. USEPRET ACCESSES INTERPRETIVE CODING WHICH CAN BE ENTERED WITHOUT CHANGING FBANK.
001368,000105:                                                                                          	#    THE CALLING SEQUENCE IS AS FOLLOWS:
001369,000106: 
001370,000107:                                                                                          	# L             TC              USEPRET
001371,000108:                                                                                          	# L+1           TC,TCF          INTPRETX                        TC,TCF MEANS TC OR TCF
001372,000109:                                                                                          	#                                                               INTPRETX IS THE INTERPRETIVE CODING
001373,000110:                                                                                          	#                                                               RETURN IS TO L+2
001374,000111: 
001375,000112:                                                                                          	# 2. USPRCADR ACCESSES INTERPRETIVE CODING IN OTHER THAN THE USER'S FBANK. THE CALLING SEQUENCE IS AS FOLLOWS:
001376,000113: 
001377,000114:                                                                                          	# L             TC              USPRCADR
001378,000115:                                                                                          	# L+1           CADR            INTPRETX                        INTPRETX IS THE INTERPRETIVE CODING
001379,000116:                                                                                          	#                                                               RETURN IS TO L+2
001380,000117: 
001381,000118:    4131           56002        USEPRET            XCH      Q                             	# FETCH Q, SAVING A
001382,000119:    4132           54150                           TS       LOC                           	# L+1 TO LOC
001383,000120:    4133           30004                           CA       FBANK                         	#
001384,000121:    4134           54151                           TS       BANKSET                       	# USERS BANK TO BANKSET
001385,000122:    4135           37650                           CA       BIT8                          	#
001386,000123:    4136           54023                           TS       EDOP                          	# EXIT INSTRUCTION TO EDOP
001387,000124:    4137           30002                           CA       Q                             	# RETRIEVE ORIGINAL A
001388,000125:    4140           00150                           TC       LOC                           	#
001389,000126: 
001390,000127:    4141           54150        USPRCADR           TS       LOC                           	# SAVE A
001391,000128:    4142           37650                           CA       BIT8                          	#
001392,000129:    4143           54023                           TS       EDOP                          	# EXIT INSTRUCTION TO EDOP
001393,000130:    4144           30004                           CA       FBANK                         	#
001394,000131:    4145           54151                           TS       BANKSET                       	# USERS BANK TO BANKSET
001395,000132:    4146           50002                           INDEX    Q                             	#
001396,000133:    4147           30000                           CA       0                             	#
001397,000134:    4150           54004                           TS       FBANK                         	# INTERPRETIVE BANK TO FBANK
001398,000135:    4151           76426                           MASK     LOW10                         	# YIELDS INTERPRETIVE RELATIVE ADDRESS
001399,000136:    4152           56002                           XCH      Q                             	# INTERPRETIVE ADDRESS TO Q, FETCHING L+1
001400,000137:    4153           56150                           XCH      LOC                           	# L+1 TO LOC, RETRIEVING ORIGINAL A
001401,000138:    4154           50002                           INDEX    Q                             	#
001402,000139:    4155           12000                           TCF      10000                         	#
001403,000140: 
001405,000142:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING ROUTINES ARE IDENTICAL TO BANKCALL AND SWCALL EXCEPT THAT THEY ARE USED IN INTERRUPT.
001406,000143: 
001407,000144:    4156           52077        IBNKCALL           DXCH     RUPTREG3                      	# USES RUPTREG3,4 FOR DP RETURN ADDRESS.
001408,000145:    4157           50002                           INDEX    Q                             	#
001409,000146:    4160           30000                           CAF      0                             	#
001410,000147:    4161           24002                           INCR     Q                             	#
001411,000148: 
001412,000149:    4162           54001        ISWCALLL           TS       L                             	#
001413,000150:    4163           22004                           LXCH     FBANK                         	#
001414,000151:    4164           76426                           MASK     LOW10                         	#
001415,000152:    4165           56002                           XCH      Q                             	#
001416,000153:    4166           52077                           DXCH     RUPTREG3                      	#
001417,000154:    4167           50002                           INDEX    Q                             	#
001418,000155:    4170           02000                           TC       10000                         	#
001419,000156: 
001420,000157:    4171           56077        ISWRETRN           XCH      RUPTREG4                      	#
001421,000158:    4172           56004                           XCH      FBANK                         	#
001422,000159:    4173           56077                           XCH      RUPTREG4                      	#
001423,000160:    4174           00076                           TC       RUPTREG3                      	#
001424,000161: 
001426,000163:                                                                                          	# T6-RUPT PROGRAMS.
001427,000164: 
001428,000165:                                                                                          	# ENTER HERE AFTER A T6-RUPT.DETERMINE IF IT IS A GENUINE RUPT.
001429,000166: 
001430,000167:    4175           04177        DOT6RUPT           TC       T6JOBCHK                      	#
001431,000168:    4176           14606                           TCF      RESUME                        	#
001432,000169: 
001433,000170:                                                                                          	# T6JOBCHK DETERMINES IF T6 = -0 ( A T6RUPT HAS OCCURRED ) OR IF T6
001434,000171:                                                                                          	# EQUALS +0 ( T6 NOT COUNTING DOWN ) OR =SOME POS.OR NEG. NUMBER ( T6
001435,000172:                                                                                          	# BEING DECREMENTED AND NO RUPT IS NEEDED ).
001436,000173: 
001437,000174:    4177           10031        T6JOBCHK           CCS      TIME6                         	#
001438,000175:    4200           00002                           TC       Q                             	#
001439,000176:    4201           00002                           TC       Q                             	#
001440,000177:    4202           00002                           TC       Q                             	#
001441,000178:                                                                                          	# T6JOB EXECUTES A JET STATE CHANGE AND SETS UP ANY ADDITIONAL T6 RUPTS
001442,000179:                                                                                          	# WHICH MIGHT BE NECESSARY.
001443,000180: 
001444,000181:    4203           37665        T6JOB              CA       ZERO                          	#
001445,000182:    4204           56767                           XCH      T6NEXT     +1                 	#
001446,000183:    4205           56766                           XCH      T6NEXT                        	#
001447,000184:    4206           54031                           TS       TIME6                         	#
001448,000185:    4207           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
001449,000186:    4210           14230                           BZF      T6ZERO                        	#
001450,000187:    4211           37641                           CA       BIT15                         	#
001451,000188:    4212           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
001452,000189:    4213           05013                           WOR      13                            	#
001453,000190:    4214           37665                           CA       ZERO                          	#
001454,000191:    4215           56772                           XCH      T6NEXTJT   +2                 	#
001455,000192:    4216           56771                           XCH      T6NEXTJT   +1                 	#
001456,000193:    4217           56770                           XCH      T6NEXTJT                      	#
001457,000194:    4220           00006        WRITEJTS           EXTEND                                 	#
001458,000195:    4221           64225                           BZMF     WRITEQR                       	#
001459,000196:    4222           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
001460,000197:    4223           01006                           WRITE    6                             	#
001461,000198:    4224           00002                           TC       Q                             	#
001462,000199:    4225           00006        WRITEQR            EXTEND                                 	#
001463,000200:    4226           01005                           WRITE    5                             	#
001464,000201:    4227           00002                           TC       Q                             	#
001465,000202:    4230           30770        T6ZERO             CA       T6NEXTJT                      	#
001466,000203:    4231           14220                           TCF      WRITEJTS                      	#
001467,000204:    4232                        ENDIBNKF           EQUALS                                 	#
(End of include-file INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc, resuming main.agc)
001467,000028: 
001468,000029: $LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc		# 34
001470,000002:                                                                                          	# Copyright:    Public domain.
001471,000003:                                                                                          	# Filename:     LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc
001472,000004:                                                                                          	# Purpose:      Part of the source code for Aurora (revision 12).
001473,000005:                                                                                          	# Assembler:    yaYUL
001474,000006:                                                                                          	# Contact:      Hartmuth Gutsche <hgutsche@xplornet.com>.
001475,000007:                                                                                          	# Website:      https://www.ibiblio.org/apollo.
001476,000008:                                                                                          	# Pages:        34-122
001477,000009:                                                                                          	# Mod history:  2016-09-20 JL   Created.
001478,000010:                                                                                          	#               2016-09-22 HG   Start trancription from scans using Luminary099\INTERPRETER.agc as base
001479,000011:                                                                                          	#               2016-10-04 HG   Fix FBBANK -> FBANK
001480,000012: 
001481,000013:                                                                                          	# This source code has been transcribed or otherwise adapted from
001482,000014:                                                                                          	# digitized images of a hardcopy from the private collection of
001483,000015:                                                                                          	# Don Eyles.  The digitization was performed by archive.org.
001484,000016: 
001485,000017:                                                                                          	# Notations on the hardcopy document read, in part:
001486,000018: 
001487,000019:                                                                                          	#       473423A YUL SYSTEM FOR BLK2: REVISION 12 of PROGRAM AURORA BY DAP GROUP
001488,000020:                                                                                          	#       NOV 10, 1966
001489,000021: 
001490,000022:                                                                                          	#       [Note that this is the date the hardcopy was made, not the
001491,000023:                                                                                          	#       date of the program revision or the assembly.]
001492,000024: 
001493,000025:                                                                                          	# The scan images (with suitable reduction in storage size and consequent
001494,000026:                                                                                          	# reduction in image quality) are available online at
001495,000027:                                                                                          	#       https://www.ibiblio.org/apollo.
001496,000028:                                                                                          	# The original high-quality digital images are available at archive.org:
001497,000029:                                                                                          	#       https://archive.org/details/aurora00dapg
001498,000030: 
001499,000031: 
001501,000033:                                                                                          	# SECTION 1:  DISPATCHER
001502,000034: 
001503,000035:                                                                                          	#          ENTRY TO THE INTERPRETER. INTPRET SETS LOC TO THE FIRST INSTRUCTION, BANKSET TO THE FBANK OF THE
001504,000036:                                                                                          	# OBJECT INTERPRETIVE PROGRAM, AND INTBIT15 TO THE BIT15 CONTENTS OF FBANK. INTERPRETIVE PROGRAMS MAY BE IN
001505,000037:                                                                                          	# VIRTUALLY ALL BANKS PRESENT UNDER ANY SUPER-BANK SETTING, WITH THE RESTRICTION THAT PROGRAMS IN HIGH BANKS
001506,000038:                                                                                          	# (BIT15 OF FBANK = 1) DO NOT REFER TO LOWBANKS, AND VICE-VERSA. THE INTERPRETER DOES NOT SWITCH SUPER-BANK,
001507,000039:                                                                                          	# NOR DOES IT SWITCH EBANKS. MOST EBANK SWITCHING IS DONE BY THE EXECUTIVE PROGRAM.
001508,000040: 
001509,000041:    6000                                           SETLOC   6000                          	#
001510,000042: 
001511,000043:    6000           00006        INTPRET            EXTEND                                 	# SET LOC TO THE WORD FOLLOWING THE TC.
001512,000044:    6001           22150                           QXCH     LOC                           	#
001513,000045: 
001514,000046:    6002           30004                 +2        CA       FBANK                         	# INTERPRETIVE BRANCHES FINISH HERE.
001515,000047:    6003           54151                           TS       BANKSET                       	#
001516,000048:    6004           77641                           MASK     BIT15                         	# GET 15TH BIT FOR INDEXABLE ADDRESSES.
001517,000049:    6005           54101                           TS       INTBIT15                      	#
001518,000050:    6006           66426                           AD       LOW10                         	# THIS VERSION IS USED IN PROCESSING
001519,000051:    6007           54100                           TS       INTB15+                       	# INDEXABLE FIXED-BANK ADDRESSES.
001520,000052: 
001521,000053:    6010           16023                           TCF      NEWOPS                        	# PICK UP OP CODE PAIR AND BEGIN.
001522,000054: 
001523,000055:    6011           22006        INTRSM             LXCH     BBANK                         	# RESUME SUSPENDED INTERPRETIVE JOB
001524,000056:    6012           16003                           TCF      INTPRET    +3                 	# (ACTUALLY PART OF THE EXECUTIVE).
001525,000057: 
001527,000059:                                                                                          	#       AT THE END OF MOST INSTRUCTIONS, CONTROL IS GIVEN TO DANZIG TO DISPATCH THE NEXT OPERATION.
001528,000060:    6013           54147        NEWMODE            TS       MODE                          	# PROLOGUE FOR MODE-CHANGING INSTRUCTIONS.
001529,000061: 
001530,000062:    6014           30151        DANZIG             CA       BANKSET                       	# SET BBANK BEFORE TESTING NEWJOB SO THAT
001531,000063:    6015           54004                           TS       FBANK                         	# BBANK MAY BE SAVED DIRECTLY BY CHANJOB.
001532,000064: 
001533,000065:    6016           10023        NOIBNKSW           CCS      EDOP                          	# SEE IF AN ORDER CODE IS LEFT OVER FROM
001534,000066:    6017           16032                           TCF      OPJUMP                        	# THE LAST PAIR RETRIEVED. IF SO, EXECUTE.
001535,000067:                                                                                          	# EDOP IS SET TO ZERO ON ITS RE-EDITIING.
001536,000068: 
001537,000069:    6020           10067                           CCS      NEWJOB                        	# SEE IF A JOB OF HIGHER PRIORITY IS
001538,000070:    6021           14412                           TCF      CHANG2                        	# PRESENT, AND IF SO, CHANGE JOBS.
001539,000071: 
001540,000072:    6022           24150                           INCR     LOC                           	# ADVANCE THE LOCATION COUNTER.
001541,000073:    6023           50150        NEWOPS             INDEX    LOC                           	# ENTRY TO BEGIN BY PICKING OP CODE PAIR.
001542,000074:    6024           30000                           CA       0                             	# MAY BE AN OPCODE PAIR OR A STORE CODE.
001543,000075:    6025           10000                           CCS      A                             	# TEST SIGN AND GET DABS(A).
001544,000076:    6026           16342                           TCF      DOSTORE                       	# PROCESS STORE CODE.
001545,000077: 
001546,000078:    6027           00177        LOW7               OCT      177                           	#
001547,000079: 
001548,000080:    6030           54023                           TS       EDOP                          	# OP CODE PAIR.  LEAVE THE OTHER IN EDOP
001549,000081:    6031           76027                           MASK     LOW7                          	# WHERE CCS EDOP WILL HONOR IT NEXT.
001550,000082: 
001551,000083:    6032           54020        OPJUMP             TS       CYR                           	# LOWWD ENTERS HERE IF A RIGHT-HAND OP
001552,000084:    6033           10020                           CCS      CYR                           	# CODE IS TO BE PROCESSED. TEST PREFICES.
001553,000085:    6034           16167                           TCF      OPJUMP2                       	# TEST SECOND PREFIX BIT.
001554,000086: 
001555,000087:    6035           16731                           TCF      EXIT                          	# +0 OP CODE IS EXIT
001556,000088: 
001558,000090:                                                                                          	#       PROCESS ADDRESSES WHICH MAY BE DIRECT, INDEXED, OR REFERENCE THE PUSHDOWN LIST.
001559,000091: 
001560,000092:    6036           77657        ADDRESS            MASK     BIT1                          	# SEE IF ADDRESS IS INDEXED.  CYR CONTAINED
001561,000093:    6037           10000                           CCS      A                             	# 400XX, SO BIT 1 IS NOW AS IT WAS IN CYR.
001562,000094:    6040           16073                           TCF      INDEX                         	# FORM INDEXED ADDRESS.
001563,000095: 
001564,000096:    6041           50150        DIRADRES           INDEX    LOC                           	# LOOK AHEAD TO NEXT WORD TO SEE IF
001565,000097:    6042           40001        OCT40001           CS       1                             	# ADDRESS IS GIVEN.
001566,000098:    6043           10000                           CCS      A                             	#
001567,000099:    6044           16135                           TCF      PUSHUP                        	# IF NOT.
001568,000100: 
001569,000101:    6045           77773        NEG4               DEC      -4         B-14               	#
001570,000102: 
001571,000103:    6046           24150                           INCR     LOC                           	# IF SO, TO SHOW WE PICKED UP A WORD.
001572,000104:    6047           54102                           TS       ADDRWD                        	#
001573,000105: 
001575,000107:                                                                                          	#          FINAL DIGESTION OF DIRECT ADDRESSES OF OP CODES WITH 01 PREFIX IS DONE HERE. IN EACH CASE, THE
001576,000108:                                                                                          	# REQUIRED 12-BIT SUB-ADDRESS IS LEFT IN ADDRWD, WITH ANY REQUIRED BANK SWITCHING DONE (F ONLY). ADDRESSES LESS
001577,000109:                                                                                          	# THAN 45D ARE TAKEN TO BE RELATIVE TO THE WORK AREA. THE OP CODE IS NOW IN BITS 1-5 OF CYR WITH BIT 14 = 1.
001578,000110: 
001579,000111: 
001580,000112: 
001581,000113:    6050           66171                           AD       -ENDVAC                       	# SEE IF ADDRESS RELATIVE TO WORK AREA.
001582,000114:    6051           10000                           CCS      A                             	#
001583,000115:    6052           66234                           AD       -ENDERAS                      	# IF NOT, SEE IF IN GENERAL ERASABLE.
001584,000116:    6053           16060                           TCF      IERASTST                      	#
001585,000117: 
001586,000118:    6054           30104        NETZERO            CA       FIXLOC                        	# IF SO, LEAVE THE MODIFIED ADDRESS IN
001587,000119:    6055           26102                           ADS      ADDRWD                        	# ADDRWD AND DISPATCH.
001588,000120:    6056           50020                 +2        INDEX    CYR                           	# THIS INDEX MAKES THE NEXT INSTRUCTION
001589,000121:    6057           76234                           7        INDJUMP    -1                 	# TCF INDJUMP + OP, EDITING CYR.
001590,000122: 
001591,000123:    6060           00006        IERASTST           EXTEND                                 	#
001592,000124:    6061           66056                           BZMF     NETZERO    +2                 	# GENERAL ERASABLE - DISPATCH IMMEDIATELY
001593,000125: 
001594,000126:    6062           60100        FIXEDADR           AD       INTB15+                       	# FIXED BANK ADDRESS. RESTORE AND ADD B15.
001595,000127:    6063           54004                 +1        TS       FBANK                         	# SWITCH BANKS AND LEAVE SUB-ADDRESS IN
001596,000128:    6064           76426                           MASK     LOW10                         	# ADDRWD FOR OPERAND RETRIEVAL.
001597,000129:    6065           67645                           AD       2K                            	#
001598,000130:    6066           54102                           TS       ADDRWD                        	#
001599,000131:    6067           50020                           INDEX    CYR                           	#
001600,000132:    6070           76234                           7        INDJUMP    -1                 	#
001601,000133: 
001603,000135:                                                                                          	#          THE FOLLOWING ROUTINE PROCESSES INTERPRETIVE INDEXED ADDRESSES. AN INTERPRETER INDEX REGISTER MAY
001604,000136:                                                                                          	# CONTAIN THE ADDRESS OF ANY ERASABLE REGISTER (0-42 BEING RELATIVE TO THE VAC AREA) OR ANY INTERPRETIVE PROGRAM
001605,000137:                                                                                          	# BANK, OR ANY INTEGER IN THAT RANGE.
001606,000138: 
001607,000139:    6071           37676        DODLOAD*           CAF      DLOAD*                        	# STODL* COMES HERE TO PROCESS LOAD ADR.
001608,000140:    6072           54020                           TS       CYR                           	# (STOVL* ENTERS HERE).
001609,000141: 
001610,000142:    6073           30104        INDEX              CA       FIXLOC                        	# SET UP INDEX LOCATION.
001611,000143:    6074           54114                           TS       INDEXLOC                      	#
001612,000144:    6075           24150                           INCR     LOC                           	# (ADDRESS ALWAYS GIVEN).
001613,000145:    6076           50150                           INDEX    LOC                           	#
001614,000146:    6077           40000                           CS       0                             	#
001615,000147:    6100           10000                           CCS      A                             	# INDEX 2 IF ADDRESS STORED COMPLEMENTED.
001616,000148:    6101           24114                           INCR     INDEXLOC                      	#
001617,000149:    6102           16103                           NOOP                                   	#
001618,000150: 
001619,000151:    6103           54102                           TS       ADDRWD                        	# 14 BIT ADDRESS TO ADDRWD.
001620,000152:    6104           76232                           MASK     BANKMASK                      	# IF ADDRESS GREATER THAN 1K, ADD INTBIT15
001621,000153:    6105           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
001622,000154:    6106           16111                           BZF      INDEX2                        	#
001623,000155:    6107           30101                           CA       INTBIT15                      	#
001624,000156:    6110           26102                           ADS      ADDRWD                        	#
001625,000157: 
001626,000158:    6111           50114        INDEX2             INDEX    INDEXLOC                      	#
001627,000159:    6112           40046                           CS       X1                            	#
001628,000160:    6113           26102                           ADS      ADDRWD                        	# DO AUGMENT, IGNORING AND CORRECTING OVF.
001629,000161: 
001630,000162:    6114           76231                           MASK     HIGH9                         	# SEE IF ADDRESS IS IN WORK AREA.
001631,000163:    6115           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
001632,000164:    6116           16131                           BZF      INDWORK                       	#
001633,000165:    6117           76232                           MASK     BANKMASK                      	# SEE IF IN FIXED BANK.
001634,000166:    6120           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
001635,000167:    6121           16133                           BZF      INDERASE                      	#
001636,000168: 
001637,000169:    6122           30102                           CA       ADDRWD                        	# IN FIXED - SWITCH BANKS AND CREATE
001638,000170:    6123           54004                           TS       FBANK                         	# SUB-ADDRESS.
001639,000171:    6124           76426                           MASK     LOW10                         	#
001640,000172:    6125           67645                           AD       2K                            	#
001641,000173:    6126           54102                           TS       ADDRWD                        	#
001642,000174:    6127           50020                           INDEX    CYR                           	#
001643,000175:    6130           36234                           3        INDJUMP    -1                 	#
001644,000176: 
001645,000177:    6131           30104        INDWORK            CA       FIXLOC                        	# MAKE ADDRWD RELATIVE TO WORK AREA.
001646,000178:    6132           26102                           ADS      ADDRWD                        	#
001647,000179: 
001648,000180:    6133           50020        INDERASE           INDEX    CYR                           	#
001649,000181:    6134           36234                           3        INDJUMP    -1                 	#
001650,000182: 
001652,000184:                                                                                          	#          PUSH-UP ROUTINES. WHEN NO OPERAND ADDRESS IS GIVEN, THE APPROPRIATE OPERAND IS TAKEN FROM THE PUSH-DOWN
001653,000185:                                                                                          	# LIST. IN MOST CASES THE MODE OF THE RESULT (VECTOR OR SCALAR) OF THE LAST ARITHMETIC OPERATION PERFORMED
001654,000186:                                                                                          	# IS THE SAME AS THE TYPE OF OPERAND DESIRED (ALL ADD/SUBTRACT ETC.). EXCEPTIONS TO THIS GENERAL RULE ARE LISTED
001655,000187:                                                                                          	# BELOW (NOTE THAT IN EVERY CASE THE MODE REGISTER IS LEFT INTACT):
001656,000188: 
001657,000189:                                                                                          	#          1.  VXSC AND V/SC WANT THE OPPOSITE TYPE OF OPERAND, E.G., IF THE LAST OPERATION YIELDED A VECTOR
001658,000190:                                                                                          	# RESULT, VXSC WANTS A SCALAR.
001659,000191: 
001660,000192:                                                                                          	#          2.  THE LOAD CODES SHOULD LOAD THE ACCUMULATOR INDEPENDENT OF THE RESULT OF THE LAST OPERATION. THIS
001661,000193:                                                                                          	# INCLUDES VLOAD, DLOAD, TLOAD, PDDL, AND PDVL (NO PUSHUP WITH SLOAD).
001662,000194: 
001663,000195:                                                                                          	#          3.  SOME ARITHMETIC OPERATIONS REQUIRE A STANDARD TYPE OF OPERAND REGARDLESS OF THE PREVIOUS OPERATION.
001664,000196:                                                                                          	# THIS INCLUDES SIGN WANTING DP AND TAD REQUIRING TP.
001665,000197: 
001666,000198:    6135           36227        PUSHUP             CAF      OCT23                         	# IF THE LOW 5 BITS OF CYR ARE LESS THAN
001667,000199:    6136           70020                           MASK     CYR                           	# 20, THIS OP REQUIRES SPECIAL ATTENTION.
001668,000200:    6137           66142                           AD       -OCT10                        	# (NO -0).
001669,000201:    6140           10000                           CCS      A                             	#
001670,000202:    6141           16153                           TCF      REGUP                         	# FOR ALL CODES GREATEER THAN OCT 7.
001671,000203: 
001672,000204:    6142           77767        -OCT10             OCT      -10                           	#
001673,000205: 
001674,000206:    6143           66045                           AD       NEG4                          	# WE NOW HAVE 7 - OP CODE (MOD4). SEE IF
001675,000207:    6144           10000                           CCS      A                             	# THE OP CODE (MOD4) IS THREE (REVERSE).
001676,000208:    6145           50000                           INDEX    A                             	# NO - THE MODE IS DEFINITE.  PICK UP THE
001677,000209:    6146           46164                           CS       NO.WDS                        	#
001678,000210:    6147           16155                           TCF      REGUP      +2                 	#
001679,000211: 
001680,000212:    6150           50147                           INDEX    MODE                          	# FOR VXSC AND V/SC WE WANT THE REQUIRED
001681,000213:    6151           46162                           CS       REVCNT                        	# PUSHLOC DECREMENT WITHOUT CHANGING THE
001682,000214:    6152           16155                           TCF      REGUP      +2                 	# MODE AT THIS TIME.
001683,000215: 
001684,000216:    6153           50147        REGUP              INDEX    MODE                          	# MOST ALL OP CODES PUSHUP HERE.
001685,000217:    6154           46164                           CS       NO.WDS                        	#
001686,000218:    6155           26152                 +2        ADS      PUSHLOC                       	#
001687,000219:    6156           54102                           TS       ADDRWD                        	#
001688,000220:    6157           50020                           INDEX    CYR                           	#
001689,000221:    6160           76234                           7        INDJUMP    -1                 	# (THE INDEX MAKES THIS A TCF.)
001690,000222: 
001691,000223:    6161           00002                           OCT      2                             	# REVERSE PUSHUP DECREMENT. VECTOR TAKES 2
001692,000224:    6162           00006        REVCNT             OCT      6                             	# WORDS, SCALAR TAKES 6.
001693,000225:    6163           00006                           OCT      6                             	#
001694,000226:    6164           00002        NO.WDS             OCT      2                             	# CONVENTIONAL DECREMENT IS 6 WORDS VECTOR
