003283,001815: 00,2321           10147        LEFT               CCS      MODE                          	# SINCE LEFT SHIFTING IS SONE ONE PLACE AT
003284,001816: 00,2322           12325                           TCF      GENSCL                        	# A TIME, NO COMPARISON WITH 14 NEED BE
003285,001817: 00,2323           12325                           TCF      GENSCL                        	# DONE. FOR SCALARS, SEE IF TERMINAL ROUND
003286,001818: 00,2324           12126                           TCF      VSSL                          	# DESIRED. FOR VECTORS, SHIFT IMMEDIATELY.
003287,001819: 
003288,001820: 00,2325           37652        GENSCL             CAF      BIT6                          	# PUT ROUNDING BIT (BIT10 OF ADDRWD) INTO
003289,001821: 00,2326           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# BIT 15 OF CYR WHERE THE ROUNDING BIT OF
003290,001822: 00,2327           70102                           MP       ADDRWD                        	# A SHORT SHIFT LEFT WOULD BE.
003291,001823: 00,2330           54020                           TS       CYR                           	#
003292,001824: 00,2331           12064                           TCF      TSSL       +2                 	# DO THE SHIFT.
003293,001825: 
003295,001827:                                                                                          	#          SCALAR DIVISION INSTRUCTIONS, DDV AND BDDV, ARE EXECUTED HERE. AT THIS POINT, THE DIVIDEND IS IN MPAC
003296,001828:                                                                                          	# AND THE DIVISOR IS IN BUF.
003297,001829: 
003298,001830: 00,2332           47657        DDV/BDDV           CS       ONE                           	# INITIALIZATION
003299,001831: 00,2333           54122                           TS       DVSIGN                        	# +-1 FOR POSITIVE QUOTIENT - -0 FOR NEG.
003300,001832: 00,2334           54123                           TS       DVNORMCT                      	# DIVIDEND NORMALIZATION COUNT.
003301,001833: 00,2335           54124                           TS       MAXDVSW                       	# NEAR-ONE DIVIDE FLAG.
003302,001834: 
003303,001835: 00,2336           10114                           CCS      BUF                           	# FORCE BUF POSITIVE WITH THE MAJOR PART
003304,001836: 00,2337           12366                           TCF      BUF+                          	# NON-ZERO.
003305,001837: 00,2340           12342                           TCF      +2                            	#
003306,001838: 00,2341           12362                           TCF      BUF-                          	#
003307,001839: 
003308,001840: 00,2342           56115                           XCH      BUF        +1                 	# SHIFT DIVIDEND AND DIVISOR LEFT 14
003309,001841: 00,2343           56114                           XCH      BUF                           	#
003310,001842: 00,2344           56141                           XCH      MPAC       +1                 	#
003311,001843: 00,2345           56140                           XCH      MPAC                          	#
003312,001844: 00,2346           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# CHECK FOR OVERFLOW
003313,001845: 00,2347           12351                           BZF      +2                            	#
003314,001846: 00,2350           12355                           TCF      DVOVF                         	#
003315,001847: 
003316,001848: 00,2351           10114                           CCS      BUF                           	# TRY AGAIN ON FORMER MINOR PART.
003317,001849: 00,2352           12366                           TCF      BUF+                          	#
003318,001850: 00,2353           12355                           TCF      DVOVF                         	# OVERFLOW ON ZERO DIVISOR.
003319,001851: 00,2354           12362                           TCF      BUF-                          	#
003320,001852: 
003321,001853: 00,2355           37637        DVOVF              CAF      POSMAX                        	# ON DIVISION OVERFLOW OF ANY SORT, SET
003322,001854: 00,2356           54140                           TS       MPAC                          	# SET DP MPAC TO +-POSMAX.
003323,001855: 00,2357           02552                           TC       FINALDV    +3                 	#
003324,001856: 00,2360           37657                           CAF      ONE                           	# SET OVERFLOW INDICATOR AND EXIT.
003325,001857: 00,2361           17061                           TCF      SETOVF                        	#
003326,001858: 
003327,001859: 00,2362           00006        BUF-               EXTEND                                 	# IF BUF IS NEGATIVE, COMPLEMENT IT AND
003328,001860: 00,2363           40115                           DCS      BUF                           	# MAINTAIN DVSIGN FOR FINAL QUOTIENT SIGN.
003329,001861: 00,2364           52115                           DXCH     BUF                           	#
003330,001862: 00,2365           24122                           INCR     DVSIGN                        	# NOW -0.
003331,001863: 
003332,001864: 00,2366           10140        BUF+               CCS      MPAC                          	# FORCE MPAC POSITIVE, CHECKING FOR ZERO
003333,001865: 00,2367           12403                           TCF      MPAC+                         	# DIVIDEND IN THE PROCESS.
003334,001866: 00,2370           12372                           TCF      +2                            	#
003335,001867: 00,2371           12377                           TCF      MPAC-                         	#
003336,001868: 00,2372           10141                           CCS      MPAC       +1                 	#
003337,001869: 00,2373           12403                           TCF      MPAC+                         	#
003338,001870: 00,2374           16014                           TCF      DANZIG                        	# EXIT IMMEDIATELY ON ZERO DIVIDEND.
003339,001871: 00,2375           12377                           TCF      MPAC-                         	#
003340,001872: 00,2376           16014                           TCF      DANZIG                        	#
003341,001873: 
003342,001874: 00,2377           00006        MPAC-              EXTEND                                 	# FORCE MPAC POSITIVE AS BUF IN BUF-.
003343,001875: 00,2400           40141                           DCS      MPAC                          	#
003344,001876: 00,2401           52141                           DXCH     MPAC                          	#
003345,001877: 
003347,001879: 00,2402           24122                           INCR     DVSIGN                        	# NOW +1 OR -0.
003348,001880: 
003350,001882: 00,2403           40140        MPAC+              CS       MPAC                          	# CHECK FOR DIVISION OVERFLOW. IF THE
003351,001883: 00,2404           67667                           AD       NEGONE                        	# MAJOR PART OF THE DIVIDEND IS LESS THAN
003352,001884: 00,2405           60114                           AD       BUF                           	# THE MAJOR PART OF THE DIVISOR BY AT
003353,001885: 00,2406           10000                           CCS      A                             	# LEAST TWO, WE CAN PROCEED IMMEDIATELY
003354,001886: 00,2407           12451                           TCF      DVNORM                        	# WITHOUT NORMALIZATION PRODUCING A DVMAX.
003355,001887: 00,2410           60001        -1/2+2             OCT      60001                         	# USED IN SQRTSUB.
003356,001888: 
003357,001889: 00,2411           12412                           TCF      +1                            	# IF THE ABOVE DOES NOT HOLD, FORCE SIGN
003358,001890: 00,2412           37642                           CAF      HALF                          	# AGREEMENT IN NUMERATOR AND DENOMINATOR
003359,001891: 00,2413           60000                           DOUBLE                                 	# TO FACILITATE OVERFLOW AND NEAR-ONE
003360,001892: 00,2414           60141                           AD       MPAC       +1                 	# CHECKING.
003361,001893: 00,2415           54141                           TS       MPAC       +1                 	#
003362,001894: 00,2416           37665                           CAF      ZERO                          	#
003363,001895: 00,2417           67637                           AD       POSMAX                        	#
003364,001896: 00,2420           26140                           ADS      MPAC                          	#
003365,001897: 
003366,001898: 00,2421           37642                           CAF      HALF                          	# SAME FOR BUF.
003367,001899: 00,2422           60000                           DOUBLE                                 	#
003368,001900: 00,2423           60115                           AD       BUF        +1                 	#
003369,001901: 00,2424           54115                           TS       BUF        +1                 	#
003370,001902: 00,2425           37665                           CAF      ZERO                          	#
003371,001903: 00,2426           67637                           AD       POSMAX                        	#
003372,001904: 00,2427           26114                           ADS      BUF                           	#
003373,001905: 
003374,001906: 00,2430           40140                           CS       MPAC                          	# CHECK MAGNITUDE OF SIGN-CORRECTED
003375,001907: 00,2431           60114                           AD       BUF                           	# OPERANDS.
003376,001908: 00,2432           10000                           CCS      A                             	#
003377,001909: 00,2433           12451                           TCF      DVNORM                        	# DIVIDE OK - WILL NOT BECOME MAXOV CASE.
003378,001910: 00,2434           00117        LBUF2              ADRES    BUF2                          	#
003379,001911: 00,2435           12355                           TCF      DVOVF                         	# DIVISOR NOT LESS THAN DIVIDEND - OVF.
003380,001912: 
003381,001913: 00,2436           54124                           TS       MAXDVSW                       	# IF THE MAJOR PARTS OF THE DIVIDEND AND
003382,001914: 00,2437           40141                           CS       MPAC       +1                 	# DIVISOR ARE EQUAL, A SPECIAL APPROXIMA-
003383,001915: 00,2440           60115                           AD       BUF        +1                 	# TION IS USED (PROVIDED THE DIVISION IS
003384,001916: 00,2441           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# POSSIBLE, OF COURSE).
003385,001917: 00,2442           62355                           BZMF     DVOVF                         	#
003386,001918: 00,2443           12451                           TCF      DVNORM                        	# IF NO OVERFLOW.
003387,001919: 
003389,001921: 00,2444           00006        BUFNORM            EXTEND                                 	# ADD -1 TO AUGMENT SHIFT COUNT AND SHIFT
003390,001922: 00,2445           24123                           AUG      DVNORMCT                      	# LEFT ONE PLACE.
003391,001923: 00,2446           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
003392,001924: 00,2447           30115                           DCA      BUF                           	#
003393,001925: 00,2450           20115                           DAS      BUF                           	#
003394,001926: 
003395,001927: 00,2451           30114        DVNORM             CA       BUF                           	# SEE IF DIVISOR NORMALIZED YET.
003396,001928: 00,2452           60000                           DOUBLE                                 	#
003397,001929: 00,2453           54000                           OVSK                                   	#
003398,001930: 00,2454           12444                           TCF      BUFNORM                       	# NO - SHIFT LEFT ONE AND TRY AGAIN.
003399,001931: 
003400,001932: 00,2455           52141                           DXCH     MPAC                          	# CALL DIVIDEND NORMALIZATION SEQUENCE
003401,001933: 00,2456           50123                           INDEX    DVNORMCT                      	# PRIOR TO DOING THE DIVIDE.
003402,001934: 00,2457           02507                           TC       MAXTEST                       	#
003403,001935: 
003404,001936: 00,2460           54142                           TS       MPAC       +2                 	# RETURNS WITH DIVISION DONE AND C(A) = 0.
003405,001937: 00,2461           16014                           TCF      DANZIG                        	#
003406,001938: 
003408,001940:                                                                                          	#          THE FOLLOWING ARE PROLOGUES TO SHIFT THE DIVIDEND ARRIVING IN A AND L BEFORE THE DIVIDE.
003409,001941: 
003410,001942: 00,2462           22021                 -21D      LXCH     SR                            	# SPECIAL PROLOGUE FOR UNIT WHEN THE
003411,001943: 00,2463           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# LENGTH OF THE ARGUMENT WAS NOT LESS THAN
003412,001944: 00,2464           77642                           MP       HALF                          	# .5.  IN THIS CASE, EACH COMPONENT MUST BE
003413,001945: 00,2465           56001                           XCH      L                             	# SHIFTED RIGHT ONE TO PRODUCE A HALF-UNIT
003414,001946: 00,2466           60021                           AD       SR                            	# VECTOR.
003415,001947: 00,2467           56001                           XCH      L                             	#
003416,001948: 00,2470           12513                           TCF      GENDDV     +1                 	# WITH DP DIVIDEND IN A,L.
003417,001949: 
003418,001950: 00,2471           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	# PROLOGUE WHICH NORMALIZES THE DIVIDEND
003419,001951: 00,2472           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	# WHEN IT IS KNOWN THAT NO DIVISION
003420,001952: 00,2473           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	# OVEFLOW WILL OCCUR.
003421,001953: 00,2474           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	#
003422,001954: 00,2475           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	#
003423,001955: 00,2476           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	#
003424,001956: 00,2477           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	#
003425,001957: 00,2500           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	#
003426,001958: 00,2501           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	#
003427,001959: 00,2502           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	#
003428,001960: 00,2503           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	#
003429,001961: 00,2504           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	#
003430,001962: 00,2505           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	#
003431,001963: 00,2506           52141                           DXCH     MPAC                          	#
003432,001964: 
003433,001965: 00,2507           10124        MAXTEST            CCS      MAXDVSW                       	# 0 IF MAJORS MIGHT BE =, -1 OTHERWISE.
003434,001966: 00,2510           06552        BIASHI             DEC      .4192      B-1                	# SQRT CONSTANTS.
003435,001967: 
003436,001968: 00,2511           12564                           TCF      MAXDV                         	# CHECK TO SEE IF THAY ARE NOW EQUAL.
003437,001969: 
003439,001971:                                                                                          	#          THE FOLLOWING IS A GENERAL PURPOSE DOUBLE PRECISION DIVISION ROUTINE. IT DIVIDES MPAC BY BUF AND LEAVES
003440,001972:                                                                                          	# THE RESULT IN MPAC. THE FOLLOWING CONDITIONS MUST BE SATISFIED:
003441,001973: 
003442,001974:                                                                                          	#          1.  THE DIVISOR (BUF) MUST BE POSITIVE AND NOT LESS THAN .5.
003443,001975: 
003444,001976:                                                                                          	#          2.  THE DIVIDEND (MPAC) MUST BE POSITIVE WITH THE MAJOR PART OF MPAC STRICTLY LESS THAN THAT OF BUF
003445,001977:                                                                                          	# (A SPECIAL APPROXIMATION, MAXDV, IS USED WHEN THE MAJOR PARTS ARE EQUAL).
003446,001978: 
003447,001979:                                                                                          	#          UNDERSTANDING THAT A/B = Q + S(R/B) WHERE S = 2(-14) AND Q AND R ARE QUOTIENT AND REMAINDER, RESPEC-
003448,001980:                                                                                          	# TIVELY, THE FOLLOWING APPROXIMATION IS OBTAINED BY MULTIPLYING ABOVE AND BELOW BY C - SD AND NEGLECTING TERMS OF
003449,001981:                                                                                          	# ORDER S-SQUARED (POSSIBLY INTRODUCING ERROR INTO THE LOW TWO BITS OF THE RESULT). SIGN AGREEMENT IS UNNECESSARY.
003450,001982: 
003451,001983:                                                                                          	#          A + SB .      (R - QD)                                             A + SB
003452,001984:                                                                                          	#          ------ = Q + S(------) WHERE Q AND R ARE QUOTIENT AND REMAINDER OF ------ RESPECTIVELY.
003453,001985:                                                                                          	#          C + SD        (  C   }                                               C
003454,001986: 
003455,001987: 00,2512           52141        GENDDV             DXCH     MPAC                          	# WE NEED A AND B ONLY FOR FIRST DV.
003456,001988: 00,2513           00006                 +1        EXTEND                                 	# (SPECIAL UNIT PROLOGUE ENTERS HERE).
003457,001989: 00,2514           10114                           DV       BUF                           	# A NOW CONTAINS Q AND L, R.
003458,001990: 00,2515           52141                           DXCH     MPAC                          	#
003459,001991: 
003460,001992: 00,2516           40140                           CS       MPAC                          	# FORM DIVIDEND FOR MINOR PART OF RESULT.
003461,001993: 00,2517           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
003462,001994: 00,2520           70115                           MP       BUF        +1                 	#
003463,001995: 00,2521           60141                           AD       MPAC       +1                 	# OVERFLOW AT THIS POINT IS POSITIVE SINCE
003464,001996: 00,2522           54000                           OVSK                                   	# R IS POSITIVE IN EVERY CASE.
003465,001997: 00,2523           12530                           TCF      +5                            	#
003466,001998: 
003467,001999: 00,2524           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# OVERFLOW CAN BE REMOVED BY SUBTRACTING C
003468,002000: 00,2525           60114                           SU       BUF                           	# (BUF) ONCE SINCE R IS ALWAYS LESS THAN C
003469,002001: 00,2526           24140                           INCR     MPAC                          	# IN THIS CASE. INCR COMPENSATES SUBTRACT.
003470,002002: 00,2527           12532                           TCF      +DOWN                         	# (SINCE C(A) IS STILL POSITIVE).
003471,002003: 
003472,002004: 00,2530           00006                 +5        EXTEND                                 	# C(A) CAN BE MADE LESS THAN C IN MAGNI-
003473,002005: 00,2531           62542                           BZMF     -UP                           	# TUDE BY DIMINISHING IT BY C (SINCE C IS
003474,002006:                                                                                          	# NOT LESS THAN .5) UNLESS C(A) = 0.
003475,002007: 
003477,002009: 00,2532           00006        +DOWN              EXTEND                                 	#
003478,002010: 00,2533           60114                           SU       BUF                           	# IF POSITIVE, REDUCE ONLY IF NECESSARY
003479,002011: 00,2534           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# SINCE THE COMPENSATING INCR MIGHT CAUSE
003480,002012: 00,2535           12540                           BZF      +3                            	# OVERFLOW.
003481,002013: 00,2536           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# DONT SUBTRACT UNLESS RESULT IS POSITIVE
003482,002014: 00,2537           62546                           BZMF     ENDMAXDV                      	# OR ZERO.
003483,002015: 
003484,002016: 00,2540           24140                 +3        INCR     MPAC                          	# KEEP SUBTRACT HERE AND COMPENSATE.
003485,002017: 00,2541           12547                           TCF      FINALDV                       	#
003486,002018: 
003487,002019: 00,2542           00006        -UP                EXTEND                                 	# IF ZERO, SET MINOR PART OF RESULT TO
003488,002020: 00,2543           12552                           BZF      FINALDV    +3                 	# ZERO.
003489,002021: 
003490,002022: 00,2544           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# IF NEGATIVE, ADD C TO A, SUBTRACTING ONE
003491,002023: 00,2545           26140                           DIM      MPAC                          	# TO COMPENSATE. DIM IS OK HERE SINCE THE
003492,002024: 00,2546           60114        ENDMAXDV           AD       BUF                           	# MAJOR PART NEVER GOES NEGATIVE.
003493,002025: 
003495,002027: 00,2547           22007        FINALDV            ZL                                     	# DO DV TO OBTAIN MINOR PART OF RESULT.
003496,002028: 00,2550           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
003497,002029: 00,2551           10114                           DV       BUF                           	#
003498,002030: 00,2552           54141                 +3        TS       MPAC       +1                 	#
003499,002031: 
003500,002032: 00,2553           10122                           CCS      DVSIGN                        	# LEAVE RESULT POSITIVE UNLESS C(DVSIGN)=
003501,002033: 00,2554           00002                           TC       Q                             	# -0.
003502,002034: 00,2555           00002                           TC       Q                             	#
003503,002035: 00,2556           00002                           TC       Q                             	#
003504,002036: 
003505,002037: 00,2557           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
003506,002038: 00,2560           40141                           DCS      MPAC                          	#
003507,002039: 00,2561           52141                           DXCH     MPAC                          	#
003508,002040: 00,2562           37665                           CAF      ZERO                          	# SO WE ALWAYS RETURN WITH C(A) = 0.
003509,002041: 00,2563           00002                           TC       Q                             	#
003510,002042: 
003512,002044:                                                                                          	#          IF THE MAJOR PARTS OF THE DIVISOR AND DIVIDEND ARE EQUAL, BUT THE MINOR PARTS ARE SUCH THAT THE
003513,002045:                                                                                          	# DIVIDEND IS STRICTLY LESS THAN THE DIVISOR IN MAGNITUDE, THE FOLLOWING APPROXIMATION IS USED. THE ASSUMPTIONS
003514,002046:                                                                                          	# ARE THE SAME AS THE GENERAL ROUTINE WITH THE ADDITION THAT SIGN AGREEMENT IS NECESSARY (B, C, & D POSITIVE).
003515,002047: 
003516,002048:                                                                                          	#                 C + SB .          (C + B - D)
003517,002049:                                                                                          	#                 ------ = 37777 + S(---------)
003518,002050:                                                                                          	#                 C + SD            (    C    )
003519,002051: 
003520,002052:                                                                                          	#          THE DIVISION MAY BE PERFORMED IMMEDIATELY SINCE B IS STRICTLY LESS THAN D AND C IS NOT LESS THAN .5.
003521,002053: 
003522,002054: 
003523,002055:

004089,002621:                                                                                          	# TRIGONOMETRIC FUNCTION PACKAGE.
004090,002622: 
004091,002623:                                                                                          	#          THE FOLLOWING TRIGONOMETRIC FUNCTIONS ARE AVAIALABLE AS INTERPRETIVE OPERATIONS:
004092,002624: 
004093,002625:                                                                                          	#          1.      SIN            COMPUTES (1/2)SINE(2 PI MPAC).
004094,002626:                                                                                          	#          2.      COS            COMPUTES (1/2)COSINE(2 PI MPAC).
004095,002627: 
004096,002628:                                                                                          	#          3.      ASIN           COMPUTES (1/2PI)ARCSINE(2 MPAC).
004097,002629:                                                                                          	#          4.      ACOS           COMPUTES (1/2PI)ARCCOSINE(2 MPAC).
004098,002630: 
004099,002631:                                                                                          	# SIN-ASIN AND COS-ACOS ARE MUTUALLY INVERSE, I.E., SIN(ASIN(X)) = X.
004100,002632: 
004101,002633: 00,3445           06711        COSINE             TC       BRANCH                        	# FINDS COSINE USING THE IDENTITY
004102,002634: 00,3446           13451                           TCF      +3                            	# COS(X) = SIN(PI/2 - ABS(X)).
004103,002635: 00,3447           13454                           TCF      PRESINE                       	#
004104,002636: 00,3450           13454                           TCF      PRESINE                       	#
004105,002637:

004108,002640: 00,3453           52141                           DXCH     MPAC                          	#
004109,002641: 
004110,002642: 00,3454           37643        PRESINE            CAF      QUARTER                       	# PI/2 SCALED.
004111,002643: 00,3455           26140                           ADS      MPAC                          	#
004112,002644: 
004113,002645:

004116,002648: 00,3457           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	#
004117,002649: 00,3460           54000                           OVSK                                   	# SEE IF OVERFLOW PRESENT.
004118,002650: 00,3461           13464                           TCF      +3                            	# IF NOT, ARGUMENT OK AS IS.
004119,002651: 
004120,002652: 00,3462           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# IF SO, WE LOST (OR GAINED) PI, SO
004121,002653: 00,3463           40001                           DCOM                                   	# COMPLEMENT MPAC USING THE IDENTITY
004122,002654:                                                                                          	# SIN(X-(+)PI) = SIN(-X).

004480,003012: 01,2145           54114                           TS       SWWORD                        	#

004483,003015: 01,2147           50000                           INDEX    A                             	# LEAVE THE SWITCH WORD ITSELF IN L.
004484,003016: 01,2150           30061                           CA       STATE                         	#

004491,003023: 01,2154           70103                           MP       POLISH                        	# 7-8 OF POLISH.

004602,000060:    4264           20001                           DDOUBL                                 	#
004603,000061:    4265           55105                           TS       TEMK                          	#
004604,000062:    4266           00002                           TC       Q                             	#
004605,000063:    4267           50000        ARG90              INDEX    A                             	#
004606,000064:    4270           47640                           CS       LIMITS                        	#
004607,000065:    4271           00002                           TC       Q                             	# RESULT SCALED AT 1
004608,000066:    4272           31103        C1/2               DEC      .7853134                      	#
004609,000067:    4273           65552        C3/2               DEC      -.3216146                     	#
004610,000068:    4274           01124        C5/2               DEC      .0363551                      	#
004612,000070:                                                                                          	# ENTER WITH ARGUMENT IN A, EXIT WITH ROOT IN A.  IF GIVEN A NEGATIVE ARGUMENT, THE RETURN SKIPS WITH CCS RESULT
004613,000071:                                                                                          	# MINUS ZERO RETURNS LIKE PLUS ZERO.
004614,000072:                                                                                          	# MAXIMUM ERROR IN ANSWER IS NO GREATER THAN 2 BITS.
004615,000073:                                                                                          	# INTERRUPT PROGRAMS USING SPROOT MUST SAVE AND RESTORE SR.
004616,000074: 
004617,000075: 
004618,000076:

004619,000077:    4275           54000        SPROOT             TS       SQRARG                        	# ENTER WITH C(A) = Y
004620,000078:    4276           10000                           CCS      A                             	#
004621,000079:    4277           14303                           TCF      POSARG                        	# IF PNZ, CONTINUE
004622,000080:    4300           00002                           TC       Q                             	# RETURN WITH 0 FOR +0
004623,000081:    4301           24002                           INCR     Q                             	#
004624,000082:    4302           00002                           TC       Q                             	# RETURN WITH 0 FOR -0
004625,000083: 
004626,000084:    4303           00006        POSARG             EXTEND                                 	#
004627,000085:    4304           23106                           QXCH     ROOTRET                       	# WILL BE CALLING SPROOT1
004628,000086:    4305           64362                           AD       63/64+1                       	# B(A) = Y - 1
004629,000087:    4306           54000                           OVSK                                   	#
004630,000088:    4307           14351                           TCF      SPROOT2                       	#

005112,000429:    4450     1360                                  EBANK=   SELFRET                       	# SELF-CHECK STORAGE IN EBANK.
005113,000430: 
005114,000431:    4450           47665        DUMMYJOB           CS       ZERO                          	# SET NEWJOB TO -0 FOR IDLING.
005115,000432:    4451           54067                           TS       NEWJOB                        	#
005116,000433:    4452           00003                           RELINT                                 	#
005117,000434:    4453           47656                           CS       TWO                           	# TURN OFF THE ACTIVITY LIGHT.
005118,000435:    4454           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
EXECUTIVE.agc:436: Fatal Error: Symbol "DSALMOUT" undefined or offset bad
005119,000436:    4455           03000                           WAND     DSALMOUT                      	#
005120,000437:    4456           14461                           TCF      CHECKNJ    +2                 	#
005121,000438: 
005122,000439:    4457           00006        CHECKNJ            EXTEND                                 	# SPECIAL NEWJOB TEST FOR SELF-CHECK,
005123,000440:    4460           23360                           QXCH     SELFRET                       	# WHICH RUNS UNDER EXECUTIVE CONTROL,
005124,000441:    4461           10067                 +2        CCS      NEWJOB                        	# BUT DOES NOT HAVE A JOBS CORE REGISTERS.
005125,000442:    4462           14474                           TCF      NUCHANGE                      	# NEW JOB REQUIRING A CHANGE JOB.
005126,000443:    4463           37656                           CAF      TWO                           	# NEW JOB ALREADY IN POSITION FOR
005127,000444:    4464           14470                           TCF      NUDIRECT                      	# EXECUTION.
005128,000445: 
005129,000446:    4465           34503        ADVAN              CAF      SELFBANK                      	# (SIMULATOR ADVAN IF NEWJOB = 77777).
005130,000447:    4466           54006                           TS       BBANK                         	#
005131,000448:    4467           01360                           TC       SELFRET                       	#
005132,000449: 
005133,000450:    4470           00006        NUDIRECT           EXTEND                                 	# TURN THE GREEN LIGHT BACK ON.
EXECUTIVE.agc:451: Fatal Error: Symbol "DSALMOUT" undefined or offset bad
005134,000451:    4471           05000                           WOR      DSALMOUT                      	#

005196,000012:                                                                                          	# digitized images of a hardcopy from the private collection of

005200,000016:

005202,000018:                                                                                          	#       NOV 10, 1966

005205,000021:                                                                                          	#       date of the program revision or the assembly.]

005210,000026:                                                                                          	# The original high-quality digital images are available at archive.org:
005211,000027:                                                                                          	#       https://archive.org/details/aurora00dapg
005212,000028: 
005214,000030: 
005215,000031:                                                                                          	# GROUNDRULE....DELTA T SHOULD NOT EXCEED 12000 (= 2 MINUTES)
005216,000032: 
005217,000033:    4536                                           SETLOC   ENDEXECF                      	#
005218,000034: 
005219,000035:    4536  E3,1400                                  EBANK=   LST1                          	# TASK LISTS IN SWITCHED E BANK.
005220,000036: 
005221,000037:    4536           56002        WAITLIST           XCH      Q                             	# SAVE DELTA T IN Q AND RETURN IN
005222,000038:    4537           54065                           TS       WAITEXIT                      	# WAITEXIT.
005223,000039:    4540           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
005224,000040:    4541           50000                           INDEX    A                             	#
005225,000041:    4542           30001                           DCA      0                             	# PICK UP 2CADR OF TASK.
005226,000042:    4543           54070                           TS       WAITADR                       	# BBCON WILL REMAIN IN L.
005227,000043:    4544           34553        DLY2               CAF      WAITBB                        	# ENTRY FROM FIXDELAY AND VARDELAY.
005228,000044:    4545           56006                           XCH      BBANK                         	#
005229,000045:    4546           12566                           TCF      WAIT2                         	#
005230,000046: 
005231,000047:                                                                                          	# RETURN TO CALLER AFTER TASK INSERTION:
005232,000048: 
005233,000049:    4547           30066        LVWTLIST           CA       WAITBANK                      	#
005234,000050:    4550           54006                           TS       BBANK                         	#
005235,000051:    4551           50065                           INDEX    WAITEXIT                      	#
005236,000052:    4552           00002                           TC       2                             	#
005237,000053: 
005238,000054:    4553           02063        WAITBB             BBCON    WAIT2                         	#
005239,000055: 
005240,000056:                                                                                          	# RETURN TO CALLER +2 AFTER WAITING DT SPECIFIED AT CALLER +1.
005241,000057: 
005242,000058:    4554           50002        FIXDELAY           INDEX    Q                             	# BOTH ROUTINES MUST BE CALLED UNDER
005243,000059:    4555           30000                           CAF      0                             	# WAITLIST CONTROL AND TERMINATE THE TASK
005244,000060:    4556           24002                           INCR     Q                             	# IN WHICH THEY WERE CALLED.
005245,000061: 
005246,000062:                                                                                          	# RETURN TO CALLER +1 AFTER WAITING THE DT AS ARRIVING IN A.
005247,000063: 
005248,000064:    4557           56002        VARDELAY           XCH      Q                             	# DT TO Q.  TASK ADRES TO WAITADR.
005249,000065:    4560           54070                           TS       WAITADR                       	#
005250,000066:    4561           30006                           CA       BBANK                         	# BBANK IS SAVED DURING DELAY.
005251,000067:    4562           54001                           TS       L                             	#
005252,000068:    4563           34566                           CAF      DELAYEX                       	#
005253,000069:    4564           54065                           TS       WAITEXIT                      	# GO TO TASKOVER AFTER TASK ENTRY.
005254,000070:    4565           14544                           TCF      DLY2                          	#
005255,000071: 
005256,000072:    4566           14600        DELAYEX            TCF      TASKOVER   -2                 	# RETURNS TO TASKOVER
005257,000073: 
005259,000075: 
005260,000076:                                                                                          	# ENDTASK MUST ENTERED IN FIXED-FIXED SO IT IS DISTINGUISHABLE BY ITS ADRES ALONE.
005261,000077: 
005262,000078:    4567           73206 73714  ENDTASK            -2CADR   SVCT3                         	#
005263,000079: 
005264,000080:    4571           10063        SVCT3              CCS      STATE      +2                 	# DRIFT FLAG
005265,000081:    4572           14602                           TCF      TASKOVER                      	#
005266,000082:    4573           14602                           TCF      TASKOVER                      	#
005267,000083:    4574           14575                           TCF      +1                            	#
005268,000084: 
005269,000085:    4575           34533                           CAF      PRIO35                        	# COMPENSATE FOR NBD COEFFICIENTS ONLY.
005270,000086:    4576           04363                           TC       NOVAC                         	#     ENABLE EVERY 81.93 SECONDS
005271,000087:    4577           02257 16063                     2CADR    NBDONLY                       	# EBANK IS SET TO 3
005272,000088: 
005273,000089:    4601           14602                           TCF      TASKOVER                      	#
005274,000090: 
005276,000092: 
005277,000093:                                                                                          	# BEGIN TASK INSERTION.
005278,000094: 
005279,000095: 01,2566                                           SETLOC   ENDEXECS                      	#
005280,000096: 
005281,000097: 01,2566           54066        WAIT2              TS       WAITBANK                      	# BBANK OF CALLING PROGRAM.
005282,000098: 01,2567           40026                           CS       TIME3                         	#
005283,000099: 01,2570           62571                           AD       +1                            	# CCS  A  = + 1/4
005284,000100: 01,2571           10000                           CCS      A                             	# TEST  1/4 - C(TIME3).  IF POSITIVE,
005285,000101:                                                                                          	# IT MEANS THAT TIME3 OVERFLOW HAS OCCURED PRIOR TO CS  TIME3 AND THAT
005286,000102:                                                                                          	# C(TIME3) = T - T1, INSTEAD OF 1.0 - (T1 - T).  THE FOLLOWING FOUR
005287,000103:                                                                                          	# ORDERS SET C(A) = TD - T1 + 1 IN EITHER CASE.
005288,000104: 
005289,000105: 01,2572           66042                           AD       OCT40001                      	# OVERFLOW HAS OCCURRED.  SET C(A) =
005290,000106: 01,2573           40000                           CS       A                             	# T - T1 + 3/4 - 1
005291,000107: 
005292,000108:                                                                                          	# NORMAL CASE (C(A) MINUS) YIELDS SAME C(A)  -(-(1.0-(T1 - T))+1/4)-1
005293,000109: 
005294,000110: 01,2574           62722                           AD       OCT50001                      	#
005295,000111: 01,2575           60002                           AD       Q                             	# RESULT = TD - T1 + 1.
005296,000112: 
005297,000113: 01,2576           10000                           CCS      A                             	# TEST TD - T1 + 1
005298,000114: 
005299,000115: 01,2577           61400                           AD       LST1                          	# IF TD - T1 POS, GO TO WTLST5 WITH
005300,000116: 01,2600           12642                           TCF      WTLST5                        	# C(A) = (TD - T1) + C(LIST1) = TD-T2+1
005301,000117: 
005302,000118: 01,2601           12602                           NOOP                                   	#
005303,000119: 01,2602           40002                           CS       Q                             	#
005304,000120: 
005305,000121:                                                                                          	# NOTE THAT THIS PROGRAM SECTION IS NEVER ENTERED WHEN T-T1 G/E -1,
005306,000122:                                                                                          	# SINCE TD-T1+1 = (TD-T) + (T-T1+1), AND DELTA T = TD-T G/E +1 .  (G/E
005307,000123:                                                                                          	# SYMBOL MEANS GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO).  THUS THERE NEED BE NO CON-
005308,000124:                                                                                          	# CERN OVER A PREVIOUS OR IMMINENT OVEFLOW OF TIME3 HERE.
005309,000125: 
005310,000126: 01,2603           67642                           AD       POS1/2                        	# WHEN TD IS NEXT, FORM QUANTITY
005311,000127: 01,2604           67642                           AD       POS1/2                        	#   1.0 - DELTA T = 1.0 - (TD - T)
005312,000128: 01,2605           56026                           XCH      TIME3                         	#
005313,000129: 01,2606           67641                           AD       NEGMAX                        	#
005314,000130: 01,2607           60002                           AD       Q                             	# 1.0 - DELTAT T NOW COMPLETE.
005315,000131: 01,2610           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# ZERO INDEX Q.
005316,000132: 01,2611           22007                           QXCH     7                             	# (ZQ)
005317,000133: 
005319,000135: 
005320,000136: 01,2612           57400        WTLST4             XCH      LST1                          	#
005321,000137: 01,2613           57401                           XCH      LST1       +1                 	#
005322,000138: 01,2614           57402                           XCH      LST1       +2                 	#
005323,000139: 01,2615           57403                           XCH      LST1       +3                 	#
005324,000140: 01,2616           57404                           XCH      LST1       +4                 	#
005325,000141: 01,2617           57405                           XCH      LST1       +5                 	#
005326,000142: 01,2620           57406                           XCH      LST1       +6                 	#
005327,000143: 01,2621           57407                           XCH      LST1       +7                 	#
005328,000144: 
005329,000145: 01,2622           30070                           CA       WAITADR                       	# (MINOR PART OF TASK CADR HAS BEEN IN L.)
005330,000146: 01,2623           50002                           INDEX    Q                             	#
005331,000147: 01,2624           12625                           TCF      +1                            	#
005332,000148: 
005333,000149: 01,2625           53411                           DXCH     LST2                          	#
005334,000150: 01,2626           53413                           DXCH     LST2       +2                 	#
005335,000151: 01,2627           53415                           DXCH     LST2       +4                 	#
005336,000152: 01,2630           53417                           DXCH     LST2       +6                 	#
005337,000153: 01,2631           53421                           DXCH     LST2       +8D                	#
005338,000154: 01,2632           53423                           DXCH     LST2       +10D               	# AT END, CHECK THAT C(LST2 +10) IS STD
005339,000155: 01,2633           53425                           DXCH     LST2       +12D               	#
005340,000156: 01,2634           53427                           DXCH     LST2       +14D               	#
005341,000157: 01,2635           53431                           DXCH     LST2       +16D               	#
005342,000158: 01,2636           64567                           AD       ENDTASK                       	#   END ITEM, AS CHECK FOR EXCEEDING
005343,000159:                                                                                          	#   THE LENGTH OF THE LIST.
005344,000160: 01,2637           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# DUMMY TASK ADRES SHOULD BE IN FIXED-
005345,000161: 01,2640           14547                           BZF      LVWTLIST                      	# FIXED SO ITS ADRES ALONE DISTINGUISHES
005346,000162: 01,2641           12715                           TCF      WTABORT                       	# IT.
005347,000163: 
005348,000164:                                                                                          	# Page 143
005349,000165: 
005350,000166: 01,2642           10000        WTLST5             CCS      A                             	# TEST TD - T2 + 1
005351,000167: 01,2643           61401                           AD       LST1       +1                 	#
005352,000168: 01,2644           12650                           TCF      +4                            	#
005353,000169: 01,2645           67657                           AD       ONE                           	#
005354,000170: 01,2646           02723                           TC       WTLST2                        	#
005355,000171: 01,2647           00001                           OCT      1                             	#
005356,000172: 
005357,000173: 01,2650           10000                 +4        CCS      A                             	# TEST TD - T3 + 1
005358,000174: 01,2651           61402                           AD       LST1       +2                 	#
005359,000175: 01,2652           12656                           TCF      +4                            	#
005360,000176: 01,2653           67657                           AD       ONE                           	#
005361,000177: 01,2654           02723                           TC       WTLST2                        	#
005362,000178: 01,2655           00002                           OCT      2                             	#
005363,000179: 
005364,000180: 01,2656           10000                 +4        CCS      A                             	# TEST TD - T4 + 1
005365,000181: 01,2657           61403                           AD       LST1       +3                 	#
005366,000182: 01,2660           12664                           TCF      +4                            	#
005367,000183: 01,2661           67657                           AD       ONE                           	#
005368,000184: 01,2662           02723                           TC       WTLST2                        	#
005369,000185: 01,2663           00003                           OCT      3                             	#
005370,000186: 
005371,000187: 01,2664           10000                 +4        CCS      A                             	# TEST TD - T5 + 1
005372,000188: 01,2665           61404                           AD       LST1       +4                 	#
005373,000189: 01,2666           12672                           TCF      +4                            	#
005374,000190: 01,2667           67657                           AD       ONE                           	#
005375,000191: 01,2670           02723                           TC       WTLST2                        	#
005376,000192: 01,2671           00004                           OCT      4                             	#
005377,000193: 
005378,000194: 01,2672           10000                 +4        CCS      A                             	# TEST TD - T6 + 1
005379,000195: 01,2673           61405                           AD       LST1       +5                 	#
005380,000196: 01,2674           12700                           TCF      +4                            	#
005381,000197: 01,2675           67657                           AD       ONE                           	#
005382,000198: 01,2676           02723                           TC       WTLST2                        	#
005383,000199: 01,2677           00005                           OCT      5                             	#
005384,000200: 
005385,000201: 01,2700           10000                 +4        CCS      A                             	# TEST TD - T7 + 1
005386,000202: 01,2701           61406                           AD       LST1       +6                 	#
005387,000203: 01,2702           12706                           TCF      +4                            	#
005388,000204: 01,2703           67657                           AD       ONE                           	#
005389,000205: 01,2704           02723                           TC       WTLST2                        	#
005390,000206: 01,2705           00006                           OCT      6                             	#
005391,000207: 
005393,000209: 
005394,000210: 01,2706           10000                 +4        CCS      A                             	#
005395,000211: 01,2707           61407                           AD       LST1       +7                 	#
005396,000212: 01,2710           12714                           TCF      +4                            	#
005397,000213: 01,2711           67657                           AD       ONE                           	#
005398,000214: 01,2712           02723                           TC       WTLST2                        	#
005399,000215: 01,2713           00007                           OCT      7                             	#
005400,000216: 
005401,000217: 01,2714           10000                 +4        CCS      A                             	#
WAITLIST.agc:218: Fatal Error: Symbol "ABORT" undefined or offset bad
005402,000218: 01,2715           00000        WTABORT            TC       ABORT                         	# NO ROOM IN THE INN.
005403,000219: 01,2716           01203                           OCT      1203                          	#
005404,000220: 
005405,000221: 01,2717           67657                           AD       ONE                           	#
005406,000222: 01,2720           02723                           TC       WTLST2                        	#
005407,000223: 01,2721           00010                           OCT      10                            	#
005408,000224: 
005409,000225: 01,2722           50001        OCT50001           OCT      50001                         	#
005410,000226: 
005412,000228: 
005413,000229:                                                                                          	# THE ENTRY TC WTLST2 JUST PRECEDING OCT  N  IS FOR T  LE TD LE T   -1.
005414,000230:                                                                                          	#                                                    N           N+1
005415,000231: 
005416,000232:                                                                                          	# (LE MEANS LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO).  AT ENTRY, C(A) = -(TD - T   + 1)
005417,000233:                                                                                          	#                                                             N+1
005418,000234: 
005419,000235:                                                                                          	# THE LST1 ENTRY -(T   - T +1) IS TO BE REPLACED BY -(TD - T  + 1), AND
005420,000236:                                                                                          	#                   N+1   N                                 N
005421,000237: 
005422,000238:                                                                                          	# THE ENTRY -(T   - TD + 1) IS TO BE INSERTED IMMEDIATELY FOLLOWING.
005423,000239:                                                                                          	#              N+1
005424,000240: 
005425,000241: 01,2723           54071        WTLST2             TS       WAITTEMP                      	#     C(A) = -(TD - T   + 1)
005426,000242: 01,2724           50002                           INDEX    Q                             	#
005427,000243: 01,2725           30000                           CAF      0                             	#
005428,000244: 01,2726           54002                           TS       Q                             	# INDEX VALUE INTO Q.
005429,000245: 
005430,000246: 01,2727           37657                           CAF      ONE                           	#
005431,000247: 01,2730           60071                           AD       WAITTEMP                      	#
005432,000248: 01,2731           50002                           INDEX    Q                             	# C(A) = -(TD - T ) + 1.
005433,000249: 01,2732           27377                           ADS      LST1       -1                 	#                N
005434,000250: 
005435,000251: 01,2733           40071                           CS       WAITTEMP                      	#
005436,000252: 01,2734           50002                           INDEX    Q                             	#
005437,000253: 01,2735           12612                           TCF      WTLST4                        	#
005438,000254: 
005439,000255:                                                                                          	# C(TIME3)  = 1.0 - (T1 - T)
005440,000256: 
005441,000257:                                                                                          	# C(LST1  ) = - (T2 - T1) + 1
005442,000258:                                                                                          	# C(LST1+1) = - (T3 - T2) + 1
005443,000259:                                                                                          	# C(LST1+2) = - (T4 - T3) + 1
005444,000260:                                                                                          	# C(LST1+3) = - (T5 - T4) + 1
005445,000261:                                                                                          	# C(LST1+4) = - (T6 - T5) + 1
005446,000262: 
005447,000263:                                                                                          	# C(LST2   ) = 2CADR  TASK1
005448,000264:                                                                                          	# C(LST2+2 ) = 2CADR  TASK2
005449,000265:                                                                                          	# C(LST2+4 ) = 2CADR  TASK3
005450,000266:                                                                                          	# C(LST2+6 ) = 2CADR  TASK4
005451,000267:                                                                                          	# C(LST2+8 ) = 2CADR  TASK5
005452,000268:                                                                                          	# C(LST2+10) = 2CADR  TASK6
005453,000269: 
005455,000271: 
005456,000272:                                                                                          	# ENTERS HERE ON T3 RUPT TO DISPATCH WAITLISTED TASK.
005457,000273: 
005458,000274: 01,2736           54016        T3RUPT             TS       BANKRUPT                      	#
005459,000275: 01,2737           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
005460,000276: 01,2740           22012                           QXCH     QRUPT                         	#
005461,000277: 
005462,000278: 01,2741           37640        T3RUPT2            CAF      NEG1/2                        	# DISPATCH WAITLIST TASK.
005463,000279: 01,2742           57407                           XCH      LST1       +7                 	#
005464,000280: 01,2743           57406                           XCH      LST1       +6                 	#
005465,000281: 01,2744           57405                           XCH      LST1       +5                 	#
005466,000282: 01,2745           57404                           XCH      LST1       +4                 	# 1.  MOVE UP LST1 CONTENTS, ENTERING
005467,000283: 01,2746           57403                           XCH      LST1       +3                 	#     A VALUE OF 1/2 +1 AT THE BOTTOM
005468,000284: 01,2747           57402                           XCH      LST1       +2                 	#     FOR T6-T5, CORRESPONDING TO THE
005469,000285: 01,2750           57401                           XCH      LST1       +1                 	#     INTERVAL 81.91 SEC FOR ENDTASK.
005470,000286: 01,2751           57400                           XCH      LST1                          	#
005471,000287: 01,2752           67637                           AD       POSMAX                        	# 2. SET T3 = 1.0 - T2 -T USING LIST 1.
005472,000288: 01,2753           26026                           ADS      TIME3                         	# SO T3 WONT TICK DURING UPDATE.
005473,000289: 01,2754           55070                           TS       RUPTAGN                       	#
005474,000290: 01,2755           47665                           CS       ZERO                          	#
005475,000291: 01,2756           55070                           TS       RUPTAGN                       	# SETS RUPTAGN TO +1 ON OVERFLOW.
005476,000292: 
005477,000293: 01,2757           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# DISPATCH TASK.
005478,000294: 01,2760           44570                           DCS      ENDTASK                       	#
005479,000295: 01,2761           53431                           DXCH     LST2       +16D               	#
005480,000296: 01,2762           53427                           DXCH     LST2       +14D               	#
005481,000297: 01,2763           53425                           DXCH     LST2       +12D               	#
005482,000298: 01,2764           53423                           DXCH     LST2       +10D               	#
005483,000299: 01,2765           53421                           DXCH     LST2       +8D                	#
005484,000300: 01,2766           53417                           DXCH     LST2       +6                 	#
005485,000301: 01,2767           53415                           DXCH     LST2       +4                 	#
005486,000302: 01,2770           53413                           DXCH     LST2       +2                 	#
005487,000303: 01,2771           53411                           DXCH     LST2                          	#
005488,000304: 
005489,000305: 01,2772           52006                           DTCB                                   	#
005490,000306: 
005491,000307: 01,2773                        ENDWAITS           EQUALS                                 	#
005492,000308: 
005494,000310: 
005495,000311:                                                                                          	# RETURN, AFTER EXECUTION OF T3 OVERFLOW TASK:
005496,000312: 
005497,000313:    4602                                           BLOCK    02                            	#
005498,000314: 
005499,000315:    4602           11070        TASKOVER           CCS      RUPTAGN                       	# IF +1 RETURN TO T3RUPT, IF -0 RESUME.
005500,000316:    4603           34553                           CAF      WAITBB                        	#
005501,000317:    4604           54006                           TS       BBANK                         	#
005502,000318:    4605           12741                           TCF      T3RUPT2                       	# DISPATCH NEXT TASK IF IT WAS DUE.
005503,000319: 
005504,000320:    4606           00006        RESUME             EXTEND                                 	#
005505,000321:    4607           22012                           QXCH     QRUPT                         	#
005506,000322:    4610           30016        NOQRSM             CA       BANKRUPT                      	#
005507,000323:    4611           54006                           TS       BBANK                         	#
005508,000324:    4612           52011        NOQBRSM            DXCH     ARUPT                         	#
005509,000325:    4613           50017                           RESUME                                 	#
005510,000326: 
005511,000327:    4614                        ENDWAITF           EQUALS                                 	# LAST FIXED-FIXED LOCATION OF T3RUPT.
(End of include-file WAITLIST.agc, resuming main.agc)

005512,000033: $PHASE_TABLE_MAINTENANCE.agc			# 148
005514,000002:                                                                                          	# Copyright:    Public domain.
005515,000003:                                                                                          	# Filename:     PHASE_TABLE_MAINTENANCE.agc
005516,000004:                                                                                          	# Purpose:      Part of the source code for Aurora (revision 12).
005517,000005:                                                                                          	# Assembler:    yaYUL
005518,000006:                                                                                          	# Contact:      Ron Burkey <info@sandroid.org>.
005519,000007:                                                                                          	# Website:      https://www.ibiblio.org/apollo.
005520,000008:                                                                                          	# Pages:        148-150
005521,000009:                                                                                          	# Mod history:  2016-09-20 JL   Created.
005522,000010:                                                                                          	#               2016-10-03 JL   Transcribed pages 148-150.
005523,000011: 
005524,000012:                                                                                          	# This source code has been transcribed or otherwise adapted from
005525,000013:                                                                                          	# digitized images of a hardcopy from the private collection of
005526,000014:                                                                                          	# Don Eyles.  The digitization was performed by archive.org.
005527,000015: 
005528,000016:                                                                                          	# Notations on the hardcopy document read, in part:
005529,000017: 
005530,000018:                                                                                          	#       473423A YUL SYSTEM FOR BLK2: REVISION 12 of PROGRAM AURORA BY DAP GROUP
005531,000019:                                                                                          	#       NOV 10, 1966
005532,000020: 
005533,000021:                                                                                          	#       [Note that this is the date the hardcopy was made, not the
005534,000022:                                                                                          	#       date of the program revision or the assembly.]
005535,000023: 
005536,000024:                                                                                          	# The scan images (with suitable reduction in storage size and consequent
005537,000025:                                                                                          	# reduction in image quality) are available online at
005538,000026:                                                                                          	#       https://www.ibiblio.org/apollo.
005539,000027:                                                                                          	# The original high-quality digital images are available at archive.org:
005540,000028:                                                                                          	#       https://archive.org/details/aurora00dapg
005541,000029: 
005543,000031:                                                                                          	#       THE FOLLOWING ROUTINES ARE PROVIDED TO MAINTAIN THE PHASE TABLE. TWO ROUTINES ARE AVILABLE:
005544,000032: 
005545,000033:                                                                                          	#               TC      PHASCHNG        SLOWER BUT LESS STORAGE.
005546,000034:                                                                                          	#               OCT     PPPGG           CHANGE RESTART GROUP GG TO PHASE PPP
005547,000035:                                                                                          	#                                       (PPP IS A SIGNED 8 BIT NUMBER).
005548,000036: 
005549,000037:                                                                                          	#               CA      PPPPP           NEW PHASE ARRIVES IN A.
005550,000038:                                                                                          	#               TC      NEWPHASE
005551,000039:                                                                                          	#               OCT     000GG           UPDATES GG.
005552,000040: 
005553,000041:                                                                                          	#       IN ALL CASES THE OLD PHASE RETURNS IN A. IF THE OLD PHASE WAS NEGATIVE, CALL A ROUTINE USING THE
005554,000042:                                                                                          	# CORRESPONDING TERMCADR.
005555,000043: 
005556,000044:    4614                                           SETLOC   ENDWAITF                      	#
005557,000045: 
005558,000046:    4614           00004        PHASCHNG           INHINT                                 	#
005559,000047:    4615           50002                           INDEX    Q                             	#
005560,000048:    4616           30000                           CAF      0                             	# GET PARAMETER WORD.
005561,000049:    4617           54077                           TS       RUPTREG4                      	#
PHASE_TABLE_MAINTENANCE.agc:50: Fatal Error: Symbol "LOW5" undefined or offset bad
005562,000050:    4620           70000                           MASK     LOW5                          	# GROUP NUMBER 0 - 37.
005563,000051:    4621           60000                           DOUBLE                                 	#
005564,000052:    4622           56077                           XCH      RUPTREG4                      	#
005565,000053:    4623           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
005566,000054:    4624           77647                           MP       BIT9                          	# SIGNED NEW PHASE.
005567,000055:    4625           14634                           TCF      PHASCH2                       	#
005568,000056: 
005569,000057:    4626           00004        NEWPHASE           INHINT                                 	# NEW PHASE ARRIVES IN A.
005570,000058:    4627           54077                           TS       RUPTREG4                      	#
005571,000059:    4630           50002                           INDEX    Q                             	#
005572,000060:    4631           30000                           CAF      0                             	# GROUP NUMBER.
005573,000061:    4632           60000                           DOUBLE                                 	#
005574,000062:    4633           56077                           XCH      RUPTREG4                      	#
005575,000063: 
PHASE_TABLE_MAINTENANCE.agc:64: Fatal Error: Symbol "LXCH" undefined or offset bad
005576,000064:    4634           54000        PHASCH2            TS       LXCH                          	# DIRECT VERSION.
005577,000065:    4635           40000                           COM                                    	# COMPLEMENTED VERSION IMMEDIATELY PRE-
005578,000066:    4636           50077                           INDEX    RUPTREG4                      	# CEDES THE DIRECT ONE.
005579,000067:    4637           53072                           DXCH     -PHASE0                       	# COPIES DISAGREE FOR MINIMUM TIME.
005580,000068:    4640           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
005581,000069:    4641           64655                           BZMF     PHASEXIT                      	# IF NO DERAIL.
005582,000070: 
005584,000072:    4642           54074                           TS       RUPTREG1                      	# IF NEGATIVE, SAVE ABSOLUTE VALUE OF
005585,000073:    4643           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# OLD PHASE AND RETURN Q.
005586,000074:    4644           22075                           QXCH     RUPTREG2                      	#
005587,000075:    4645           30077                           CA       RUPTREG4                      	# GET BACK GROUP NUMBER.
005588,000076:    4646           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#

005595,000083:    4654           22002                           LXCH     Q                             	#
005596,000084: 
005597,000085:    4655           40000        PHASEXIT           COM                                    	# RETURN OLD PHASE IN A.
005598,000086:    4656           00003                           RELINT                                 	#
005599,000087:    4657           50002                           INDEX    Q                             	#
005600,000088:    4660           00001                           TC       1                             	#
005601,000089:

005602,000090:    4661           00000        TERMCADR           CADR     10000                         	# FILLED IN AS NEEDED.

005603,000091:    4662           00000                           CADR     10000                         	#

005604,000092:    4663           00000                           CADR     10000                         	#

005611,000099:

005617,000105:    4674           60276                           AD       MODREG                        	#
005618,000106:    4675           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
005619,000107:    4676           14712                           BZF      TCQ                           	#

005621,000109:    4677           34701                           CAF      +2                            	# CALL PINBALL SUBROUTINE.

006863,000821: 12,3544           20002        OCT20002           OCT      20002                         	#
006864,000822:                                                                                          	# Page 181
006865,000823:                                                                                          	# PROGRAM NAME: GPMATRIX          MOD. NO. 0  DATE: OCTOBER 20, 1966
006866,000824: 
006867,000825:                                                                                          	# AUTHOR: JONATHAN D. ADDELSTON (ADAMS ASSOCIATES)
006868,000826: 
006869,000827:                                                                                          	# THIS PROGRAM CALCULATES ALL THE SINGLE-PRECISION MATRIX ELEMENTS WHICH ARE USED BY LEM DAP TO TRANSFORM VECTORS
006870,000828:                                                                                          	# FROM GIMBAL TO PILOT (BODY) AXES AND BACK AGAIN.  THESE ELEMENTS ARE USED EXCLUSIVELY BY BASIC LANGUAGE ROUTINES
006871,000829:                                                                                          	# AND THEREFORE ARE NOT ARRAYED FOR USE BY INTERPRETIVE PROGRAMS.
006872,000830: 
006873,000831:                                                                                          	# CALLING SEQUENCE: GPMATRIX IS ALWAYS EXECUTED 4 TIMES A SECOND BY T4RUPT PROGRAM.  IT IS LISTED EXPLICITLY TWICE
006874,000832:                                                                                          	# IN THE T4JUMP TABLE, BUT IT ALSO OCCURS AFTER RRAUTCHK (TWICE).
006875,000833: 
006876,000834:                                                                                          	# SUBROUTINES CALLED: SPSIN, SPCOS.
006877,000835: 
006878,000836:                                                                                          	# NORMAL EXIT MODE: CONTROL IS ALWAYS TRANSFERRED TO DBSELECT.
006879,000837: 
006880,000838:                                                                                          	# ALARM/ABORT MODE: THERE ARE NO REAL ALARMS OR ABORTS.  HOWEVER, WHEN THE MIDDLE GIMBAL ANGLE NEARS GIMBAL LOCK,
006881,000839:                                                                                          	# A DIVISION BY COS(MG) WILL CAUSE OVERFLOW (I.E. A BAD QUOTIENT).  THIS CONDITION IS PREVENTED BY TESTING COS(MG)
006882,000840:                                                                                          	# AND SUBSTITUTING POSMAX/NEGMAX FOR THE INCALCULABLE QUANTITIES.
006883,000841: 
006884,000842:                                                                                          	# INPUT: CDUX,CDUY,CDUZ.          OUTPUT: M11,M21,M31,M22,M32,MR12,MR13.
006885,000843:                                                                                          	#                                         (ALSO MR22=M22,MR23=M32)        AM DOES NOT DETECT IT.
006886,000844: 
006887,000845:                                                                                          	# *** WARNING ** IT DIES ON DV OVERFLOW.
006888,000846: 
006889,000847:                                                                                          	# AOG = CDUX, AIG = CDUY, AMG = CDUZ: MNEMONIC IS: OIM = XYZ
006890,000848: 
006891,000849:                                                                                          	#    *       *    SIN(MG)        0         1  *
006892,000850:                                                                                          	#    M   =   *    COS(MG)COS(OG) SIN(OG)   0  *
006893,000851:                                                                                          	#     GP     *   -COS(MG)SIN(OG) COS(OG)   0  *
006894,000852: 
006895,000853:                                                                                          	#    *       *  0    COS(OG)/COS(MG)        -SIN(OG)/COS(MG)         *
006896,000854:                                                                                          	#    M   =   *  0    SIN(OG)                 COS(OG)                 *
006897,000855:                                                                                          	#     PG     *  1   -SIN(MG)COS(OG)/COS(MG)  SIN(MG)SIN(OG)/COS(MG)  *
006898,000856: 
006899,000857: 12,3545           30034        GPMATRIX           CAE      CDUZ                          	# SINGLE ENTRY POINT
006900,000858: 12,3546           04233                           TC       SPSIN                         	# SIN(CDUZ) = SIN(MG)
006901,000859: 12,3547           55404                           TS       M11                           	# SCALED AT 1
006902,000860: 
006903,000861: 12,3550           30034                           CAE      CDUZ                          	#
006904,000862: 12,3551           04232                           TC       SPCOS                         	# COS(CDUZ) = COS(MG)
006905,000863: 12,3552           55466                           TS       COSMG                         	# SCALED AT 1 (ONLY A FACTOR)
006906,000864: 
006907,000865: 12,3553           30032                           CAE      CDUX                          	#
006908,000866: 12,3554           04233                           TC       SPSIN                         	# SIN(CDUX) = SIN(OG)
006909,000867: 12,3555           55401                           TS       M22                           	# SCALED AT 1 (ALSO IS MR22)
006910,000868: 
006911,000869: 12,3556           41401                           CS       M22                           	#
006912,000870: 12,3557           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
006913,000871: 12,3560           71466                           MP       COSMG                         	# -SIN(OG)COS(MG)
006914,000872: 12,3561           55406                           TS       M31                           	# SCALED AT 1
006915,000873:                                                                                          	# Page 182
006916,000874: 12,3562           30032                           CAE      CDUX                          	#
