006922,000880: 12,3567           55405                           TS       M21                           	# SCALED AT 1
006923,000881: 
T4RUPT_PROGRAM.agc:882: Fatal Error: Symbol "COSMSG" undefined or offset bad
006924,000882: 12,3570           30000                           CAE      COSMSG                        	# TEST FOR GIMBAL LOCK (OVERFLOW) REGION

006951,000909: 12,3617           13621                           TCF      +2                            	#
006952,000910: 12,3620           37641                           CAF      NEGMAX                        	#
006953,000911: 12,3621           55402        MR13STOR           TS       MR13                          	# SCALED AT 2
006955,000913:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING SECTION TESTS THE ATTITUDE HOLD BIT TO DETERMINE WHICH DEA
006957,000915:                                                                                          	# PROGRAM NAME: DB SELECT         MOD. NO. 1  DATE: OCTOBER 24, 1966
006958,000916: 
006959,000917:                                                                                          	# AUTHOR: JONATHAN D. ADDELSTON (ADAMS ASSOCIATES)
006960,000918: 
006961,000919:                                                                                          	# THIS PROGRAM SETS THE ERASABLE REGISTER DB TO ONE OF THE THREE VALUES:
006962,000920:                                                                                          	#          1) O.3 DEGREES IF IN ATTITUDE HOLD MODE OR IF IN AUTO WITH THE DEADBAND SELECT BIT OF DAPBOOLS SET
006963,000921:                                                                                          	#             TO MINIMUM.
006964,000922:                                                                                          	#          2) 5.0 DEGREES IF IN AUTO WITH DEADBAND SELECT BIT SET TO MAXIMUM.
006965,000923:                                                                                          	#          3) 1.0 DEGREES IF IN POWERED FLIGHT (ASCENT OR DESCENT) AND OVERRIDING ANY SETTING OF SCSMODE OR THE
006966,000924:                                                                                          	#             DEADBAND SELECT BIT.  (*** SEE COMMENT AFTER CODING. ***)
006967,000925: 
006968,000926:                                                                                          	# ***** NOTICE *****
006969,000927: 
006970,000928:                                                                                          	# THE ABOVE CAPABILTY FULFILLS ALL THE KNOWN DEADBAND REQUIREMENTS FOR AS206, AS208B, AND AS278 (GIVEN THE
006971,000929:                                                                                          	# APPROPRIATE MISSION PROGRAMS).
006972,000930: 
006973,000931:                                                                                          	# (ALSO FOR MANNED FLIGHTS A DSKY ENTRY MUST BE SET UP TO SET THE DEADBAND BITS OF DAPBOOLS. - NOT DONE AS
006974,000932:                                                                                          	# OF 10/24/66.)
006975,000933: 
006976,000934:                                                                                          	# ***** DEADBAND SELECT BIT IS BIT13 OF DAPBOOLS. *****
006977,000935:                                                                                          	#          0: MEANS MINIMUM DEADBAND
006978,000936:                                                                                          	#          1: MEANS MAXIMUM DEADBAND
006979,000937: 
006980,000938:                                                                                          	# CALLING SEQUENCE: CONTROL FALLS THROUGH FROM GPMATRIX. (4 TIMES/SECOND)
006981,000939: 
006982,000940:                                                                                          	# SUBROUTINES CALLED: NONE.
006983,000941: 
006984,000942:                                                                                          	# NORMAL EXIT MODE: CONTROL IS ALWAYS TRANSFERRED TO UP/DOWN.
006985,000943: 
006986,000944:                                                                                          	# ALARM/ABORT MODE: NONE.
006987,000945: 
006988,000946:                                                                                          	# INPUT: BIT13/CHNL11,BIT13/CHNL31,BIT13/DAPBOOLS.  (SPOOKY, ISN'T IT?)
006989,000947: 
006990,000948:                                                                                          	# OUTPUT: DB (SCALED AT PI RADIANS).     (NO DEBRIS EXCEPT A)
006991,000949: 
006992,000950: 12,3622           37643        DBSELECT           CAF      BIT13                         	# ATTITUDE HOLD BIT OF CHANNEL 31
006993,000951: 12,3623           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# 0 MEANS ATTITUDE HOLD
006994,000952: 12,3624           02031                           RAND     31                            	# 1 MEANS EITHER OFF OR AUTO
006995,000953: 12,3625           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
006996,000954: 12,3626           13635                           BZF      ATTHLDDB                      	# (ATTITUDE HOLD BRANCH)
006997,000955: 
006998,000956: 12,3627           40765                           CS       DAPBOOLS                      	# DEADBAND SELECT BIT OF DAPBOOLS
006999,000957: 12,3630           77643                           MASK     BIT13                         	# 0 MEANS MINIMUM DEADBAND
007000,000958: 12,3631           10000                           CCS      A                             	# 1 MEANS MAXIMUM DEADBAND
007001,000959: 12,3632           13635                           TCF      ATTHLDDB                      	# (MINIMUM DEADBAND BRANCH)
007002,000960: 
007003,000961: 12,3633           33747                           CAF      DBMAXUM                       	# SET MAXIMUM DEADBAND
007004,000962: 12,3634           13636                           TCF      +2                            	#
007005,000963: 
007006,000964: 12,3635           33751        ATTHLDDB           CAF      DBATTHLD                      	# SET MINUMUM (ATTITUDE HOLD) DEADBAND
007008,000966: 12,3636           55415                           TS       DB                            	#
007009,000967: 
007010,000968:                                                                                          	# ***** IMPORTANT NOTICE *****
007011,000969: 
007012,000970:                                                                                          	# FOR EFFICIENCY, THE OVERRIDING 1 DEGREE DEADBAND DURING POWERED FLIGHT IS NOT TESTED FOR ABOVE. THE PROGRAM
007013,000971:                                                                                          	# FOLLOWING (I.E. UP/DOWN) PERFORMS THIS FUNCTION AFTER THE APPROPRIATE TESTS. THEREFORE, DB MAY TRANSIENTLY BE
007014,000972:                                                                                          	# INVALID, BUT THE DAP CANNOT USE IT THEN DUE TO T4RUPT MODE.
007015,000973:                                                                                          	# Page 186
007016,000974:                                                                                          	# PROGRAM NAME: UP/DOWN           MOD. NO. 1  DATE: OCTOBER 25, 1966
007017,000975: 
007018,000976:                                                                                          	# AUTHOR: JONATHAN D. ADDELSTON (ADAMS ASSOCIATES)
007019,000977: 
007020,000978:                                                                                          	# THIS PROGRAM MONITORS THE STAGE OF THE LEM AND THE ENGINE ON BIT IN ORDER TO DETERMINE WHEN ASCENT, DESCENT, AND
007021,000979:                                                                                          	# COAST PHASES MUST BE SET UP FOR THE DAP. (DONE 4 TIMES A SECOND.)
007022,000980: 
007023,000981:                                                                                          	# CALLING SEQUENCE: NONE.         SUBROUTINES CALLED: WAITLIST.
007024,000982: 
007025,000983:                                                                                          	# NORMAL EXIT MODE: CONTROL IS ALWAYS TRANSFERRED TO ENDDAPT4.
007026,000984: 
007027,000985:                                                                                          	# ALARM/ABORT MODE: NONE.
007028,000986: 
007029,000987:                                                                                          	# INPUT:BIT2/CHNL30,BIT13/CHNL11,BIT8/DAPBOOLS.
007030,000988: 
007031,000989:                                                                                          	# OUTPUT:  A) ASCENT COAST:
007032,000990:                                                                                          	#                 1) BIT8/DAPBOOLS SET TO ZERO, MEANING COAST.
007033,000991:                                                                                          	#                 2) MINIMPDB AND DBMINIMP SET TO 0.3 DEGREES.
007034,000992:                                                                                          	#          B) ASCENT BURN:
007035,000993:                                                                                          	#                 1) INITIALIZATION PASS:
007036,000994:                                                                                          	#                        I) BIT8/DAPBOOLS SET FROM 0 TO 1, MEANING THAT THE AOSTASK HAS BEEN STARTED UP AND THAT
007037,000995:                                                                                          	#                           INITIALIZATION HAS OCCURRED.
007038,000996:                                                                                          	#                       II) MINIMPDB SET TO -DB.
007039,000997:                                                                                          	#                      III) DBMINIMP SET TO ZERO.
007040,000998:                                                                                          	#                       IV) SUMRATEQ AND SUMRATER ZEROED FOR FIRST TWO SECOND AOSTASK SAMPLE PERIOD.
007041,000999:                                                                                          	#                        V) KCOEFCTR ZEROED TO RECORD INITIAL TIME.
007042,001000:                                                                                          	#                       VI) OMEGAQ AND OMEGAR RECORDED IN OLDWFORQ AND OLDWFORR AS LAST OMEGA VECTOR FOR AOSTASK.
007043,001001:                                                                                          	#                      VII) AOSTASK SET IN WAITLIST FOR TWO SECONDS.
007044,001002:                                                                                          	#                     VIII) DB SET TO DBAUTO.
007045,001003:                                                                                          	#                       IX) ****** CHECKOUT ONLY **** IXXTASK, IYYTASK, AND IZZTASK SET IN WAITLIST FOR TEN MS.
007046,001004:                                                                                          	#                 2) NORMAL PASS VOID.
007047,001005:                                                                                          	#          C) DESCENT COAST:
007048,001006:                                                                                          	#                 1) BIT2/DAPBOOLS SET TO 1, MEANING THAT TRIM GIMBAL CONTROL OF DESCENT IS IMPOSSIBLE SINCE
007049,001007:                                                                                          	#                    DESCENT ENGINE OFF.
007050,001008:                                                                                          	#                 2) AOSQTERM AND AOSRTERM ZEROED.
007051,001009:                                                                                          	#          D) DESCENT BURN:
007052,001010:                                                                                          	#                 1) DB SET TO DBAUTO.
007053,001011:                                                                                          	#                 2) BIT2/DAPBOOLS CANNOT NOW BE ZEROED (EVEN THOUGH THE DESCENT ENGINE IS ON), SINCE IT IS NOT
007054,001012:                                                                                          	#                    NECESSARILY TRUE THAT THIS IMPLIES AN OPERATIVE TRIM GIMBAL SYSTEM.
007055,001013: 
007056,001014: 12,3637           37656        UP/DOWN            CAF      BIT2                          	# STAGE VERIFY BIT OF CHANNEL 30: INVERTED
007057,001015: 12,3640           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# 0 MEANS ASCENT STAGE
007058,001016: 12,3641           02030                           RAND     30                            	# 1 MEANS DESCENT STAGE
007059,001017: 12,3642           10000                           CCS      A                             	#
007060,001018: 12,3643           13725                           TCF      DESCLEM                       	# (DESCENT STAGE BRANCH)
007061,001019: 
007062,001020: 12,3644           37643        ASCLEM             CAF      BIT13                         	# ENGINE ON BIT OF CHANNEL 11
007063,001021: 12,3645           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# 0 MEANS OFF
007064,001022: 12,3646           02011                           RAND     11                            	# 1 MEANS ON
007065,001023: 12,3647           10000                           CCS      A                             	#
007067,001025: 12,3650           13660                           TCF      ASCDAP                        	# (ASCENT BURN BRANCH)
007068,001026: 
007069,001027: 12,3651           47650        ASCCOAST           CS       BIT8                          	# SET BIT8 OF DAPBOOLS TO COAST DAP LOGIC
007070,001028: 12,3652           70765                           MASK     DAPBOOLS                      	# LEM IS STAGED FOR ASCENT, BUT THE ASCENT
007071,001029: 12,3653           54765                           TS       DAPBOOLS                      	# ENGINE IS NOT ON.
007072,001030: 
007073,001031: 12,3654           33751                           CAF      DBATTHLD                      	# FOR ASCENT COAST SET BOTH MINIMUM PULSE
007074,001032: 12,3655           55647                           TS       MINIMPDB                      	# DEADBANDS TO THE DESCENT PHASE VALUE OF
007075,001033: 12,3656           55646                           TS       DBMINIMP                      	# 0.3 DEGREES SCALED AT PI RADIANS.
007076,001034: 
007077,001035: 12,3657           14606                           TCF      ENDDAPT4                      	# (END OF UP/DOWN)
007078,001036: 
007079,001037: 12,3660           37650        ASCDAP             CAF      BIT8                          	# CHECK AOSTASK BIT OF DAPBOOLS
007080,001038: 12,3661           70765                           MASK     DAPBOOLS                      	# IF 0, SET BIT AND INITIATE WAITLIST TASK
007081,001039: 12,3662           10000                           CCS      A                             	# IF 1, THEN TASK LOOP ALREADY BEGUN
007082,001040: 12,3663           14606                           TCF      ENDDAPT4                      	# (END OF UP/DOWN)
007083,001041: 
007084,001042: 12,3664           33750                           CAF      DBAUTO                        	# SINCE ASCENT ENGINE IS ON -
007085,001043: 12,3665           55415                           TS       DB                            	# SET DEADBAND TO 1.0 DEGREES
007086,001044: 
007087,001045: 12,3666           37650                           CAF      BIT8                          	# SET BIT TO INDICATE AOSTASK SET UP AND
007088,001046: 12,3667           26765                           ADS      DAPBOOLS                      	# ASCENT LOGIC.  BIT CLEARLY NOT SET YET.
007089,001047: 
007090,001048: 12,3670           41415                           CS       DB                            	# MODIFY THE TJETLAW FOR ASCENT:
007091,001049: 12,3671           55647                           TS       MINIMPDB                      	# (IN ONE EQUATION DELETE MINIMPDB AND
007092,001050: 12,3672           37665                           CAF      ZERO                          	# SHIFT THE SWITCHING CURVE TO THE ORIGIN)
007093,001051: 12,3673           55646                           TS       DBMINIMP                      	# MINIMPDB = -DB, DBMINIMP = 0
007094,001052: 
007095,001053: 12,3674           37665                           CAF      ZERO                          	# INITIALIZE THE SUM RATES
007096,001054: 12,3675           55640                           TS       SUMRATEQ                      	#
007097,001055: 12,3676           55641                           TS       SUMRATER                      	#
007098,001056: 12,3677           55671                           TS       KCOEFCTR                      	# INITIALIZE TIME COUNTER
007099,001057: 12,3700           31417                           CAE      OMEGAQ                        	# CREATE OLD OMEGAQ
007100,001058: 12,3701           55644                           TS       OLDWFORQ                      	#
007101,001059: 12,3702           31421                           CAE      OMEGAR                        	# CREATE OLD OMEGAR
007102,001060: 12,3703           55645                           TS       OLDWFORR                      	#
007103,001061: 
007104,001062:                                                                                          	# ***** EVENTUALLY, USE 2SECWLT4 FROMM FIXED-FIXED AND NEW NAME. *****
007105,001063: 
007106,001064: 12,3704           33746                           CAF      2SECWLT4                      	# SET UP AOSTASK TO BEGIN IN 2 SECONDS
007107,001065: 12,3705           04536                           TC       WAITLIST                      	# IT THEN SETS UP A LOOP ON WAITLIST FOR
007108,001066: 12,3706           03064 52066                     2CADR    AOSTASK                       	# 2 SECOND INTERVALS AND CHECKS FOR THE
007109,001067:                                                                                          	# SHUTDOWN CONDITION IN BIT8 OF DAPBOOLS
007110,001068: 
007111,001069:                                                                                          	# ******************************************************************************
007112,001070: 
007113,001071:                                                                                          	# REMOVE THIS AND THE TASKS WHEN THE INERTIA ESTIMATOR WORKS.
007114,001072: 
007115,001073: 12,3710           37657                           CAF      ONE                           	# *** SPECIAL DAP CHECKOUT SEQUENCE ***
007116,001074: 12,3711           04536                           TC       WAITLIST                      	# THESE THREE CALLS TO WAITLIST BEGIN A
007118,001076: 12,3712           03525 52066                     2CADR    IXXTASK                       	# COMPLICATED PROCEDURE TO DECREMENT THE
007119,001077: 12,3714           37657                           CAF      ONE                           	# INERTIA MATRIX DIAGONAL ELEMENTS (EACH
007120,001078: 12,3715           04536                           TC       WAITLIST                      	# SCALED AT 2(+18) SLUG FEET(2) ) BY ONE
007121,001079: 12,3716           03536 52066                     2CADR    IYYTASK                       	# BIT AS SOON AS APPROPRIATE BY A NOMINAL
007122,001080: 12,3720           37657                           CAF      ONE                           	# LINEAR APPROXIMATION TO INERTIAL CHANGE.
007123,001081: 12,3721           04536                           TC       WAITLIST                      	#
007124,001082: 12,3722           03547 52066                     2CADR    IZZTASK                       	# *** NOT TO BE USED IN MISSIONS ***
007125,001083:                                                                                          	# ******************************************************************************
007126,001084: 
007127,001085: 12,3724           14606                           TCF      ENDDAPT4                      	# (END OF UP/DOWN)
007128,001086: 
007129,001087: 12,3725           37643        DESCLEM            CAF      BIT13                         	# ENGINE ON BIT OF CHANNEL 11
007130,001088: 12,3726           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# 0 MEANS OFF
007131,001089: 12,3727           02011                           RAND     11                            	# 1 MEANS ON
007132,001090: 12,3730           10000                           CCS      A                             	#
007133,001091: 12,3731           13742                           TCF      DESCDAP                       	# (DESCENT BURN BRANCH)
007134,001092: 
007135,001093: 12,3732           47656        DESCOAST           CS       BIT2                          	# SET BIT2 OF DAPBOOLS TO INDICATE THAT
007136,001094: 12,3733           70765                           MASK     DAPBOOLS                      	# TRIM GIMBAL CANNOT BE USED SINCE THE
007137,001095: 12,3734           67656                           AD       BIT2                          	# STAGE IS DESCENT, BUT THE ENGINE IS NOT
007138,001096: 12,3735           54765                           TS       DAPBOOLS                      	# ON.
007139,001097: 
007140,001098: 12,3736           37665                           CAF      ZERO                          	# ZERO TRIM GIMBAL OFFSET ACCELERATION
007141,001099: 12,3737           55642                           TS       AOSQTERM                      	# TERMS IN THE DESCENT RATE DERIVATION
007142,001100: 12,3740           55643                           TS       AOSRTERM                      	# SINCE THE THRUST IS ZERO (ENGINE OFF).
007143,001101: 
007144,001102: 12,3741           14606                           TCF      ENDDAPT4                      	# (END OF UP/DOWN)
007145,001103: 
007146,001104: 12,3742           33750        DESCDAP            CAF      DBAUTO                        	# SINCE DESCENT ENGINE IS ON -
007147,001105: 12,3743           55415                           TS       DB                            	# SET DEADBAND TO 1.0 DEGREES
007148,001106: 
007149,001107: 12,3744           14606                           TCF      ENDDAPT4                      	# (END OF UP/DOWN)
007150,001108: 
007151,001109: 12,3745           14606                           TCF      ENDDAPT4                      	#
007152,001110: 
007153,001111: 
007154,001112: 12,3746           00310        2SECWLT4           DEC      200        B-14               	# 2 SECONDS WAITLIST DT
007155,001113: 12,3747           00707        DBMAXUM            DEC      0.02778                       	# 5.0 DEGREES SCALED AT PI RADIANS
007156,001114: 12,3750           00133        DBAUTO             DEC      0.00555                       	# 1.0 DEGREES SCALED AT PI RADIANS
007157,001115: 12,3751           00033        DBATTHLD           DEC      0.00167                       	# 0.3 DEGREES SCALED AT PI RADIANS
007158,001116: 
007159,001117: 
007160,001118: 
007161,001119: 12,3752  12,3545               NORRGMON           EQUALS   GPMATRIX                      	#
007162,001120: 12,3752     4606               ENDDAPT4           EQUALS   RESUME                        	#
(End of include-file T4RUPT_PROGRAM.agc, resuming main.agc)

007201,000038:    4757           54033                           TS       CDUY                          	#
007202,000039:    4760           54034                           TS       CDUZ                          	#
007203,000040:    4761           00002                           TC       Q                             	#

007206,000043: 
007207,000044:    4763                        ENDIMODF           EQUALS                                 	#
007208,000045: 
007210,000047:                                                                                          	# IMU ZEROING ROUTINE.
007211,000048: 
007212,000049: 13,2000                                           BANK     13                            	#
007213,000050: 
007214,000051: 13,2000           00004        IMUZERO            INHINT                                 	# ROUTINE TO ZERO ICDUS.
007215,000052: 13,2001           47650                           CS       IMUSEFLG                      	# SET INDICATION THAT A MISSION OR TEST
007216,000053: 13,2002           70061                           MASK     STATE                         	# PROGRAM IS USING THE IMU.
007217,000054: 13,2003           67650                           AD       IMUSEFLG                      	#
007218,000055: 13,2004           54061                           TS       STATE                         	#
007219,000056: 
007220,000057: 13,2005           02650                           TC       CAGETSTQ                      	# IF IMU COMING UP, TURN-ON PROGRAM WILL
007221,000058: 13,2006           12033                           TCF      MODEEXIT                      	# DO ALL THE WORK.
007222,000059: 
007223,000060: 13,2007           42743                           CS       BITS3&4                       	# INHIBIT ICDUFAIL AND IMUFAIL (IN CASE WE
007224,000061: 13,2010           70367                           MASK     IMODES30                      	# JUST CAME OUT OF COARSE ALIGN).
007225,000062: 13,2011           62743                           AD       BITS3&4                       	#
007226,000063: 13,2012           54367                           TS       IMODES30                      	#
007227,000064: 
007228,000065: 13,2013           42744                           CS       BITS4&6                       	# SEND ZERO ENCODE WITH COARSE AND ERROR
007229,000066: 13,2014           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# COUNTER DISABLED.
007230,000067: 13,2015           03012                           WAND     12                            	#
007231,000068: 
007232,000069: 13,2016           37653                           CAF      BIT5                          	#
007233,000070: 13,2017           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
007234,000071: 13,2020           05012                           WOR      12                            	#
007235,000072: 
007236,000073: 13,2021           37652                           CAF      BIT6                          	# WAIT 320 MS TO GIVE AGS ADEQUATE TIME TO
007237,000074: 13,2022           04536                           TC       WAITLIST                      	# RECEIVE ITS PULSE TRAIN.
007238,000075: 13,2023           02035 26063                     2CADR    IMUZERO2                      	#
007239,000076: 
007240,000077: 13,2025           40367                           CS       IMODES30                      	# SEE IF IMU OPERATING AND ALARM IF NOT.
007241,000078: 13,2026           77647                           MASK     BIT9                          	#
007242,000079: 13,2027           10000                           CCS      A                             	#
007243,000080: 13,2030           12033                           TCF      MODEEXIT                      	#
007244,000081: 
IMU_MODE_SWITCHING_ROUTINES.agc:82: Fatal Error: Symbol "ALARM" undefined or offset bad

007247,000084:

007249,000086: 13,2034           14076                           TCF      SWRETURN                      	#
007250,000087: 
007252,000089: 13,2035           02650        IMUZERO2           TC       CAGETSTQ                      	# POSSIBLY SWITCH TO TURN-ON PROGRAM.

007851,000688:

007889,000003:                                                                                          	# Filename:     IMU_COMPENSATION_PACKAGE.agc
007890,000004:                                                                                          	# Purpose:      Part of the source code for Aurora (revision 12).
007891,000005:                                                                                          	# Assembler:    yaYUL
007892,000006:                                                                                          	# Contact:      Hartmuth Gutsche<hgutsche@xplornet.com>.
007893,000007:                                                                                          	# Website:      https://www.ibiblio.org/apollo.
007894,000008:                                                                                          	# Pages:        209-217
007895,000009:                                                                                          	# Mod history:  2016-09-20 JL   Created.
007896,000010:                                                                                          	#               2016-09-21 HG   Initial transcription from scans
007897,000011: 
007898,000012:                                                                                          	# This source code has been transcribed or otherwise adapted from
007899,000013:                                                                                          	# digitized images of a hardcopy from the private collection of 
007900,000014:                                                                                          	# Don Eyles.  The digitization was performed by archive.org.
007901,000015: 
007902,000016:                                                                                          	# Notations on the hardcopy document read, in part:
007903,000017: 
007904,000018:                                                                                          	#       473423A YUL SYSTEM FOR BLK2: REVISION 12 of PROGRAM AURORA BY DAP GROUP
007905,000019:                                                                                          	#       NOV 10, 1966
007906,000020: 
007907,000021:                                                                                          	#       [Note that this is the date the hardcopy was made, not the
007908,000022:                                                                                          	#       date of the program revision or the assembly.]
007909,000023: 
007910,000024:                                                                                          	# The scan images (with suitable reduction in storage size and consequent 
007911,000025:                                                                                          	# reduction in image quality) are available online at 
007912,000026:                                                                                          	#       https://www.ibiblio.org/apollo.  
007913,000027:                                                                                          	# The original high-quality digital images are available at archive.org:
007914,000028:                                                                                          	#       https://archive.org/details/aurora00dapg
007915,000029: 
007916,000030:                                                                                          	##Page 209
007917,000031: 07,2000                                           BANK     7                             	#
007918,000032: 07,2000  E3,1440                                  EBANK=   NBDX                          	#
007919,000033:                                                                                          	# PROGRAM DESCRIPTION- IMU COMPENSATION (LEM)                             DATE- 30 AUG 66
007920,000034:                                                                                          	# MOD NO- 0                                                               LOG SECTION- IMU COMPENSATION PACKAGE
007921,000035:                                                                                          	# MOD BY- GILBERT                                                         ASSEMBLY- SUNBURST REVISION 13 
007922,000036: 
007923,000037:                                                                                          	# FUNCTIONAL DESCRIPTION
007924,000038:                                                                                          	#       THE IMU COMPENSATION PACKAGE IS DESIGNED TO COMPENSATE FOR PIPA BIAS AND SCALE FACTOR ERROR AND AT THE
007925,000039:                                                                                          	# SAME TIME ACCUMULATE GYRO TORQUING COMMANDS NECESSARY TO COMPENSATE FOR THE ASSOCIATED BIAS AND ACCELERATION-
007926,000040:                                                                                          	# CAUSED GYRO DRIFTS. 1/PIPA MUST BE CALLED AT LEAST EVERY 2.55 SECONDS DUE TO SCALING CONSIDERATIONS.
007927,000041:                                                                                          	# SPECIFICALLY, THE CORRECTION IS
007928,000042: 
007929,000043:                                                                                          	#       PIPA  = (1 + SCALE FACTOR ERROR)PIPA  -  (BIAS)(DELTAT)
007930,000044:                                                                                          	#           C                               I
007931,000045: 
007932,000046:                                                                                          	# WHERE PIPA  IS THE COMPENSATED DATA OBTAINED FROM THE SAMPLED DATA PIPA
007933,000047:                                                                                          	#           C                                                            I
007934,000048: 
007935,000049:                                                                                          	# THE COMPENSATED DATA IS THEN USED TO COMPUTE THE IRIG TORQUING NECESSARY TO CANCEL THE NBD, ADIA, AND ADSRA
007936,000050:                                                                                          	# GYRO COEFFICIENTS.
007937,000051:                                                                                          	# SPECIFICALLY, THE COMPUTATIONS ARE
007938,000052: 
007939,000053:                                                                                          	#       XIRIG     -(ADIAX)(PIPAX ) + (ADSRAX)(PIPAY ) - (NBDX)(DELTAT)  
007940,000054:                                                                                          	#                               C                  C
007941,000055:                                                                                          	#       YIRIG     -(ADIAY)(PIPAY ) + (ADSRAY)(PIPAZ ) - (NBDY)(DELTAT)
007942,000056:                                                                                          	#                               C                  C  
007943,000057:                                                                                          	#       ZIRIG     -(ADIAZ)(PIPAZ ) - (ADSRAZ)(PIPAY ) + (NBDZ)(DELTAT)
007944,000058:                                                                                          	#                               C                  C
007945,000059: 
007946,000060:                                                                                          	# THIS COMPENSATION IS SUMMED INTO THE GCOMP REGISTERS AND WHEN THE MAGNITUDE OF ANY IRIG COMMAND EXCEEDS 2
007947,000061:                                                                                          	# PULSES, THE COMMANDS ARE SENT TO THE GYROS.
007948,000062: 
007949,000063:                                                                                          	# DURING FREE-FALL PHASES OF A FLIGHT NBDX, NBDY, AND NBDZ ARE THE ONLY RELEVANT COEFFICIENTS. THESE BIAS TERMS
007950,000064:                                                                                          	# WILL BE INTEGRATED BY BY ROUTINE NBDONLY APPROXIMATELY EVERY 81.93 SECONDS FOLLOWING AN EXECUTIVE CALL BY THE DUMMY
007951,000065:                                                                                          	# TASK OF THE WAITLIST PROGRAM. NBDONLY IS ENABLED WHEN BIT 15 OF FLAGWRD2 IS SET TO INDICATE FREE-FALL. DURING
007952,000066:                                                                                          	# THIS TIME 1/PIPA IS NOT CALLED.
007953,000067: 
007954,000068:                                                                                          	# LASTBIAS IS CALLED VIA EXECUTIVE WHEN MAKING THE TRANSITION FROM-FALL TO A PIPA READING MODE. THE NBD TERMS
007955,000069:                                                                                          	# ARE COMPENSATED FOR FROM THE LAST NBDONLY CALL UP TO PIPA ZEROING. PREREAD WILL THEN ENABLE 1/PIPA AT ITS
007956,000070:                                                                                          	# REGULAR INTERVAL. THE DRIFT FLAG MUST BE DOWN JUST PRIOR TO LASTBIAS. GYROCOMPASS NEVER CALLS LASTBIAS.
007957,000071: 
007958,000072:                                                                                          	# SCALING CONSIDERATIONS
007959,000073:                                                                                          	#                            UNITS              MAX. VALUE     INTERNAL UNITS AND SCALING
007960,000074: 
007961,000075:                                                                                          	#        PIPA BIAS           (CM)/(SEC)(SEC)    3.125          (PIPA PULSES)/(CS) X 2(-5) 
007962,000076:                                                                                          	#        PIPA SCALE FACTOR   P.P.M.             1953.125       (PPM) X 2(-9)
007963,000077:                                                                                          	#        NBD                 MERU               128.74604      (GYRO PULSES)/(CS) X 2(-5) 
007964,000078:                                                                                          	#        ADIA                (MERU)/(G)         630.36633      (GYRO PULSES)/(PIPA PULSE) X 2(-6)
007965,000079:                                                                                          	#        ADSRA               (MERU)/(G)         630.36633      (GYRO PULSES)/(PIPA PULSE) X 2(-6)
007966,000080: 
007967,000081:                                                                                          	##Page 210
007968,000082:                                                                                          	# CONVERSION TABLE
007969,000083:                                                                                          	#       1 PIPA PULSE = 1.00 (CM)/(SEC)(SEC)          1 ERU = 7.29209817 X 10(-5) (RAD)/(SEC)
007970,000084:                                                                                          	#       1 ERU = 15.04104488 (ARCSEC)/(SEC)           1 (CM)/(SEC)(SEC) = .01 (PIPA PULSES)/(CS)
007971,000085:                                                                                          	#       1 GYRO PULSE = .61798096 (ARCSEC)            1 MERU = .0024272592 (GYRO PULSES)/(CS)
007972,000086:                                                                                          	#       1 g = 979.24 (CM)/(SEC)(SEC)                 1 (MERU)/(G) = .000144787174 (GYRO PULSES)/(PIPA PULSE)
007973,000087: 
007974,000088:                                                                                          	# REFERENCES
007975,000089:                                                                                          	#       AGC PROGRAMMING MEMO NO. 12, I.S.S. MEMO NO. 247, I.S.S. MEMO NO 328, I.S.S. MEMO NO. 339
007976,000090: 
007977,000091:                                                                                          	# CALLING SEQUENCE 
007978,000092:                                                                                          	#       L      TC     BANKALL
007979,000093:                                                                                          	#       L+1    CADR   1/PIPA
007980,000094:                                                                                          	#       L+2                       RETURNS HERE
007981,000095: 
007982,000096:                                                                                          	# NORMAL EXIT MODES
007983,000097:                                                                                          	#       AT L+2 OF CALLING SEQUENCE
007984,000098: 
007985,000099:                                                                                          	# ALARM OR ABORT MODES
007986,000100:                                                                                          	#       ENDOFJOB
007987,000101: 
007988,000102:                                                                                          	# ERASABLE INITIALIZATION REQUIRED (CONSECUTIVE LOCATIONS)
007989,000103:                                                                                          	#       PBIASX    PIPAX BIAS
007990,000104:                                                                                          	#       PIPASCFX  PIPAX SCALE FACTOR ERROR
007991,000105:                                                                                          	#       PBIASY    PIPAY BIAS
007992,000106:                                                                                          	#       PIPASCFY  PIPAY SCALE FACTOR ERROR
007993,000107:                                                                                          	#       PBIASZ    PIPAZ BIAS
007994,000108:                                                                                          	#       PIPASCFZ  PIPAZ SCALE FACTOR ERROR
007995,000109:                                                                                          	#       NBDX      X IRIG BIAS DRIFT
007996,000110:                                                                                          	#       NBDY      Y IRIG BIAS DRIFT
007997,000111:                                                                                          	#       NDBZ      Z IRIG BIAS DRIFT
007998,000112:                                                                                          	#       ADIAX     IRIG ACCELERATION SENSITIVE DRIFT ALONG THE X INPUT AXIS  
007999,000113:                                                                                          	#       ADIAY     IRIG ACCELERATION SENSITIVE DRIFT ALONG THE Y INPUT AXIS 
008000,000114:                                                                                          	#       ADIAZ     IRIG ACCELERATION SENSITIVE DRIFT ALONG THE Z INPUT AXIS
008001,000115:                                                                                          	#       ADSRAX    IRIG ACCELERATION SENSITIVE DRIFT ALONG THE X SPIN REFERENCE AXIS      
008002,000116:                                                                                          	#       ADSRAY    IRIG ACCELERATION SENSITIVE DRIFT ALONG THE Y SPIN REFERENCE AXIS  
008003,000117:                                                                                          	#       ADSRAZ    IRIG ACCELERATION SENSITIVE DRIFT ALONG THE Z SPIN REFERENCE AXIS
008004,000118:                                                                                          	#       GCOMP     GYRO COMPENSATION PULSES (SET = ZERO FOR 1ST PASS)
008005,000119: 
008006,000120:                                                                                          	# INPUT
008007,000121:                                                                                          	#       1/PIPADT - DELTA TIME SCALED AT (CS) X 2(+8)
008008,000122:                                                                                          	#       DELVX, DELVY, DELVZ - PIPA READINGS IN THE MAJOR PARTS - MINOR PARTS IRRELEVANT 
008009,000123: 
008010,000124:                                                                                          	# OUTPUT
008011,000125:                                                                                          	#       DELVX, DELVY, DELVZ - PIPA COUNTS SCALED 2(+14) COMPENSATED FOR PIPA BIAS AND SCALE FACTOR ERROR
008012,000126:                                                                                          	#       GCOMP - 3 DP LOCATIONS CONTAINING GYRO PULSES TO COMPENSATE FOR NBD, ADIA, AND ADSRA COEFFICIENTS
008013,000127: 
008014,000128:                                                                                          	# DEBRIS
008015,000129:                                                                                          	#       CENTRALS - A,L,Q
008016,000130:                                                                                          	#       OTHER - BUF - BUF +2, VBUF - VBUF +2, GCOMPSW
008017,000131: 
008018,000132:                                                                                          	##Page 211

008890,000093: 07,2456           54342                           TS       UPLOCK                        	#

008896,000099: 07,2463           54021                           TS       SR                            	#

008903,000106: 07,2467           40021                           CS       SR                            	#
008904,000107: 07,2470           40021                           CS       SR                            	#
008905,000108: 07,2471           40021                           CS       SR                            	#
008906,000109: 07,2472           40000                           CS       A                             	#
008907,000110: 07,2473           00002                           TC       Q                             	# DELIVERS WORD UNCOMPLEMENTED
008908,000111: 
008909,000112: 07,2474           60077        UPTEST             AD       KEYTEMP1                      	#
008910,000113: 07,2475           10000                           CCS      A                             	#
008911,000114: 07,2476           02452                           TC       TMFAIL2                       	#
008912,000115: 07,2477           77740        HI10               OCT      77740                         	#
008913,000116: 07,2500           02452                           TC       TMFAIL2                       	#
008914,000117: 07,2501           00002                           TC       Q                             	#
008915,000118: 
008916,000119:                                                                                          	# UPACT IS TURNED OFF BY VBRELDSP, ALSO BY ERROR LIGHT RESET.       
008918,000121:                                                                                          	# THE RECEPTION OF A BAD CODE BY UPLINK LOCKS OUT FURTHER UPLINK ACTIVITY
008919,000122:                                                                                          	# BY PLACING A 1 INTO BIT1 OF UPLOCK. BIT9 (ALONG WITH BIT11) OF TMKEYBUF
008920,000123:                                                                                          	# IS SET TO 1 TO SEND AN INDICATION OF THIS SITUATION DOWN THE DOWNLINK.
008921,000124:                                                                                          	# THE UPLINK INTERLOCK IS ALLOWED WHEN AN ERROR LIGHT RESET CODE IS SENT
008922,000125:                                                                                          	# UP THE UPLINK, OR WHEN A FRESH START IS PERFORMED.
008923,000126: 
008924,000127: 07,2502                                           EQUALS                                 	#

009134,000050: 15,2020           03571                           ECADR    AGSBUFF    +18D               	#
009135,000051: 15,2021           03570                           ECADR    AGSBUFF    +17D               	#
009136,000052: 15,2022           03567                           ECADR    AGSBUFF    +16D               	#
009137,000053: 15,2023           00412                           ECADR    AGSWORD                       	#
009138,000054: 15,2024           03566                           ECADR    AGSBUFF    +15D               	#
009139,000055: 15,2025           03565                           ECADR    AGSBUFF    +14D               	#
009140,000056: 15,2026           03564                           ECADR    AGSBUFF    +13D               	#
009141,000057: 15,2027           03563                           ECADR    AGSBUFF    +12D               	#
009142,000058: 15,2030           00412                           ECADR    AGSWORD                       	#
009143,000059: 15,2031           03562                           ECADR    AGSBUFF    +11D               	#
009144,000060: 15,2032           03561                           ECADR    AGSBUFF    +10D               	#
009145,000061: 15,2033           01560                           ADRES    AGSBUFF    +9D                	#
009146,000062: 15,2034           01557                           ADRES    AGSBUFF    +8D                	#
009147,000063: 15,2035           00412                           ADRES    AGSWORD                       	#
009148,000064: 15,2036           01556                           ADRES    AGSBUFF    +7                 	#
009149,000065: 15,2037           01555                           ADRES    AGSBUFF    +6                 	#
009150,000066: 15,2040           01554                           ADRES    AGSBUFF    +5                 	#
009151,000067: 15,2041           01553                           ADRES    AGSBUFF    +4                 	#
009152,000068: 15,2042           00412                           ADRES    AGSWORD                       	#
009153,000069: 15,2043           01552                           ADRES    AGSBUFF    +3                 	#
009154,000070: 15,2044           01551                           ADRES    AGSBUFF    +2                 	#
009155,000071: 15,2045           01550                           ADRES    AGSBUFF    +1                 	#
009156,000072: 15,2046           01547                           ADRES    AGSBUFF                       	#
009158,000074:                                                                                          	#       THIS ROUTINE IS INITIATED EVERY 20MS BY AN INTERRUPT TRIGGERED
009159,000075:                                                                                          	# BY THE RECEIPT OF AN ENDPULSE FROM THE SPACECRAFT TELEMETRY PROGRAMMER.
009160,000076: 
009161,000077: 15,2047           54016        DODOWNTM           TS       BANKRUPT                      	# DO APPROPRIATE TM PHASE.
009162,000078: 15,2050           51401                           INDEX    DNTMGOTO                      	#
009163,000079: 15,2051           10000                           TCF      0                             	#
009164,000080: 
009165,000081: 15,2052           30411        DNPAHSE1           CA       DNLSTADR                      	# ONCE PER CYCLE (1 SECOND), AN ID IS SENT
009166,000082: 15,2053           55400                           TS       LDATALST                      	# AND THE DATA LIST SWITCHED TO THAT
009167,000083: 15,2054           76426                           MASK     LOW10                         	# SELECTED BY A MISSION OR TEST PROGRAM.
009168,000084: 15,2055           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
DOWN_TELEMETRY_PROGRAM.agc:85: Fatal Error: Symbol "DNTM1" undefined or offset bad
009169,000085: 15,2056           01000                           WRITE    DNTM1                         	#
009170,000086: 15,2057           47651                           CS       BIT7                          	# WORD ORDER BIT IS 0 FOR ID WORD ONLY.
009171,000087: 15,2060           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
009172,000088: 15,2061           03013                           WAND     13                            	#
009173,000089: 
009174,000090: 15,2062           32212                           CAF      LDNPHAS2                      	# SWITCH TO PHASE 2.
009175,000091: 15,2063           55401                           TS       DNTMGOTO                      	#
009176,000092: 15,2064           32000                           CAF      LOWIDCOD                      	# SPECIAL ID CODE IN L.
009177,000093: 15,2065           12151                           TCF      TMEXITL                       	#
009178,000094: 
009179,000095: 15,2066           37651        DNPHASE2           CAF      BIT7                          	# SET WORD ORDER BACK TO 1 FOR REMAINDER
009180,000096: 15,2067           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# OF CYCLE AND SET UP TO PICK UP 12 PAIRS
009181,000097: 15,2070           05013                           WOR      13                            	# FROM ANYWHERE IN COMMON ERASABLE OR E7.
009182,000098: 
009183,000099: 15,2071           37665                           CAF      ZERO                          	#
009184,000100: 15,2072           54065                           TS       ITEMP1                        	# TAKE SNAPSHOT OF 12 DP WORDS
009185,000101: 15,2073           37661                           CAF      TEN                           	#
009186,000102: 
009187,000103: 15,2074           54066        LOOP               TS       ITEMP2                        	# THESE 12 DP WORDS ARE READ INTO AN
009188,000104: 15,2075           61400                           AD       LDATALST                      	# INTERMEDIATE BUFFER SO THEY REFER TO THE
009189,000105: 15,2076           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# SAME POINT IN THE EXECUTION OF A MISSION
009190,000106: 15,2077           50000                           INDEX    A                             	# PROGRAM. THE WORDS MAY BE IN NON-
009191,000107: 15,2100           50032                           INDEX    26D                           	#
009192,000108: 15,2101           30001                           DCA      0                             	# 12 OF THE DATA LIST ARE USED AS
009193,000109: 15,2102           50065                           INDEX    ITEMP1                        	# ADDRESSES OF THE DESIRED DATA.
009194,000110: 15,2103           53404                           DXCH     DNTMBUFF                      	#
009195,000111: 
009196,000112: 15,2104           37656                           CAF      TWO                           	#
009197,000113: 15,2105           26065                           ADS      ITEMP1                        	#
009198,000114: 15,2106           10066                           CCS      ITEMP2                        	#
009199,000115: 15,2107           12074                           TCF      LOOP                          	#
009200,000116: 
009201,000117: 15,2110           32220                           CAF      DEC11                         	# SET UP TO SEND 11 REMAINING WORDS
009202,000118: 15,2111           55402                           TS       TMINDEX                       	#
009203,000119: 15,2112           32213                           CAF      LDNPHASX                      	#
009204,000120: 15,2113           55401                           TS       DNTMGOTO                      	#
009205,000121: 
009206,000122: 15,2114           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
009207,000123: 15,2115           51400                           INDEX    LDATALST                      	#
009209,000125: 15,2116           50045                           INDEX    37D                           	#
009210,000126: 15,2117           30001                           DCA      0                             	#
009211,000127: 15,2120           12146                           TCF      DNTMEXIT                      	#
009212,000128: 
009213,000129: 15,2121           55402        DNPHASXA           TS       TMINDEX                       	#
009214,000130: 15,2122           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
009215,000131: 15,2123           50000                           INDEX    A                             	# SENDS SNAPSHOT BUFFER.
009216,000132: 15,2124           52230                           INDEX    FIXLISTB                      	#
009217,000133: 15,2125           30001                           DCA      0                             	#
009218,000134: 15,2126           12146                           TCF      DNTMEXIT                      	#
009219,000135: 
009220,000136: 15,2127           11402        DNPHASEX           CCS      TMINDEX                       	# AT END OF SNAPSHOT TRANSMISSION, SET UP
009221,000137: 15,2130           12121                           TCF      DNPHASXA                      	# TO SEND 26 PRS FROM ANY ERASABLE LOC AS
009222,000138: 
009223,000139: 15,2131           32214                           CAF      LDNPHAS3                      	# SPECIFIED BY WORDS 1 - 26 OF THE DATA
009224,000140: 15,2132           55401                           TS       DNTMGOTO                      	# LIST.
009225,000141: 15,2133           32217                           CAF      NOGENWDS                      	#
009226,000142: 
009227,000143: 15,2134           55402        PHASE3A            TS       TMINDEX                       	# GET DP WORD FROM ANY EBANK.
009228,000144: 15,2135           61400                           AD       LDATALST                      	#
009229,000145: 15,2136           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
009230,000146: 15,2137           50000                           INDEX    A                             	#
009231,000147: 15,2140           30001                           DCA      0                             	# THIS GETS THE ADDRESS - MUST USE DCA
009232,000148: 15,2141           54003                           TS       EBANK                         	#
DOWN_TELEMETRY_PROGRAM.agc:149: Fatal Error: Symbol "LOW8" undefined or offset bad
009233,000149: 15,2142           70000                           MASK     LOW8                          	#
009234,000150: 15,2143           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
009235,000151: 15,2144           50000                           INDEX    A                             	#
009236,000152: 15,2145           31401                           DCA      3400                          	# (NOTE ASSEMBLY AS DCA 1400)
009237,000153: 15,2146           00006        DNTMEXIT           EXTEND                                 	# GENERAL DNTM EXIT LOCATION.

010003,000603: 20,2711           26002                           ADS      Q                             	# UNDERFLOW

010008,000608: 
010009,000609:                                                                                          	# RUPTCHK CHECKS THAT INTERRUPT DOES NOT OCCUR WHILE OVERFLOW OR UNDERFLOW
010010,000610:                                                                                          	# IS IN THE A REGISTER. ALSO CHECKS THAT INHINT RELINT WORK PROPERLY.
010011,000611: 20,2716           00004        RUPTCHK            INHINT                                 	#

010025,000625: 20,2734           02716                           TC       RUPTCHK                       	# THERE WAS AN INTERRUPT. START AGAIN.

010181,000781:                                                                                          	# BANK NUMBERS IN EB.

010297,000897: 
010299,000899:                                                                                          	# SKEEP1 HOLDS SUM
010300,000900:                                                                                          	# SKEEP2 HOLDS PRESENT CONTENTS OF ADDRESS IN ROPECHK AND SHOWSUM ROUTINES
010301,000901:                                                                                          	# SKEEP2 HOLDS BANK NUMBER IN LOW ORDER BITS DURING SHOWSUM DISPLAY
010302,000902:                                                                                          	# SKEEP3 HOLDS PRESENT ADDRESS (00000 TO 01777 IN COMMON FIXED BANKS)
010303,000903:                                                                                          	#                              (04000 TO 07777 IN FXFX BANKS)

010593,001193: 20,3666           02033                           TC       -0CHK                         	#
010594,001194: 20,3667           47642                           CS       SBIT14                        	# -20000
010595,001195: 20,3670           60001                           AD       L                             	#
010596,001196: 20,3671           02041                           TC       -1CHK                         	#
010597,001197: 
010598,001198:                                                                                          	# DIVIDE +37776 BY +37776.  THE RESULT SHOULD BE +37777 AND THE
010599,001199:                                                                                          	# REMAINDER SHOULD BE +37776.
010600,001200: 20,3672           37665        DV4CHK             CA       S+ZERO                        	#
010601,001201: 20,3673           54001                           TS       L                             	#
010602,001202: 20,3674           32011                           CA       DVCON                         	#
010603,001203: 20,3675           55371                           TS       SKEEP1                        	# 37776
010605,001205: 20,3676           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
010606,001206: 20,3677           11371                           DV       SKEEP1                        	#
010607,001207: 20,3700           40000                           CS       A                             	#
010608,001208: 20,3701           62011                           AD       DVCON                         	#
010609,001209: 20,3702           02041                           TC       -1CHK                         	#
010610,001210: 20,3703           30001                           CA       L                             	# 37776
010611,001211: 20,3704           63432                           AD       S-MAX                         	#
010612,001212: 20,3705           02041                           TC       -1CHK                         	#
010613,001213: 
010614,001214:                                                                                          	# DIVIDE SAME (ZERO).  THE CONTENTS OF THE A REGISTER AND L REGISTER WILL
010615,001215:                                                                                          	# HAVE OPPOSITE SIGNS BEFORE DIVISION.  THE QUOTIENT WILL BE + OR - MAX.,
010616,001216:                                                                                          	# DEPENDING UPON THE SIGN OF THE L REGISTER AND THE SIGN OF THE DIVISOR.
010617,001217:                                                                                          	# C(L) REMAINS THE SAME BECAUSE IT IS THE DIVIDEND.
010618,001218: 20,3706           37665        DV5CHK             CA       S+ZERO                        	#
010619,001219: 20,3707           55371                           TS       SKEEP1                        	# +0
010620,001220: 20,3710           54001                           TS       L                             	#
010621,001221: 20,3711           40000                           CS       A                             	#
010622,001222: 20,3712           55372                           TS       SKEEP2                        	# -0
010623,001223: 20,3713           00006        DV5++              EXTEND                                 	#
010624,001224: 20,3714           11371                           DV       SKEEP1                        	# +37777, +0
010625,001225: 20,3715           55377                           TS       SKEEP7                        	# 37777
010626,001226: 20,3716           30001                           CA       L                             	#
010627,001227: 20,3717           02032                           TC       +0CHK                         	#
010628,001228: 20,3720           40000        DV5+-              CS       A                             	#
010629,001229: 20,3721           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
010630,001230: 20,3722           11372                           DV       SKEEP2                        	# 40000, +0
010631,001231: 20,3723           55376                           TS       SKEEP6                        	# 40000
010632,001232: 20,3724           61377                           AD       SKEEP7                        	#
010633,001233: 20,3725           02033                           TC       -0CHK                         	#
010634,001234: 20,3726           40000                           CS       A                             	#
010635,001235: 20,3727           56001                           XCH      L                             	# ALSO PUT -0 IN L
010636,001236: 20,3730           02032                           TC       +0CHK                         	#
010637,001237: 20,3731           00006        DV5-+              EXTEND                                 	#
010638,001238: 20,3732           11371                           DV       SKEEP1                        	# 40000, -0
010639,001239: 20,3733           61377                           AD       SKEEP7                        	#
010640,001240: 20,3734           02033                           TC       -0CHK                         	#

011099,000033: 
011100,000034:                                                                                          	# LEM FCS TEST  ENTRY AND INITIALIZATION JOB.
011101,000035: 
011102,000036:                                                                                          	#       THIS JOB INITIALIZES THE ERASABLE TABLES FOR THE FCS TEST AND PUTS THE FOLLOWING PROGRAMS UNDER
011103,000037:                                                                                          	# WAITLIST CONTROL.
011104,000038:                                                                                          	#            (1) RCS JET SET TASK
011105,000039:                                                                                          	#            (2) ENGINE ON - OFF TASK
011106,000040:                                                                                          	#            (3) DESCENT ENGINE GIMBAL TRIM TASK
011107,000041:                                                                                          	#            (4) DESCENT ENGINE THROTTLE TASK
011108,000042:                                                                                          	#            (5) INTERFACE CONTROL CHANNEL LOOK TASK

011170,000104: 
011171,000105:                                                                                          	# Page 433
011172,000106:                                                                                          	# LEM FCS TEST   RCS JETSET TASK
011173,000107:                                                                                          	#     THIS JOB ISSUES A PROFILE OF  JET ON-OFF SIGNALS AS DETERMINED BY THE CONSTANTS IN A SET OF SIX REGISTERS.
011174,000108:                                                                                          	# THE SIX REGISTERS ARE, (1) NTIMES, THE NUMBER OF TIMES A PARTICULAR STEP WILL BE PERFORMED. (2) NEXTTIME, THE
011175,000109:                                                                                          	# TIME BETWEEN STEPS, A MAXIMUM OF 2 MINUTES, (3) JETONTM, THE TIME TO TURN THE JETS ON, SCALED FOR T3, (4) JET-
011176,000110:                                                                                          	# OFFTM, THE TIME AFTER ONTM TO TURN THE JETS OFF, (5) XJETS, THE PARTICULAR X JETS TO BE TURNED ON AND OFF
011177,000111:                                                                                          	# DURING EACH REPEAT OF A STEP, AND (6) YZJETS,, THE Y AND Z JETS TO BE TURNED ON AND OFF DURING EACH REPEAT OF A
011178,000112:                                                                                          	# STEP.  XJETS AND YZJETS MUST BE IN THE SAME FORMAT AS CHANNELS 5 AND6 RESPECTIVELY.  THERE ARE EIGHT SETS OF
011179,000113:                                                                                          	# THESE SIX REGISTERS.
011180,000114:                                                                                          	#     THE REGISTER JETSTEP IS USED TO INDEX THE 8 SETS OF REGISTERS, THE ALLOWABLE VALUES OF JETSTEP ARE +0 THRU 7
011181,000115:                                                                                          	#     THIS JOB WILL BE ENTERED BUT IMMEDIATELY ENDED IF THE INITIAL VALUES OF JETSTEP AND NTIMES ARE +0.

011289,000223:                                                                                          	# LEM FCS TEST  ENGINE ON - OFF TASK
011290,000224:                                                                                          	# THIS TASK TURNS THE LEM ASCENT OR DESCENT ENGINE ON AND OFF ACCORDING TOTHE CONSTANTS STORED IN THE FIVE SETS OF
011291,000225:                                                                                          	# REGISTERS, (1) CYLTIMES, WHICH CONTAINS THE NUMBER OF TIMES A PARTICULARSTEP WILL BE REPEATED, (2) NEXTCYLT,
011292,000226:                                                                                          	#  WHICH CONTAINS THE TIME BETWEEN STEPS SCALED FOR T3, (3) ONTIME, WHICH CONTAINS THE TIME TO TURN THE ENGINE ON
011293,000227:                                                                                          	# WHICH ALSO DETERMINES THE LENGTH OF TIME THE ENGINE WILL BE OFF WITHIN A SERIES OF ON:OFF CYCLES, (4) OFFTIME,
011294,000228:                                                                                          	#  WHICH CONTAINS THE NUMBER OF 2 MINUTES BEFORE THE ENGINE WILL BE TURNED OFF, AND (5) OFFTIMER, WHICH
011295,000229:                                                                                          	# CONTAINS THE RESIDUAL TIME BEFORE THE ENGINE WILL BE TURNED OFF.  OFFTIME AND OFFTIMER DETERMINE THE LENGTH
011296,000230:                                                                                          	# OF TIME THE ENGINE WILL BE ON IN ANY ONE CYCLE. THERE ARE THREE SETS OF THESE REGISTERS.
011297,000231:                                                                                          	#     THE ENGSTEP REGISTER IS USED AS AN INDEX TO PICK UP A PARTICULAR SET  OF THE ABOVE 5 REGISTERS.  THIS TASK
011298,000232:                                                                                          	# WILL BE ENTERED BUT IMMEDIATELY ENDED IF ENGSTEP AND CYLTIMES = +0.     THE ALLOWABLE VALUES OF ENGSTEP ARE +0,
011299,000233:                                                                                          	# 1 AND 2.

011375,000309:                                                                                          	# LEM FCS TEST  TRIM TASK
011376,000310:                                                                                          	# THIS PROGRAM ISSUES A PROFILE OF PITCH AND ROLL TRIM COMMANDS TO THE LEM DESCENT ENGINE GIMBAL IN ACCORDANCEWITH
011377,000311:                                                                                          	# THE VALUE S IN THE TRIMSTEP REGISTER AND THE 12 SETS OF 5 REGISTERS CALLED NUMTIMES, STEPDLYT, TRIMONT, TRIMOFFT
011378,000312:                                                                                          	# AND TRIMIND.  TRIMSTEP IS USED TO PICK UP A PARTICULAR SET OF THE 5 REGISTERS AND HAS ALLOWABLE VALUES FROM +0
011379,000313:                                                                                          	# THROUGH +11 DECIMAL.  THE 5 REGISTERS IN EACH SET ARE DEFINED AS FOLLOWS
011380,000314:                                                                                          	#     (1) NUMTIMES DETERMINES THE NUMBER OF TIMES THE COMMAND IN TRIMIND  WILL BE ISSUED.  VALUES FROM +0 TO
011381,000315:                                                                                          	# OCT 37777 ARE PERMITTED.
011382,000316:                                                                                          	#     (2) STEPDLYT DETERMINES THE TIME BETWEEN THE START OF A STEP AND THE BEGINNING OF TRIMONT.  STEPDLYT MUST BE
011383,000317:                                                                                          	# FORMATTED FOR T3, ITS MAXIMUM VALUE IS 2 MINUTES.
011384,000318:                                                                                          	#     (3) TRIMONT DETERMINES THE TIME BETWEEN THE END OF STEPDLYT OR TRIMOFFT AND THE TIME THE TRIM COMMANDS ARE
011385,000319:                                                                                          	# ISSUED.  IT MUST BE FORMATTED FOR T3.
011386,000320:                                                                                          	#     (4) TRIMOFFT DETERMINES THE LENGTH OF TIME THE TRIM COMMAND WILL BE ON, FORMATTED FOR T3.
011387,000321:                                                                                          	#     (5) TRIMIND DETERMINES THE PITCH AND ROLL COMMAND TO BE ISSUED.  THE FORMAT IS, BIT9=1=+ PITCH COMMAND,
011388,000322:                                                                                          	# BIT10=1=-PITCH, BIT11=1= +ROLL, BIT12=1= -ROLL.  A BIT=0 INDICATES NO COMMAND.  ANY COMBINATION OF COMMANDS IS
011389,000323:                                                                                          	# PERMITTED.
011390,000324:                                                                                          	#    THIS TASK WILL BE ENTERED BUT IMMEDIATELY ENDED IF TRIMSTEP AND NUMTIMES = +0.
011391,000325: 
011392,000326:

011486,000420: 
011488,000422:                                                                                          	# LEM FCS TEST  THROTTLE TASK
011489,000423:                                                                                          	#    THIS PROGRAM ISSUES A PROFILE OF THROTTLE COMMANDS TO THE LEM DESCENT ENGINE.  THE PROFILE IS DETERMINED BY
011490,000424:                                                                                          	# THE VALUES IN THE THRTSTEP REGISTER AND THE 6  SETS OF REGISTERS, 5 PER SET, CALLED  DOTIMES, DELAY, THR1TIME,
011491,000425:                                                                                          	# THCOMM1 AND THCOMM2.  THE THRTSTEP REGISTER VALUE IS USED TO INDEX THE  6  SETS OF 5 REGISTERS AND HAS ALLOWABLE
011492,000426:                                                                                          	# VALUES OF +0 THROUGH +5.  THE 5 REGISTERS PER SET ARE DEFINED AS FOLLOWS
011493,000427:                                                                                          	#     (1) DOTIMES DETERMINES THE NUMBER OF TIMES THE THROTTLE WILL BE EXERCISED AS PER THE VALUES OF THR1TIME,
011494,000428:                                                                                          	# THCOMM1 AND THCOMM2 OF THE CURRENT STEP.  IT HAS ALLOWABLE VALUES OF +0 THROUGH 37777 OCT.
011495,000429:                                                                                          	#     (2) DELAY DETERMINES THE TIME BETWEEN THE START OF A STEP AND THE BE GINNING OF THR1TIME. ITIS CALLED ONLY
011496,000430:                                                                                          	# ONCE PER STEP,I.E., REPEATS OF THE SAME THCOMM1 AND THCOMM2 START AT THR1TIME.  DELAY MUST BE FORMATTED FOR T3
011497,000431:                                                                                          	# AND HENCE HAS A MAXIMUM VALUE OF 2 MINUTES.
011498,000432:                                                                                          	#     (3) THR1TIME DETERMINES THE TIME BETWEEN THE END OF DELAY OR THE END   OF THCOMM2 AND THE START OF
011499,000433:                                                                                          	# THCOMM1.  IT MUST BE FORMATTED FOR T3.
011500,000434:                                                                                          	#     (4) THCOMM1 AND (5) THCOMM2 DETERMINE THE NUMBER OF THRUST INCREASE  OR DECREASE PULSES TOBE ISSUED AT A
011501,000435:                                                                                          	# 3.2KPPS RATE.  THE RANGE OF POSSIBLE VALUES OF EITHER IS FROM POSMAX (OCT 37777) TO NEGMAX (OCT 40000) ALTHOUGH
011502,000436:                                                                                          	# THE ACTUAL THROTTLE RANGE IS FROM OCT 6116 TO OCT 71661 (+,- 3150 DEC).
011503,000437:                                                                                          	#    THIS TASK WILL BE ENTERED BUT IMMEDIATELY ENDED IF THE INITIAL VALUES OF THRTSTEP AND DOTIMES ARE +0.
011504,000438: 
011505,000439: 
011506,000440: 06,2431           11605        NEXTTHRT           CCS      THRTSTEP                      	#
011507,000441: 06,2432           02434                           TC       +2                            	#
011508,000442: 06,2433           04602                           TC       TASKOVER                      	# EXIT HERE.
011509,000443: 06,2434           55605                           TS       THRTSTEP                      	#
011510,000444: 
011511,000445: 06,2435           51605        THRSTART           NDX      THRTSTEP                      	# ENTER HERE.
011512,000446: 06,2436           11606                           CCS      DOTIMES                       	# NUMBER OF TIMES COMMANDS 1 AND 2 DONE.
011513,000447: 06,2437           02441                           TC       +2                            	#
011514,000448: 06,2440           02431                           TC       NEXTTHRT                      	#
011515,000449: 06,2441           51605                           NDX      THRTSTEP                      	#
011516,000450: 06,2442           31614                           CAE      DELAY                         	# TIME BETWEEN STEPS.  BIAS FOR THR1TIME.
011517,000451:                                                                                          	# MUST BE SCALED FOR T3.
011518,000452: 06,2443           04536                           TC       WAITLIST                      	#
011519,000453: 06,2444  E4,1605                                  EBANK=   THRTSTEP                      	#
011520,000454: 06,2444           02467 14064                     2CADR    THROTON1                      	#

011526,000460: 06,2451           02505                           TC       THROTON                       	#
