011528,000462: 06,2453           04536                           TC       WAITLIST                      	#
011529,000463: 06,2454  E4,1605                                  EBANK=   THRTSTEP                      	#
011530,000464: 06,2454           02457 14064                     2CADR    CKDOTIME                      	#
011531,000465:

011533,000467:

011540,000474: 06,2464           67657                           AD       ONE                           	#

011575,000509: 06,2522           00031        250MS              OCT      00031                         	#
011576,000510: 
011578,000512:                                                                                          	# LEM FCS TEST  INTERFACE LOOK TASK.
011579,000513: 
011580,000514:                                                                                          	#     THIS PROGRAM KEEPS A RUNNING HISTORY OF THE STATE OF ALL THE BITS IN INPUT CHANNELS 30, 31, 32 AND 33.
011581,000515:                                                                                          	# IT DOES THIS BY DETECTING A CHANGE OF AN INPUT BIT FROM AN INITIAL ONE STATE TO A ZERO STATE OR FROM AN INITIAL
011582,000516:                                                                                          	# ZERO TO A ONE.  THE HISTORY IS MAINTAINED IN TWO BUFFER REGISTERS FOR EACH CHANNEL, ONE FOR STORING ONE TO ZERO
011583,000517:                                                                                          	# CHANGES (30BUF1, +1, +2, AND +3) AND ONE FOR ZERO TO ONE CHANGES (30BUF0, +1 +2 AND +3).  THE OPERATOR MUST
011584,000518:                                                                                          	# LOAD THE INITIAL STATES OF THE INPUT CHANNELS INTO THEIR RESPECTIVE BUFFER REGISTERS BEFORE THIS PROGRAM IS IN-
011585,000519:                                                                                          	# ITIATED.
011586,000520:                                                                                          	#     TO ALLOW THIS PROGRAM TO RUN C(QUITLOOK) MUST BE SET GREATER THAN +0 BEFORE IT IS STARTED.  IF THE OPERATOR
011587,000521:                                                                                          	# DOES NOT DESIRE THIS PROGRAM TO RUN HE SHOULD SET C(QUITLOOK)=+0 BEFORE STARTING THE FCS TEST.  AFTER THIS TASK
011588,000522:                                                                                          	# IS RUNNING THE OPERATOR CAN STOP IT BY SETTING C(QUITLOOK) = +0.
011589,000523:                                                                                          	#     NO DISPLAYS OF EITHER THE BUFFER REGISTERS OR CHANNELS ARE INCORPORATED INTO THIS PROGRAM.  THIS WAS DONE TO
011590,000524:                                                                                          	# ALLOW THE TEST OPERATOR MONITORING FLEXIBILITY.  FOR REAL TIME MONITORING IT IS SUGGESTED THAT THE BUFFER
011591,000525:                                                                                          	# REGISTERS BE DISPLAYED WITH THE MONITOR VERBS (11 THROUGH 15).  ON THE OTHER HAND, THE OPERATOR MAY ELECT TO
011592,000526:                                                                                          	# PERFORM NO REAL TIME MONITORING UNTIL THE TEST IS COMPLETED, WHEN THE BUFFER REGISTERS WOULD BE CALLED FOR
011593,000527:                                                                                          	# DISPLAY (VERB 01) AND RECORDED.
011594,000528:                                                                                          	#     THIS PROGRAM IS PRIMARILY INTENDED FOR INTERFACE MONITORING DURING THE LEM VIBRATION TEST AT BETHPAGE, N.Y.,
011595,000529:                                                                                          	# ALTHOUGH IT MAY ALSO BE USEFUL DURING VEHICAL LEVEL EMI TESTS.
011596,000530: 
011597,000531: 06,2523           11654        LOOKTOP            CCS      QUITLOOK                      	# IS THIS TASK WANTED.
011598,000532: 06,2524           02526                           TC       +2                            	# YES.
011599,000533: 06,2525           04602                           TC       TASKOVER                      	# NO.
011600,000534: 06,2526           36165                           CAF      THREE                         	# START SCAN OF CHANNELS.
011601,000535: 06,2527           55655        LOOKLOOP           TS       CHCNTR                        	# 3, 2, 1, 0.
011602,000536: 06,2530           51655                           NDX      CHCNTR                        	#
011603,000537: 06,2531           31644                           CAE      30BUF1                        	#
011604,000538: 06,2532           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
011605,000539: 06,2533           51655                           NDX      CHCNTR                        	#
011606,000540: 06,2534           02030                           RAND     30                            	# DETECTS CHANGES FROM 1 TO 0.
011607,000541: 06,2535           51655                           NDX      CHCNTR                        	#
011608,000542: 06,2536           57644                           XCH      30BUF1                        	# STORE NEW ZEROS.
011609,000543: 06,2537           51655                           NDX      CHCNTR                        	#
011610,000544: 06,2540           31650                           CAE      30BUF0                        	#
011611,000545: 06,2541           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
011612,000546: 06,2542           51655                           NDX      CHCNTR                        	#
011613,000547: 06,2543           04030                           ROR      30                            	# DETECTS CHANGES FROM 0 TO 1.
011614,000548: 06,2544           51655                           NDX      CHCNTR                        	#
011615,000549: 06,2545           57650                           XCH      30BUF0                        	# STORE NEW ONES.
011616,000550: 06,2546           11655                           CCS      CHCNTR                        	# IS THIS SCAN DONE.
011617,000551: 06,2547           02527                           TC       LOOKLOOP                      	# NO.
011618,000552: 06,2550           37661                           CAF      TEN                           	# YES.  100MS RECALL.
011619,000553: 06,2551           04536                           TC       WAITLIST                      	#
011620,000554: 06,2552  E4,1654                                  EBANK=   QUITLOOK                      	#
011621,000555: 06,2552           02523 14064                     2CADR    LOOKTOP                       	#
011622,000556: 
011623,000557: 06,2554           04602                           TC       TASKOVER                      	#
011624,000558: 06,2555                        ENDLFCSS           =                                      	#

012767,001142: 
012769,001144:                                                                                          	#      THE AOT ANGLE CHECKING PROGRAM PROVIDES A SIMPLE VERIFICATION OF THE ACCURACY OF THE AOT,  THE IDEA IS TO
012770,001145:                                                                                          	# COMPUTE THE ANGLE BETWEEN TWO LINES OF SIGHT AS INDICATED BY THE AOT, WHICH IS WHAT THIS PROGRAM DOES.
012771,001146:                                                                                          	# INDEPENDENT KNOWLEDGE OF THE INCLUDED ANGLE PROVIDES A COMPARISON AND THUS A MEASURE OF THE AOT ACCURACY.
012772,001147:                                                                                          	#       THE ISS NEED NOT BE ON TO RUN THIS PROGRAM.

013837,000909: 17,3421           03564                           TC       POSN11                        	# COMPASS POSITION
013838,000910: 
013840,000912:                                                                                          	# WE WILL DENOTE THE FLASHING DISPLAY OF A HORIZONTAL TEST BY DH
013841,000913:                                                                                          	# (XXX.XX MERU) AND A VERTICAL TEST BY DV (XXX.XX MERU) EACH POSITION TELL
013842,000914:                                                                                          	# HOW THE DISPLAYS ARE RELATED TO TTHE DRIFT COEFFICIENTS BEING MEASURED.
013843,000915:                                                                                          	# NOTE THAT IT IS ILLEGAL TO RUN VERTICAL IN POS 6,4, OR 2 WITHOUT FIRST
013844,000916:                                                                                          	# RUNNING HORIZONTAL OF POS 5,3, OR1. THIS IS BECAUSE THE HORIZ DRIFT CALC
013845,000917:                                                                                          	# IN 1,3, OR 5 IS USED AS EAST DRIFFFT FOR VERTICAL TEST. THIS IS DONE BY
013846,000918:                                                                                          	# THE MACHINE AUTOMATICALLY EXCEPT FOR VERTICAL POSITION 6 WHICH THE
013847,000919:                                                                                          	# OPERATOR MUST DO. (SEE POSITION 6 BELOW)
013848,000920: 17,3422           37642        POSN1              CA       HALF                          	# X UP, Y SOUTH, Z EAST
013849,000921: 17,3423           55400                           TS       XSM                           	#
013850,000922: 17,3424           55410                           TS       YSM        +2                 	#   NBDY = DH
013851,000923: 17,3425           55420                           TS       ZSM        +4                 	#
013852,000924: 17,3426           37665        NGUBGH             CA       ZERO                          	#
013853,000925: 17,3427           55541                           TS       PIPINDEX                      	#

013900,000972:                                                                                          	# TO RUN POSITION 6 VERTICAL AFTER PIP TEST POS 6 IS DISPLAYED THE OPERATR
013901,000973:                                                                                          	# MUST CALCULATE FROM 2.5 -NBDZ-ADSRAZ  (XXX.XX)MERU.    WHEN PI
013902,000974:                                                                                          	# IP DATA FLASHES DO VERB 33 ENTER. THIS STARTS VERTICAL TEST. THEN THE

014760,000029: 
014762,000031:                                                                                          	# THIS PROGRAM USES A VERTICAL,SOUTH,EAST COORDINATE SYSTEM FOR PIPAS
014763,000032: 21,2000                                           BANK     21                            	#
014764,000033: 21,2000  E5,1400                                  EBANK=   XSM                           	#
014765,000034: 
014766,000035:                                                                                          	# G SCHMIDT SIMPLIFIED ESTIMATION PROGRAM FOR ALIGNMENT CALIBRATION. THE
014767,000036:                                                                                          	# PROGRAM IS COMPLETELY RESTART PROFED. DATA STORED IN BANK4.
014768,000037: 21,2000           04614        ESTIMS             TC       PHASCHNG                      	#
014769,000038: 21,2001           00101                           OCT      00101                         	#
014770,000039: 21,2002           00004        RSTGTS1            INHINT                                 	#  COMES HERE PHASE1 RESTART
014771,000040: 21,2003           30025                           CA       TIME1                         	#
014772,000041: 21,2004           55745                           TS       GTSWTLST                      	#
014773,000042: 21,2005           37665                           CAF      ZERO                          	# ZERO THE PIPAS
014774,000043: 21,2006           54037                           TS       PIPAX                         	#
014775,000044: 21,2007           54040                           TS       PIPAY                         	#
014776,000045: 21,2010           54041                           TS       PIPAZ                         	#

014778,000047: 21,2012           54406                           TS       DELVY      +1                 	#
014779,000048: 21,2013           54410                           TS       DELVZ      +1                 	#
014780,000049: 21,2014           00003                           RELINT                                 	#
014781,000050: 21,2015           02753                           TC       SETUPER                       	#
014782,000051: 21,2016           33360                           CA       77DECML                       	#
014783,000052: 21,2017           55776                           TS       ZERONDX                       	#
014784,000053: 21,2020           33361                           CA       ALXXXZ                        	#
014785,000054: 21,2021           04063                           TC       BANKCALL                      	#
014786,000055: 21,2022           37236                           CADR     ZEROING                       	#
014787,000056: 21,2023           06000                           TC       INTPRET                       	#
014788,000057: 21,2024           77775                           VLOAD                                  	#
014789,000058: 21,2025           03353                                    INTVAL     +2                 	#
014790,000059: 21,2026           02601                           STORE    ALX1S                         	#
014791,000060: 21,2027           77776                           EXIT                                   	#
014792,000061: 
014793,000062: 21,2030           11742                           CCS      GEOCOMPS                      	# GEOCOMPS IN NON ZERO IF COMPASS
014794,000063: 21,2031           02033                           TC       +2                            	#

014804,000073:

015643,000054: 
015644,000055: $DIGITAL_AUTOPILOT_ERASABLE.agc			# 535
015646,000002:                                                                                          	# Copyright:    Public domain.
015647,000003:                                                                                          	# Filename:     DIGITAL_AUTOPILOT_ERASABLE.agc
015648,000004:                                                                                          	# Purpose:      Part of the source code for Aurora (revision 12).
015649,000005:                                                                                          	# Assembler:    yaYUL
015650,000006:                                                                                          	# Contact:      Ron Burkey <info@sandroid.org>.
015651,000007:                                                                                          	# Website:      https://www.ibiblio.org/apollo.
015652,000008:                                                                                          	# Pages:        535-541
015653,000009:                                                                                          	# Mod history:  2016-09-20 JL   Created.
015654,000010:                                                                                          	#               2016-09-30 MAS  Began.
015655,000011:                                                                                          	#               2016-10-01 MAS  Completed transcription.
015656,000012:                                                                                          	#               2016-10-04 HG   Capitalize SETLOC`
015657,000013: 
015658,000014:                                                                                          	# This source code has been transcribed or otherwise adapted from
015659,000015:                                                                                          	# digitized images of a hardcopy from the private collection of 
015660,000016:                                                                                          	# Don Eyles.  The digitization was performed by archive.org.
015661,000017: 
015662,000018:                                                                                          	# Notations on the hardcopy document read, in part:
015663,000019: 
015664,000020:                                                                                          	#       473423A YUL SYSTEM FOR BLK2: REVISION 12 of PROGRAM AURORA BY DAP GROUP
015665,000021:                                                                                          	#       NOV 10, 1966
015666,000022: 
015667,000023:                                                                                          	#       [Note that this is the date the hardcopy was made, not the
015668,000024:                                                                                          	#       date of the program revision or the assembly.]
015669,000025: 
015670,000026:                                                                                          	# The scan images (with suitable reduction in storage size and consequent 
015671,000027:                                                                                          	# reduction in image quality) are available online at 
015672,000028:                                                                                          	#       https://www.ibiblio.org/apollo.  
015673,000029:                                                                                          	# The original high-quality digital images are available at archive.org:
015674,000030:                                                                                          	#       https://archive.org/details/aurora00dapg
015675,000031: 
015677,000033: E6,1400                                           SETLOC   3000                          	#
015678,000034: 
015679,000035:                                                                                          	# AXIS TRANSFORMATION MATRIX - PILOT TO GIMBAL AXES:
015680,000036: 
015681,000037: E6,1400                        MR12               ERASE                                  	# SCALED AT 2   THESE FOUR P-G MATRIX ELE-
015682,000038: E6,1401                        MR22               ERASE                                  	# SCALED AT 1   MENTS ARE IN THIS ORDER TO
015683,000039: E6,1402                        MR13               ERASE                                  	# SCALED AT 2   COMPUTE RATE HOLD DELCDUS
015684,000040: E6,1403                        MR23               ERASE                                  	# SCALED AT 1   WITH AN INDEXED LOOP
015685,000041:                                                                                          	# AXIS TRANSFORMATION MATRIX - GIMBAL TO PILOT AXES:
015686,000042: 
015687,000043: E6,1404                        M11                ERASE                                  	# SCALED AT 1
015688,000044: E6,1405                        M21                ERASE                                  	# SCALED AT 1
015689,000045: E6,1406                        M31                ERASE                                  	#
015690,000046: E6,1407  E6,1401               M22                EQUALS   MR22                          	# SCALED AT 1
015691,000047: E6,1407  E6,1403               M32                EQUALS   MR23                          	# SCALED AT 1
015692,000048:                                                                                          	# ANGLE MEASUREMENTS.
015693,000049: 
015694,000050: E6,1407                        EDOT               ERASE    +1                            	# ERROR IN ANGULAR RATE:
015695,000051: E6,1411  E6,1410               EDOT(R)            EQUALS   EDOT       +1                 	# SCALED DOWN TO PI/16 RADIANS/SECOND
015696,000052: 
015697,000053: E6,1411                        E                  ERASE    +1                            	# ANGLE ERROR SCALED AT PI RADIANS
015698,000054: E6,1413  E6,1412               EDOT(2)            EQUALS   E          +1                 	# ERROR RATE SQUARED SCALED AT PI(2)/16
015699,000055: E6,1413  E6,1411               EQ                 EQUALS   E                             	# THIS PAIR OF NAMES IS USED TO REFER TO
015700,000056: E6,1413  E6,1412               EDOT(2)Q           EQUALS   EDOT(2)                       	# THE ABOVE ERASABLES AS Q-AXIS DATA
015701,000057: E6,1413                        ER                 ERASE    +1                            	# THIS PAIR OF NAMES REFERS TO LOCATIONS
015702,000058: E6,1415  E6,1414               EDOT(2)R           EQUALS   ER         +1                 	# FOR THE R-AXIS DATA: INTERCHANGES WITH Q
015703,000059: 
015704,000060: E6,1415                        DB                 ERASE                                  	# ANGLE DEADBAND SCALED AT PI RADIANS
015705,000061: 
015706,000062: E6,1416                        OMEGAP             ERASE    +4                            	# BODY-AXIS ROT. RATES SCALED AT PI/4 AND
015707,000063: E6,1423  E6,1417               OMEGAQ             EQUALS   OMEGAP     +1                 	# BODY-AXIS ACCELERATIONS SCALED AT PI/8
015708,000064: E6,1423  E6,1420               ALPHAQ             EQUALS   OMEGAP     +2                 	# (IN DESCENT) OR PI/2 (IN ASCENT)
015709,000065: E6,1423  E6,1421               OMEGAR             EQUALS   OMEGAP     +3                 	# THESE W,A PAIRS ARE NEEDED, ALPHAP HAS
015710,000066: E6,1423  E6,1422               ALPHAR             EQUALS   OMEGAP     +4                 	# NO USE IN THE DIGITAL AUTOPILOT
015711,000067: 
015712,000068: E6,1423                        EDOTP              ERASE    +2                            	# ERRORS IN ANGULAR RATE:
015713,000069: E6,1426  E6,1424               EDOTQ              EQUALS   EDOTP      +1                 	# EDOT = 3MEGA - OMEGA(DESIRED)
015714,000070: E6,1426  E6,1425               EDOTR              EQUALS   EDOTP      +2                 	# SCALED AT PI/4 RADIANS/SECOND
015715,000071: 
015716,000072: E6,1426  E6,1424               QRATEDIF           EQUALS   EDOTQ                         	# ALTERNATIVE NAMES:
015717,000073: E6,1426  E6,1425               RRATEDIF           EQUALS   EDOTR                         	# DELETE WHEN NO. OF REFERENCES = 0
015718,000074: 
015719,000075: E6,1426                        OMEGAPD            ERASE    +2                            	# DESIRED VEHICLE RATES DETERMINED BY THE
015720,000076: E6,1431  E6,1427               OMEGAQD            EQUALS   OMEGAPD    +1                 	# "OUTER LOOP" USED TO CALCULATE EDOT
015721,000077: E6,1431  E6,1430               OMEGARD            EQUALS   OMEGAPD    +2                 	# SCALED AT PI/4 RADIANS/SECOND
015722,000078: 
015723,000079: E6,1431                        OLDXFORP           ERASE    +3                            	# STORED CDU READINGS FOR P AND Q,R RATE
015724,000080: E6,1435  E6,1432               OLDYFORP           EQUALS   OLDXFORP   +1                 	# DERIVATIONS: SCALED AT PI RADIANS (2'S)
015725,000081: E6,1435  E6,1433               OLDYFORQ           EQUALS   OLDXFORP   +2                 	# (THERE MUST BE TWO REGISTERS FOR CDUY
015726,000082: E6,1435  E6,1434               OLDZFORQ           EQUALS   OLDXFORP   +3                 	# SINCE P AND Q,R ARE NOT IN PHASE)
015727,000083: 
015729,000085:                                                                                          	# RHC INPUTS SCALED AT PI/4 RAD/SEC.
015730,000086:

015816,000172: 
015818,000174:                                                                                          	# TRIM GIMBAL CONTROL LAW ERASABLES:
015819,000175: 
015820,000176:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING ASSIGNMENTS OF RUPTREGS AND ITEMPS HAS BEEN MADE IN AN EFFORT TO OPTIMIZE USE OF ERASABLES:
015821,000177: 
015822,000178: E6,1526     0074               K2THETA            EQUALS   RUPTREG1                      	# D.P. K(2)THETA AND "NEGUSUM"
015823,000179: E6,1526     0075               ETHETA             EQUALS   RUPTREG2                      	# S.P. ERROR ANGLE SCALED AT PI/64 RADIANS
015824,000180: E6,1526     0076               A2CNTRAL           EQUALS   RUPTREG3                      	# D.P. ALPHA(2) SCALED AT PI(2)/64 R/S(2)
015825,000181: E6,1526     0076               SF1                EQUALS   RUPTREG3                      	# S.P. VARIABLE SCALE FACTORS WHICH ARE
015826,000182: E6,1526     0077               SF2                EQUALS   RUPTREG4                      	# S.P. - REALLY SINGLE BITS (OR ZERO)
015827,000183: E6,1526     0065               OMEGA.K            EQUALS   ITEMP1                        	# D.P. OMEGA*K SUPERCEDES K AND K(2)
015828,000184: E6,1526     0065               KCENTRAL           EQUALS   ITEMP1                        	# S.P. K FROM KQ OR KR FIRST AT PI/2(8)
015829,000185: E6,1526     0066               K2CNTRAL           EQUALS   ITEMP2                        	# S.P. K(2) FROM Q OR R 1ST AT PI(2)/2(16)
015830,000186: E6,1526     0070               WCENTRAL           EQUALS   ITEMP3                        	# S.P. OMEGA SCALED AT PI/4 RADIANS/SECOND
015831,000187: E6,1526     0071               ACENTRAL           EQUALS   ITEMP4                        	# S.P. ALPHA SCALED AT PI/8 RAD/SEC(2)
015832,000188: E6,1526     0072               DEL                EQUALS   ITEMP5                        	# S.P. SGN(FUNCTION)
015833,000189: E6,1526     0073               QRCNTR             EQUALS   ITEMP6                        	# S.P. COUNTER: Q,Y=0, R,Z=2
015834,000190: 
015835,000191:                                                                                          	# THE ABOVE QUANTITIES ARE ONLY NEEDED ON A VERY TEMPORARY BASIS AND HAVE BEEN PROVEN TO BE NON-CONFLICTING.
015836,000192: 
015837,000193: E6,1526                        L,PVT-CG           ERASE                                  	# TRIM GIMBAL PIVOT TO CG DIST AT 8 FEET
015838,000194: 
015839,000195: E6,1527                        MULTFLAG           ERASE                                  	# INDICATOR FOR SPDPMULT ROUTINE
015840,000196: 
015841,000197: E6,1530                        FUNCTION           ERASE    +1                            	# D.P. WORD FOR DRIVE FUNCTIONS
015842,000198: 
015843,000199: E6,1532                        NEGUQ              ERASE    +2                            	# NEGATIVE OF Q-AXIS GIMBAL DRIVE
015844,000200: E6,1535  E6,1533               THRSTCMD           EQUALS   NEGUQ      +1                 	# THRUST COMMAND AT 16384 LBS (SEPARATOR)
015845,000201: E6,1535  E6,1534               NEGUR              EQUALS   NEGUQ      +2                 	# NEGATIVE OF R-AXIS GIMBAL DRIVE
015846,000202: 
015847,000203: E6,1535                        KQ                 ERASE    +3                            	# .3ACCDOTQ SCALED AT PI/2(8)
015848,000204: E6,1541  E6,1536               KQ2                EQUALS   KQ         +1                 	# KQ2 = KQ*KQ
015849,000205: E6,1541  E6,1537               KR                 EQUALS   KQ         +2                 	# .3ACCDOTR SCALED AT PI/2(8)
015850,000206: E6,1541  E6,1540               KR2                EQUALS   KQ         +3                 	# KR2 = KR*KR
015851,000207: 
015852,000208: E6,1541                        ACCDOTQ            ERASE    +3                            	# Q-JERK SCALED AT PI/2(7) UNSIGNED
015853,000209: E6,1545  E6,1542               QACCDOT            EQUALS   ACCDOTQ    +1                 	# Q-JERK SCALED AT PI/2(7) SIGNED
015854,000210: E6,1545  E6,1543               ACCDOTR            EQUALS   ACCDOTQ    +2                 	# R-JERK SCALED AT PI/2(7) UNSIGNED
015855,000211: E6,1545  E6,1544               RACCDOT            EQUALS   ACCDOTQ    +3                 	# R-JERK SCALED AT PI/2(7) SIGNED
015856,000212: 
015857,000213: E6,1545  E6,1477               QDIFF              EQUALS   QERROR                        	# ATTITUDE ERRORS:
015858,000214: E6,1545  E6,1500               RDIFF              EQUALS   RERROR                        	# SCALED AT PI RADIANS
015859,000215: 
015860,000216: E6,1545                        TIMEOFFQ           ERASE                                  	# TIMES TO GO UNTIL TRIM GIMBAL TURN-OFF.
015861,000217: E6,1546                        TIMEOFFR           ERASE                                  	# ZERO MEANS NO ACTION, SCALED AS WAITLIST
015862,000218: 
015864,000220:                                                                                          	# KALMAN FILTER ERASABLES.
015865,000221: 
015866,000222: E6,1547                        STORCDUY           ERASE                                  	# THIS S.P. PAIR IS USED TO SAVE CDUY,Z
015867,000223: E6,1550                        STORCDUZ           ERASE                                  	# FOR THE GTS RUPT
015868,000224: 
015869,000225: E6,1551     0076               CDU                EQUALS   RUPTREG3                      	# RUPTREG3,4 USED AS D.P. WORD FOR CDU
015870,000226:                                                                                          	# VALUE WITHIN FILTER 1S COMP AT 2PI RAD
015871,000227:

015873,000229:                                                                                          	# VALUE WITHIN FILTER SCALED AT PI/4

015876,000232:                                                                                          	# VALUE WITHIN FILTER SCALED AT PI/8

015879,000235: E6,1552                        DAPTIME            ERASE                                  	# USED TO RECORD LAST TIME FROM CHANNEL 4

015882,000238:

015884,000240: E6,1556                        WPOINTER           ERASE                                  	# POINTER TO WEIGHTING VECTOR TABLE
015885,000241: E6,1557                        W0                 ERASE    +2                            	# THETA WEIGHT
015886,000242: E6,1562  E6,1560               W1                 EQUALS   W0         +1                 	# OMEGA WEIGHT

015888,000244:

015890,000246: E6,1564                        CDUZFIL            ERASE    +1                            	# Z-AXIS D.P. FILTERED THETA AT 2PI
015891,000247: E6,1566                        DCDUYFIL           ERASE    +1                            	# Y-AXIS D.P. FILTERED OMEGA AT PI/4
015892,000248: E6,1570                        DCDUZFIL           ERASE    +1                            	# Z-AXIS D.P. FILTERED OMEGA AT PI/4

015904,000260:

015907,000263: E6,1620  E6,1616               JETRATEQ           EQUALS   JETRATE    +1                 	# THE LAST CONTROL SAMPLE PERIOD OF 100 MS

015928,000284:

015948,000304:

015951,000307:                                                                                          	# SCALED AT PI RADIANS
015952,000308:

015954,000310: E6,1655  E6,1651               .5ACCMNQ           EQUALS   .5ACCMNE   +1                 	# THE MINIMUM ACCELERATION (A CONSTANT FOR
015955,000311: E6,1655  E6,1652               .5ACCMNR           EQUALS   .5ACCMNE   +2                 	# DESCENT AND A VARIABLE FOR ASCENT DAP)

015957,000313: E6,1655  E6,1654               .5ACCMNV           EQUALS   .5ACCMNE   +4                 	# IN UNITS OF SECONDS(2)/RADIAN
015958,000314:

015961,000317:

015964,000320:

015966,000322: E6,1665  E6,1662               1/NJTSR            EQUALS   1/NJTSQ    +1                 	# FOR DESCENT THIS IS ALWAYS 1/2JTS
015968,000324: E6,1665  E6,1663               1/NJTSU            EQUALS   1/NJTSQ    +2                 	# FOR ASCENT WITH HIGH OFFSET: 1/4JTS
015969,000325: E6,1665  E6,1664               1/NJTSV            EQUALS   1/NJTSQ    +3                 	# SCALED AT 2(8)/PI SEC(2)/RAD
015970,000326: 
015971,000327: E6,1665                        QMANDACC           ERASE    +3                            	# ASCENT FLAGS
015972,000328: E6,1671  E6,1666               RMANDACC           EQUALS   QMANDACC   +1                 	# 0: INDICATES NO OVER-RIDE OF 2 JETS
015973,000329: E6,1671  E6,1667               UMANDACC           EQUALS   QMANDACC   +2                 	# 1: INDICATES USE 4 INSTEAD OF 2 JETS
015974,000330: E6,1671  E6,1670               VMANDACC           EQUALS   QMANDACC   +3                 	# (ALWAYS ZERO FOR DESCENT)
015975,000331: 
015976,000332: E6,1671                        KCOEFCTR           ERASE                                  	# COUNTER FOR ASCENT DAP
015977,000333: 
015978,000334: 
015979,000335:                                                                                          	# THE SAVE RATE INDEX AND THE THREE DELCDUS ARE LOCATED HERE TEMPORARILY, AWAITING MORE LOGICAL PLACEMENT WHEN THE
015980,000336:                                                                                          	# DAP IS ASSEMBLED INTO SUNBURST
015981,000337: 
015982,000338: E6,1672                        DLCDUIDX           ERASE                                  	# SAVE RATE INDEX, = 1, 0
015983,000339: E6,1673                        DELCDUX            ERASE                                  	#
015984,000340: E6,1674                        DELCDUY            ERASE                                  	# DELCDUS ARE SCALED AT P1, LIKE THE CDUS
015985,000341: E6,1675                        DELCDUZ            ERASE                                  	#
(End of include-file DIGITAL_AUTOPILOT_ERASABLE.agc, resuming main.agc)

016024,000038:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING SECTION DRIVES THE ATTITUDE ERROR NEEDLES IN THE "EIGHT-BALL" DISPLAY:
016025,000039: 
016026,000040: 23,2000           22765        EIGHTBAL           LXCH     DAPBOOLS                      	# ATTITUDE ERRORS DISPLAYED EVERY
016027,000041: 23,2001           37651                           CAF      BIT7                          	# OTHER DAP CYCLE (.2 SECS)
016028,000042: 23,2002           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# CHANGE STATE OF FLAG
016029,000043: 23,2003           06001                           RXOR     L                             	#
016030,000044: 23,2004           54765                           TS       DAPBOOLS                      	# FLAG WORD RESTORE
016031,000045: 23,2005           77651                           MASK     BIT7                          	#
016032,000046: 23,2006           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# ZERO AS NEW STATE MEANS
016033,000047: 23,2007           12146                           BZF      PAXFILT                       	# NO DISPLAY THIS CYCLE
016034,000048:

016036,000050: 23,2011           54065                           TS       ITEMP1                        	#
016037,000051: 23,2012           50000                           INDEX    A                             	#
016039,000053: 23,2013           11476                           CCS      PERROR                        	# LOOK AT CURRENT ATT ERROR
016040,000054: 23,2014           12037                           TCF      ERLIMCHK                      	# HAVE E VALUE GET MAGNITUDE
016041,000055: 23,2015           12017                           TCF      ZERR                          	# ZERO VALUE
016042,000056: 23,2016           12037                           TCF      ERLIMCHK                      	# GET MAGNITUDE
016043,000057: 23,2017           50065        ZERR               INDEX    ITEMP1                        	#
016044,000058: 23,2020           41476                           CS       PERROR                        	#
016045,000059: 23,2021           50065                           INDEX    ITEMP1                        	#
016046,000060: 23,2022           57473                           XCH      LASTPER                       	# SAVE CURRENT E, LOAD LAST E (NEG)
016047,000061: 23,2023           50065                           INDEX    ITEMP1                        	#
016048,000062: 23,2024           61476                           AD       PERROR                        	# GET DIFF E(N-2) - E(N)
016050,000064: 23,2025           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
016051,000065: 23,2026           77643                           MP       BIT13                         	# SHIFT RIGHT 2
016052,000066: 23,2027           50065                           INDEX    ITEMP1                        	#

016080,000094: 23,2051           40000                           CS       5DEGS                         	#

016084,000098: 
016085,000099:                                                                                          	# END OF ATTITUDE ERROR NEEDLE DRIVER.  (SHOULD GO IN-LINE SOMETIME.)
016086,000100: 
016087,000101: 
016088,000102:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING T5RUPT ENTRY BEGINS THE PROGRAM WHICH CONTROLS THE P-AXIS ACTION OF THE LEM USING THE RCS JETS.
016089,000103:                                                                                          	# THE NOMINAL TIME BETWEEN THE P-AXIS RUPTS IS 100 MS IN ALL NON-IDLING MODES OF THE DAP.
016090,000104: 
016091,000105: 23,2055           33072        PAXIS              CAF      MS30P                         	# RESET TIMER IMMEDIATELY: DT = 30 MS
016092,000106: 23,2056           54030                           TS       TIME5                         	#
016093,000107: 
016094,000108: 23,2057           22016                           LXCH     BANKRUPT                      	# INTERRUPT LEAD IN (CONTINUED)
016095,000109: 23,2060           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
016096,000110: 23,2061           22012                           QXCH     QRUPT                         	#
016097,000111: 
016098,000112:                                                                                          	# CHECK TO SEE IF DAP IS STILL IN USE:
016099,000113: 
016100,000114: 23,2062           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# IF BOTH BITS 13 AND 14 OF CHANNEL 31 ARE
016101,000115: 23,2063           00031                           READ     31                            	# EQUAL TO 1, THEN THE SCS MODE SWITCH IS
016102,000116: 23,2064           40000                           COM                                    	# IN THE OFF POSITION.  ACTUALLY, THE TEST
P-AXIS_REACTION_CONTROL_SYSTEM_AUTOPILOT.agc:117: Fatal Error: Symbol "BITS13-14" undefined or offset bad
016103,000117: 23,2065           70000                           MASK     BITS13-14                     	# IS MADE ON BOTH THE ATTITUDE HOLD AND
016104,000118: 23,2066           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# AUTOMATIC MODE BITS.
016105,000119: 23,2067           13124                           BZF      GOIDLE                        	#
016106,000120: 
016107,000121:                                                                                          	# WHILE DAP ON, SET UP EITHER A KALMAN FILTER RUPT OR A DUMMY FILTER RUPT BY SETTING UP T5ADR FROM ERASABLE.
016108,000122: 
016109,000123: 23,2070           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# T5ADR IS SET TO EITHER FILTER OR
016110,000124: 23,2071           31602                           DCA      PFILTADR                      	# DUMMYFIL IN A BLIND MANNER SINCE
016111,000125: 23,2072           52346                           DXCH     T5ADR                         	# PFILTADR IS SET UP ELSEWHERE
016112,000126: 
016113,000127:                                                                                          	# DO P AXIS RATE DERIVATION AND CONTROL LAW.
016114,000128:                                                                                          	# DERIVE DELTA P.
016115,000129:

016120,000134: 23,2077           23431                           LXCH     OLDXFORP                      	#
016121,000135: 23,2100           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
016122,000136: 23,2101           77651                           MP       BIT7                          	#

016124,000138: 23,2103           30033                           CA       CDUY                          	#
016125,000139: 23,2104           54001                           TS       L                             	#
016126,000140: 23,2105           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
016127,000141: 23,2106           21432                           MSU      OLDYFORP                      	# SCALED AT PI
016128,000142: 23,2107           23432                           LXCH     OLDYFORP                      	#

016132,000146: 23,2112           31404                           CA       M11                           	# M11 SCALED AT 1
016133,000147: 23,2113           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
016134,000148: 23,2114           70001                           MP       L                             	# INTO A SCALED AT PI/2(6).
016135,000149: 23,2115           60066                           AD       DELTAP                        	#
016136,000150: 23,2116           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
016137,000151: 23,2117           71655                           MP       WFORP                         	# SCALED AT 2(4)=16, RESULT IN A AT PI/4.
016138,000152: 23,2120           57416                           XCH      OMEGAP                        	# W*DELTAP IN OMEGAP LOC. OLD OMEGAP IN A.
016139,000153: 23,2121           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
016140,000154: 23,2122           73066                           MP       ONE-K                         	# SCALED AT 1.
016142,000156: 23,2123           61615                           AD       JETRATE                       	# RATE DUE TO JETS TORQUING.
016143,000157: 23,2124           27416                           ADS      OMEGAP                        	# PRATE= WFORP*DELTAP+ALPHA*LAST-PRATE+TPF
016144,000158: 23,2125           04177                           TC       T6JOBCHK                      	# T6JOBCHK IS IN FIXED-FIXED
016145,000159: 
016146,000160:                                                                                          	# ***** KALCMANU-DAP AND "RATE-HOLD"-DAP INTERFACE *****
016147,000161: 
016148,000162:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING SECTION IS EXECUTED EVERY 100 MS (10 TIMES A SECOND) WITHIN THE P-AXIS REACTION CONTROL SYSTEM
016149,000163:                                                                                          	# AUTOPILOT (WHENEVER THE DAP IS IN OPERATION).
016150,000164: 
016151,000165: 23,2126           37656                           CAF      TWO                           	# SET UP LOOP TO DO Z,Y,X CDU AXES:
016152,000166: 23,2127           54073        KALCLOOP           TS       QRCNTR                        	#
016153,000167: 
016154,000168: 23,2130           50073                           INDEX    QRCNTR                        	# KALCMANU AND RATE-HOLD USE THIS SECTION
016155,000169: 23,2131           30774                           CAE      CDUXD                         	# TO PERFORM THEIR INDEPENDENT FUNCTIONS:
016156,000170: 23,2132           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# BOTH PROCEDURES SET UP THE DELCUD'S
016157,000171: 23,2133           50073                           INDEX    QRCNTR                        	# TO HAVE THE NEGATIVE VALUE OF THE
016158,000172: 23,2134           21673                           MSU      DELCDUX                       	# DESIRED CDU CHANGE FOR EACH 100 MS CSP
016159,000173: 23,2135           10000                           CCS      A                             	# DURING THE MANEUVER (OR MODE).  EACH IS
016160,000174: 23,2136           67657                           AD       ONE                           	# STORED AT PI RADIANS IN 2'S COMPLEMENT.
016161,000175: 23,2137           12141                           TCF      +2                            	# SINCE THE MODULAR SUBTRACT YIELDS THE
016162,000176: 23,2140           40000                           COM                                    	# NEW CDUD VALUE IN 1'S COMPLEMENT, THE
016163,000177: 23,2141           50073                           INDEX    QRCNTR                        	# CCS SECTION IS NEEDED FOR 1'S TO 2'S
016164,000178: 23,2142           54774                           TS       CDUXD                         	# CONVERSION OF DESIRED CDU ANGLES.
016165,000179: 
016166,000180: 23,2143           10073                           CCS      QRCNTR                        	# (THIS MAKES THE LOOP DO ALL THREE AXES
016167,000181: 23,2144           12127                           TCF      KALCLOOP                      	# IN THE ORDER Z, Y, X.)
016168,000182: 
016169,000183:

016425,000439:                                                                                          	#              2-JET JET SELECT LOGIC
016426,000440:                                                                                          	# READ CHANNEL 6 TO SEE WHAT THE CURRENT STATE OF THE P JETS IS AND
016427,000441:                                                                                          	#     CORRECT THE JET TIME FOR THE PROPER AMOUNT OF TIME .
016428,000442: 23,2462           00006        2PJETS             EXTEND                                 	# WHAT IS THE CURRENT STATE OF THE P JETS.

016437,000451:                                                                                          	# ........................................................................

016618,000632: 23,2717           12742                           TCF      T6ONNOW                       	#  IF T6 IS + THEN CLOCK IS ON.
016619,000633: 23,2720           12724                           TCF      T6OFFNOW                      	#  IF T6 IS + ZERO THEN T6 MUST BE OFF
016620,000634: 23,2721           12742                           TCF      T6ONNOW                       	#    SINCE ALL DINC S LEAD TO MINUS ZERO.
016621,000635: 23,2722           04203                           TC       T6JOB                         	# WE ARE IN THE UNIQUE STATE WHICH SAYS
016622,000636: 23,2723           12716                           TCF      JTLST                         	#   A T6 INTERRUPT IS WAITING.DO T6 JOB.

016629,000643: 23,2732           54770                           TS       T6NEXTJT                      	#
016630,000644: 23,2733           37665                           CA       ZERO                          	#

016633,000647:

016640,000654: 23,2744           41505                           CS       TOFJTCHG                      	# T6NEXT IS NEVER NEGATIVE.

016795,000011:                                                                                          	# This source code has been transcribed or otherwise adapted from
016796,000012:                                                                                          	# digitized images of a hardcopy from the private collection of 
016797,000013:                                                                                          	# Don Eyles.  The digitization was performed by archive.org.
016798,000014: 
016799,000015:                                                                                          	# Notations on the hardcopy document read, in part:
016800,000016: 
016801,000017:                                                                                          	#       473423A YUL SYSTEM FOR BLK2: REVISION 12 of PROGRAM AURORA BY DAP GROUP
016802,000018:                                                                                          	#       NOV 10, 1966
016803,000019: 
016804,000020:                                                                                          	#       [Note that this is the date the hardcopy was made, not the
016805,000021:                                                                                          	#       date of the program revision or the assembly.]
016806,000022: 
016807,000023:                                                                                          	# The scan images (with suitable reduction in storage size and consequent 
016808,000024:                                                                                          	# reduction in image quality) are available online at 
016809,000025:                                                                                          	#       https://www.ibiblio.org/apollo.  
016810,000026:                                                                                          	# The original high-quality digital images are available at archive.org:
016811,000027:                                                                                          	#       https://archive.org/details/aurora00dapg
016812,000028: 
016814,000030:                                                                                          	# THE DAPIDLER PROGRAM IS STARTED BY FRESH START AND RESTART.             THE DAPIDLER PROGRAM IS DONE 10 TIMES
016815,000031:                                                                                          	# PER SECOND UNTIL THE ASTRONAUT DESIRES THE DAP TO WAKE UP, AND THE IMU AND CDUS ARE READY FOR USE BY THE DAP.
016816,000032:                                                                                          	# THE NECESSARY INITIALIZATION OF THE DAP IS DONE BY THE DAPIDLER PROGRAM.
016817,000033:                                                                                          	# ADDITIONAL WORK MUST BE DONE ON DAPIDLER IN THE FUTURE.

DAPIDLER_PROGRAM.agc:149: Fatal Error: Symbol "IZZMASK" undefined or offset bad
016933,000149: 23,3277           00000 00000                     2CADR    IZZMASK                       	#
016934,000150: 
016935,000151:                                                                                          	# THIS SECTION COMPUTES THE RATE OF CHANGE OF ACCELERATION DUE TO THE
016936,000152:                                                                                          	#   ROTATION OF THE GIMBAL ENGINE. THE EQUATION IMPLEMENTED IN BOTH THE
016937,000153:                                                                                          	#   X-Y PLANE AND THE Z-X PLANE IS -- D(ALPHA)/DT = T L/I * D(DELTA)/DT
016938,000154:                                                                                          	#   WHERE ----
016939,000155:                                                                                          	#             T = ENGINE THRUST COMMAND
016940,000156:                                                                                          	#             L = PIVOT TO CG DISTANCE OF THE GIMBAL ANGLE
016941,000157:                                                                                          	#             I = INERTIA
016942,000158:                                                                                          	#             DELTA = GIMBAL ENGINE ANGLE MEASURED FROM THE X AXIS.
016943,000159: 
016944,000160: 23,3301           33403                           CAF      DELTADOT                      	# 0.2 DEG/SEC SCALED AT PI/64
016945,000161: 23,3302           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
016946,000162: 23,3303           71526                           MP       L,PVT-CG                      	# GIMBAL PIVOT TO C.G. DISTANCE ,SCALE=8.
016947,000163: 23,3304           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
016948,000164: 23,3305           71533                           MP       THRSTCMD                      	# COMMANDED THRUST SCALED AT 2(14) =16384.
016949,000165: 23,3306           52066                           DXCH     ITEMP1                        	#
016950,000166: 23,3307           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
016951,000167: 23,3310           30066                           DCA      ITEMP1                        	#
016952,000168: 23,3311           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
016953,000169: 23,3312           11463                           DV       IZZ                           	# AT 2(18)
016954,000170: 23,3313           55543                           TS       ACCDOTR                       	# AT PI/2(7)
016955,000171: 23,3314           52066                           DXCH     ITEMP1                        	#
016956,000172: 23,3315           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
016957,000173: 23,3316           11462                           DV       IYY                           	# AT 2(18)
016958,000174: 23,3317           55541                           TS       ACCDOTQ                       	# AT PI/2(7)
016959,000175:

017056,000028:                                                                                          	#       https://archive.org/details/aurora00dapg
017057,000029: 
017059,000031: 24,2000                                           BANK     24                            	#
017060,000032: 24,2000  E6,1551                                  EBANK=   DT                            	#
017061,000033:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING T5RUPT ENTRY BEGINS THE PROGRAM WHICH CONTROLS THE Q,R-AXIS ACTION OF THE LEM USING THE RCS JETS.
017062,000034:                                                                                          	# THE NOMINAL TIME BETWEEN THE Q,R-AXIS RUPTS IS 100 MS (UNLESS THE TRIM GIMBAL CONTROL SYSTEM IS USED, IN WHICH
017063,000035:                                                                                          	# CASE THIS PROGRAM IS IDLE).
017064,000036: 
017065,000037: 24,2000           02555 54066  NULLFILT           2CADR    FILDUMMY                      	#
017066,000038: 
017067,000039: 24,2002           32705        QRAXIS             CAF      MS30QR                        	# RESET TIME IMMEDIATELY: DT = 30 MS
017068,000040: 24,2003           54030                           TS       TIME5                         	#
017069,000041: 
017070,000042: 24,2004           22016                           LXCH     BANKRUPT                      	# INTERRUPT LEAD IN (CONTINUED)
017071,000043: 24,2005           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
017072,000044: 24,2006           22012                           QXCH     QRUPT                         	#
017073,000045: 
017074,000046:                                                                                          	# SET UP DUMMY KALMAN FILTER T5RUPT.  (THIS MAY BE RESET TO THE KALMAN FILTER INITIALIZATION PASS, IF THE TRIM
017075,000047:                                                                                          	# GIMBAL CONTROL SYSTEM SHOULD BE USED.)
017076,000048: 
017077,000049: 24,2007           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
017078,000050: 24,2010           32001                           DCA      NULLFILT                      	#
017079,000051: 24,2011           52346                           DXCH     T5ADR                         	#
017080,000052: 
017081,000053:                                                                                          	# CALCULATE LEM BODY RATES FOR Q AND R AXES:
017082,000054: 
017083,000055:                                                                                          	# THIS COMPUTATION IS VALID FOR BOTH ASCENT ADN DESCENT SINCE THE OFFSET ACCELERATION TERM IS INCLUDED ALWAYS,
017084,000056:                                                                                          	# BUT HAS VALUE ZERO IN DESCENT, AND SINCE THE WEIGHTING FACTORS ARE IN ERASABLE AND DISTINCT.
017085,000057: 
017086,000058:                                                                                          	# FIRST, CONSTRUCT Y AND Z CDU INCREMENTS:
017087,000059: 
017088,000060: 24,2012           30033                           CAE      CDUY                          	# 2'S COMPLEMENT MEASUREMENT SCALED AT PI
017089,000061: 24,2013           54001                           TS       L                             	# (SAVE FOR UPDATING OF OLDYFORQ)
017090,000062: 24,2014           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# FORM INCREMENT IN CDUY FOR LAST 100 MS
017091,000063: 24,2015           21433                           MSU      OLDYFORQ                      	# (100 MS OLD CDUY SAVED FROM LAST PASS)
017092,000064: 24,2016           23433                           LXCH     OLDYFORQ                      	# UPDATE OLDYFORQ WITH NEW CDUY VALUE
017093,000065: 24,2017           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# RESCALE DELTA CDUY FROM PI RADIANS TO
017094,000066: 24,2020           77651                           MP       BIT7                          	# PI/2(6) RADIANS BY MULTIPLYING BY 64
017095,000067: 24,2021           22065                           LXCH     ITEMP1                        	# SAVE 1'S COMPLEMENT VALUE TEMPORARILY
017096,000068: 24,2022           30034                           CAE      CDUZ                          	# 2'S COMPLEMENT MEASUREMENT SCALED AT PI
017097,000069: 24,2023           54001                           TS       L                             	# (SAVE FOR UPDATING OF OLDZFORQ)
017098,000070: 24,2024           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# FORM INCREMENT IN CDUZ FOR LAST 100 MS
017099,000071: 24,2025           21434                           MSU      OLDZFORQ                      	# (100 MS OLD CDUZ SAVED FROM LAST PASS)
017100,000072: 24,2026           23434                           LXCH     OLDZFORQ                      	# UPDATE OLDZFORQ WITH NEW CDUZ VALUE
017101,000073: 24,2027           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# RESCALE DELTA CDUZ FROM PI RADIANS TO
017102,000074: 24,2030           77651                           MP       BIT7                          	# PI/2(6) RADIANS BY MULTIPLYING BY 64
017103,000075: 24,2031           22066                           LXCH     ITEMP2                        	# SVAE 1'S COMPLEMENT VALUE TEMPORARILY
017104,000076: 
017106,000078: 
017107,000079:                                                                                          	# SECOND TRANSFORM CPU INCREMENTS TO BODY-ANGLE INCREMENTS:
017108,000080: 24,2032           31406                           CAE      M31                           	# MATRIX*VECTOR(WITH x COMPONENT ZERO)
017109,000081: 24,2033           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
017110,000082: 24,2034           70065                           MP       ITEMP1                        	# M31 * ITEMP1 = M31 * DELTA CDUY
017111,000083: 24,2035           54070                           TS       ITEMP3                        	#
017112,000084: 24,2036           31403                           CAE      M32                           	# M32 * ITEMP2 = M32 * DELTA CDUZ
017113,000085: 24,2037           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
017114,000086: 24,2040           70066                           MP       ITEMP2                        	# DELTAR = M31*(DEL CDUY) + M32*(DEL CDUZ)
017115,000087: 24,2041           26070                           ADS      ITEMP3                        	# R-BODY-ANGLE INCREMENT SCALED AT PI/2(6)
017116,000088: 
017117,000089: 24,2042           31405                           CAE      M21                           	# MATRIX*VECTOR(WITH X COMPONENT ZERO)
017118,000090: 24,2043           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# CLOBBERS ITEMP2=DEL CDUZ, FOR EFFICIENCY
017119,000091: 24,2044           70065                           MP       ITEMP1                        	# M21 * ITEMP1 = M21 * DELTA CDUY
017120,000092: 24,2045           56066                           XCH      ITEMP2                        	# M22 * ITEMP2 = M22 * DELTA CDUZ
017121,000093: 24,2046           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
017122,000094: 24,2047           71401                           MP       M22                           	# DELTAQ = M21*(DEL CDUY) + M22*(DEL CDUZ)
017123,000095: 24,2050           26066                           ADS      ITEMP2                        	# Q-BODY-ANGLE INCREMENT SCALED AT PI/2(6)
017124,000096: 
017125,000097:                                                                                          	# FINALLY, DERIVE Q AND R BODY ANGULAR RATES:
017126,000098: 
017127,000099: 24,2051           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# WFORQR IS K/(NOMINAL DT) SCALED AT 16
017128,000100: 24,2052           71656                           MP       WFORQR                        	# FORM WEIGHTED VALUE OF MEASURED DATA
017129,000101: 24,2053           57417                           XCH      OMEGAQ                        	# SAVE AND BEGIN TO WEIGHT VALUE OF OLD W
017130,000102: 24,2054           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# (1-K) IS SCALED AT 1 FOR EFFICIENT CALC
017131,000103: 24,2055           71657                           MP       (1-K)QR                       	# (K CHANGES EVERY 2 SECS IN ASCENT)
017132,000104: 24,2056           61616                           AD       JETRATEQ                      	# WEIGHTED TERM DUE TO JET ACCELERATION
017133,000105: 24,2057           61642                           AD       AOSQTERM                      	# TERM DUE TO ASCENT OFFSET ACCELERATION
017134,000106: 24,2060           27417                           ADS      OMEGAQ                        	# TOTAL RATE ESTIMATE SCALED AT PI/4
017135,000107: 
017136,000108: 24,2061           30070                           CAE      ITEMP3                        	# GET DELTAR
017137,000109: 24,2062           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# WFORQR IS K/(NOMINAL DT) SCALED AT 16
017138,000110: 24,2063           71656                           MP       WFORQR                        	# FORM WEIGHTED VALUE OF MEASURED DATA
017139,000111: 24,2064           57421                           XCH      OMEGAR                        	# SAVE AND BEGIN TO WEIGHT VALUE OF OLD W
017140,000112: 24,2065           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# (1-K) IS SCALED AT 1 FOR EFFICIENT CALC
017141,000113: 24,2066           71657                           MP       (1-K)QR                       	# (K CHANGES EVERY 2 SECS IN ASCENT)
017142,000114: 24,2067           61617                           AD       JETRATER                      	# WEIGHTED TERM DUE TO JET ACCELERATION
017143,000115: 24,2070           61643                           AD       AOSRTERM                      	# TERM DUE TO ASCENT OFFSET ACCELERATION
017144,000116: 24,2071           27421                           ADS      OMEGAR                        	# TOTAL RATE ESTIMATE SCALED AT PI/4
017145,000117: 
017146,000118: 24,2072           01614                           TC       QJUMPADR                      	#
017147,000119: 24,2073           32164        SKIPQRAX           CA       NORMQADR                      	#
017148,000120: 24,2074           55614                           TS       QJUMPADR                      	#
017149,000121: 24,2075           37665                           CA       ZERO                          	#
017150,000122: 24,2076           55616                           TS       JETRATEQ                      	#
017151,000123: 24,2077           55617                           TS       JETRATER                      	#
017152,000124: 24,2100           31626                           CA       TQR                           	#
017153,000125: 24,2101           62721                           AD       NEGCSP2                       	#
017154,000126: 24,2102           10000                           CCS      A                             	#
017155,000127: 24,2103           02113                           TC       QRTORQUE                      	#
017156,000128: 
017158,000130: 24,2104           14606                           TCF      RESUME                        	#
017159,000131: 24,2105           02113                           TC       QRTORQUE                      	#
017160,000132: 24,2106           41616                           CS       JETRATEQ                      	#
017161,000133: 24,2107           27417                           ADS      OMEGAQ                        	#
017162,000134: 24,2110           41617                           CS       JETRATER                      	#

017165,000137: 24,2113           67657        QRTORQUE           AD       ONE                           	#
017166,000138: 24,2114           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
017167,000139: 24,2115           77653                           MP       BIT5                          	#
017168,000140: 24,2116           30001                           CA       L                             	#
017169,000141: 24,2117           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
017170,000142: 24,2120           72722                           MP       16/25QR                       	#
